g the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nPlug and Play activity records events related to the successful connection of external devices.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-77941","V-63451","CCI-000172","CCI-003938","CCI-001814"],"reference_identifier":"6367","uuid":"f068c2a0-aa33-42ac-8913-fcf03a44d92e","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8C43DE01F3FC523B2285628EFD1A52488674EC41\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The system must be configured to audit Detailed Tracking - PNP Activity successes.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220754","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220754","title":"SRG-OS-000365-GPOS-00152","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220754","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000365-GPOS-00152","rule_id_src":"SV-220754r1051026_rule","rule_id":"SV-220754","rule_version":"WN10-AU-000050","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit Detailed Tracking - Process Creation successes.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Detailed Tracking >> \"Audit Process Creation\" with \"Success\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN10-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nDetailed Tracking >> Process Creation - Success","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nProcess creation records events related to the creation of a process and the source.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63453","SV-77943","CCI-000172","CCI-003938","CCI-001814"],"reference_identifier":"8712","uuid":"0fa22592-08ce-4818-bbd5-5f4e9e168dcc","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BC854773CF261674532C5E9F1623458CE44D525D\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The system must be configured to audit Detailed Tracking - Process Creation successes.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220755","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220755","title":"SRG-OS-000470-GPOS-00214","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220755","severity":"medium","group_ti