ity":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89083","V-74409","CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"6197","uuid":"9b515533-bb19-4341-812d-8c51d2c6f504","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 367E1E348210723A3462F8251B58CC961CC13108\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows 10 must be configured to audit Object Access - Other Object Access Events failures.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220765","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220765","title":"SRG-OS-000474-GPOS-00219","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220765","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000474-GPOS-00219","rule_id_src":"SV-220765r991583_rule","rule_id":"SV-220765","rule_version":"WN10-AU-000085","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit Object Access - Removable Storage failures.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Object Access >> \"Audit Removable Storage\" with \"Failure\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN10-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nObject Access >> Removable Storage - Failure\n\nSome virtual machines may generate excessive audit events for access to the virtual hard disk itself when this setting is enabled. This may be set to Not Configured in such cases and would not be a finding.  This must be documented with the ISSO to include mitigations such as monitoring or restricting any actual removable storage connected to the VM.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks.  Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised.  Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAuditing object access for removable media records events related to access attempts on file system objects on removable storage devices.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-77961","V-63471","CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"9407","uuid":"69d8dc7d-ae76-46fa-a1ef-3e857f32392a","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6B091B2C9EBF388A500D5A720CEFD90335D58C05\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The system must be configured to audit Object Access - Removable Storage failures.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220766","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220766","title":"SRG-OS-000474-GPOS-00219","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220766","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000