ing object access for removable media records events related to access attempts on file system objects on removable storage devices.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63473","SV-77963","CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"4826","uuid":"b7fb872f-e44a-41e8-86b3-0d67b4e07b6f","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 363BE895DB96410133955C1AD128AC3C23BE1CDB\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The system must be configured to audit Object Access - Removable Storage successes.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220767","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220767","title":"SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00215","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220767","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00215","rule_id_src":"SV-220767r991579_rule","rule_id":"SV-220767","rule_version":"WN10-AU-000100","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit Policy Change - Audit Policy Change successes.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Policy Change >> \"Audit Audit Policy Change\" with \"Success\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN10-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges 