system must be configured to audit System - Other System Events successes.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220774","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220774","title":"SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00215","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220774","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00215","rule_id_src":"SV-220774r991579_rule","rule_id":"SV-220774","rule_version":"WN10-AU-000135","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit System - Other System Events failures.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> System >> \"Audit Other System Events\" with \"Failure\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN10-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective. \n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following.  If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nSystem >> Other System Events - Failure","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAudit Other System Events records information related to cryptographic key operations and the Windows Firewall service.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-77993","V-63503","CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"1362","uuid":"7c0d1f8c-84f3-4a50-8e23-79a829f5fc1a","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 511B6E985BE8E1E977C33F426BABA4A0CE9AF11D\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'The system must be configured to audit System - Other System Events failures.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220775","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220775","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220775","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","rule_id_src":"SV-220775r958732_rule","rule_id":"SV-220775","rule_version":"WN10-AU-000140","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit System - Security State Change successes.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> System >> \"Audit Security State Change\" with \"Success\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN10-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following.  If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nSystem >> Security State Change - Success","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks.  Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised.  Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nSecurity State Change records events related to changes in the security state, such as startup and shutdown of the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63507","SV-77997","CCI-000172","CCI-002234"],"reference_identifier":"2668","uuid":"9eb48357-1edf-48e2-915a-5370415172ea","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: CBF1EE0B3FC21307EC1DD468A97756F5F963C579\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The system must be configured to audit System - Security State Change successes.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220776","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220776","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220776","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","rule_id_src