uration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks.  Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised.  Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nSystem Integrity records events related to violations of integrity to the security subsystem.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63515","SV-78005","CCI-000172","CCI-002234"],"reference_identifier":"1110","uuid":"3b975d65-a8a1-4cde-a751-cdef314b31c0","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4EC1D96C481919B0B067AAFD6214E6DA65CA8D51\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must be configured to audit System - System Integrity failures.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220778","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220778","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220778","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","rule_id_src":"SV-220778r958732_rule","rule_id":"SV-220778","rule_version":"WN10-AU-000160","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit System - System Integrity successes.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> System >> \"Audit System Integrity\" with \"Success\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN10-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following.  If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nSystem >> System Integrity - Success","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks.  Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised.  Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nSystem Integrity records events related to violations of integrity to the security subsystem.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78007","V-63517","CCI-000172","CCI-002234"],"reference_identifier":"5990","uuid":"1c06311a-033b-4d2a-aef0-8de4082c34ef","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 419EB2F04C1448E3718DD63B8634D4D7B3ADAD5A\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The system must be configured to audit System - System Integrity successes.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220779","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220779","title":"SRG-OS-000341-GPOS-00132","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220779","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000341-GPOS-00132","rule_id_src":"SV-220779r958752_rule","rule_id":"SV-220779","rule_version":"WN10-AU-000500","rule_title":"The Application event log size must be configured to 32768 KB or greater.","fix_text":"If the system is configured to send audit records directly to an audit server, this is NA.  This must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Event Log Service >> Application >> \"Specify the maximum log file size (KB)\" to \"Enabled\" with a \"Maximum Log Size (KB)\" of \"32768\" or greater.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is configured to send audit records directly to an audit server, this is NA.  This must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\EventLog\\Application\\\n\nValue Name:  MaxSize\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00008000 (32768) (or greater)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inadequate log size will cause the log to fill up quickly.  This may prevent audit events from being recorded properly and require frequent attention by administrative personnel.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63519","SV-78009","CCI-001849"],"reference_identifier":"5948","uuid":"5ff9b47a-e67e-4d71-a78b-d3992815be83","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 057E40A9ECC9D0A3EFAB49BEB5E7596F20AB096C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Application event log size must be configured to 32768 KB or greater.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220780","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220780","title":"SRG-OS-000341-GPOS-00132","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220780","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000341-GPOS-00132","rule_id_src":"SV-220780r958752_rule","rule_id":"SV-220780","rule_version":"WN10-AU-000505","rule_title":"The Security event log size must be configured to 1024000 KB or greater.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Event Log Service >> Security >> \"Specify the maximum log file size (KB)\" to \"Enabled\" with a \"Maximum Log Size (KB)\" of \"1024000\" or greater.\n\nIf the system is configured to send audit records directly to an audit server, documented with the ISSO.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is configured to send audit records directly to an audit server, this is NA. This must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\EventLog\\Security\\\n\nValue Name: MaxSize\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x000fa000 (1024000) (or greater)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inadequate log size will cause the log to fill up quickly.  This may prevent audit events from being recorded properly and require frequent attention by administrative personnel.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63523","SV-78013","CCI-001849"],"reference_identifier":"2989","uuid":"f4f176e5-2558-4de7-9baf-1beb0c739da3","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9B562A69E0E4B84E2EE558B31187AE53D53AA1BA\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Security event log size must be configured to 1024000 KB or greater.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220781","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220781","title":"SRG-OS-000341-GPOS-00132","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220781","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000341-GPOS-00132","rule_id_src":"SV-220781r958752_rule","rule_id":"SV-220781","rule_version":"WN10-AU-000510","rule_title":"The System event log size must be configured to 32768 KB or greater.","fix_text":"If the system is configured to send audit records directly to an audit server, this is NA.  This must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Event Log Service >> System >> \"Specify the maximum log file size (KB)\" to \"Enabled\" with a \"Maximum Log Size (KB)\" of \"32768\" or greater.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is configured to send audit records directly to an audit server, this is NA.  This must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\EventLog\\System\\\n\nValue Name:  MaxSize\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00008000 (32768) (or greater)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inadequate log size will cause the log to fill up quickly.  This may prevent audit events from being recorded properly and require frequent attention by administrative personnel.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78017","V-63527","CCI-001849"],"reference_identifier":"7421","uuid":"a2e32ef9-6e6e-418c-a70d-850e804f8562","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4D47AC16C8DD90C94EB93B4B404FD3460524A40F\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The System event log size must be configured to 32768 KB or greater.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220782","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220782","title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220782","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","rule_id_src":"SV-220782r958434_rule","rule_id":"SV-220782","rule_version":"WN10-AU-000515","rule_title":"Windows 10 permissions for the Application event log must prevent access by non-privileged accounts.","fix_text":"Ensure the permissions on the Application event log (Application.evtx) are configured to prevent standard user accounts or groups from having access. The default permissions listed below satisfy this requirement.\n\nEventlog - Full Control\nSYSTEM - Full Control\nAdministrators - Full Control\n\nThe default location is the \"%SystemRoot%\\SYSTEM32\\WINEVT\\LOGS\" directory.\n\nIf the location of the logs has been changed, when adding Eventlog to the permissions, it must be entered as \"NT Service\\Eventlog\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the permissions on the Application event log (Application.evtx). Standard user accounts or groups must not have access. The default permissions listed below satisfy this requirement.\n\nEventlog - Full Control\nSYSTEM - Full Control\nAdministrators - Full Control\n\nThe default location is the \"%SystemRoot%\\SYSTEM32\\WINEVT\\LOGS\" directory. They may have been moved to another folder.\n\nIf the permissions for these files are not as restrictive as the ACLs listed, this is a finding.\n\nNOTE: If \"APPLICATION PACKAGE AUTHORITY\\ALL APPLICATION PACKAGES\" has Special Permissions, this would not be a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks.  Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised.  The Application event log may be  susceptible to tampering if proper permissions are not applied.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63533","SV-78023","CCI-000162","CCI-000163","CCI-000164"],"reference_identifier":"7891","uuid":"d2739268-3882-4590-9b5c-3092cd73193f","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2B33B292EFF2778D0EA885430AF386DFBC99F86C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows 10 permissions for the Application event log must prevent access by non-privileged accounts.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220783","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220783","title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220783","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","rule_id_src":"SV-220783r958434_rule","rule_id":"SV-220783","rule_version":"WN10-AU-000520","rule_title":"Windows 10 permissions for the Security event log must prevent access by non-privileged accounts.","fix_text":"Ensure the permissions on the Security event log (Security.evtx) are configured to prevent standard user accounts or groups from having access.  The default permissions listed below satisfy this requirement.\n\nEventlog - Full Control\nSYSTEM - Full Control\nAdministrators - Full Control\n\nThe default location is the \"%SystemRoot%\\SYSTEM32\\WINEVT\\LOGS\" directory.\n\nIf the location of the logs has been changed, when adding Eventlog to the permissions, it must be entered as \"NT Service\\Eventlog\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the permissions on the Security event log (Security.evtx). Standard user accounts or groups must not have access. The default permissions listed below satisfy this requirement.\n\nEventlog - Full Control\nSYSTEM - Full Control\nAdministrators - Full Control\n\nThe default location is the \"%SystemRoot%\\SYSTEM32\\WINEVT\\LOGS\" directory. They may have been moved to another folder.\n\nIf the permissions for these files are not as restrictive as the ACLs listed, this is a finding.\n\nNOTE: If \"APPLICATION PACKAGE AUTHORITY\\ALL APPLICATION PACKAGES\" has Special Permissions, this would not be a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks.  Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised.  The Security event log may disclose sensitive information or be  susceptible to tampering if proper permissions are not applied.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63537","SV-78027","CCI-000162","CCI-000163","CCI-000164"],"reference_identifier":"8366","uuid":"8249a722-c7d6-41b1-9236-e1ea2c61300b","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FF5183032EA9D2FDAB0F4FBAF5736AE55B256C9A\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows 10 permissions for the Security event log must prevent access by non-privileged accounts.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220784","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220784","title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220784","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","rule_id_src":"SV-220784r958434_rule","rule_id":"SV-220784","rule_version":"WN10-AU-000525","rule_title":"Windows 10 permissions for the System event log must prevent access by non-privileged accounts.","fix_text":"Ensure the permissions on the System event log (System.evtx) are configured to prevent standard user accounts or groups from having access. The default permissions listed below satisfy this requirement.\n\nEventlog - Full Control\nSYSTEM - Full Control\nAdministrators - Full Control\n\nThe default location is the \"%SystemRoot%\\SYSTEM32\\WINEVT\\LOGS\" directory.\n\nIf the location of the logs has been changed, when adding Eventlog to the permissions, it must be entered as \"NT Service\\Eventlog\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the permissions on the System event log (System.evtx). Standard user accounts or groups must not have access. The default permissions listed below satisfy this requirement.\n\nEventlog - Full Control\nSYSTEM - Full Control\nAdministrators - Full Control\n\nThe default location is the \"%SystemRoot%\\SYSTEM32\\WINEVT\\LOGS\" directory. They may have been moved to another folder.\n\nIf the permissions for these files are not as restrictive as the ACLs listed, this is a finding.\n\nNOTE: If \"APPLICATION PACKAGE AUTHORITY\\ALL APPLICATION PACKAGES\" has Special Permissions, this would not be a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks.  Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised.  The System event log may be  susceptible to tampering if proper permissions are not applied.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63541","SV-78031","CCI-000162","CCI-000163","CCI-000164"],"reference_identifier":"2799","uuid":"39c55066-b200-48b5-884c-fea5d8f30a53","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 47A45A80D255FA2A2902FF69CD1C465DB0DDA784\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Windows 10 permissions for the System event log must prevent access by non-privileged accounts.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220786","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220786","title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220786","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","rule_id_src":"SV-220786r958412_rule","rule_id":"SV-220786","rule_version":"WN10-AU-000555","rule_title":"Windows 10 must be configured to audit Other Policy Change Events Failures.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Policy Change>> \"Audit Other Policy Change Events\" with \"Failure\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN10-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nPolicy Change  >> Other Policy Change Events - Failure","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAudit Other Policy Change Events contains events about EFS Data Recovery Agent policy changes, changes in Windows Filtering Platform filter, status on Security policy settings updates for local Group Policy settings, Central Access Policy changes, and detailed troubleshooting events for Cryptographic Next Generation (CNG) operations.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-99553","SV-108657","CCI-000130"],"reference_identifier":"2688","uuid":"35422b9f-b5ac-4066-90ac-2d9da35e0e8f","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: ADED3D97E5B8038EA4EDBB889FB693D86B7628F9\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows 10 must be configured to audit Other Policy Change Events Failures.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220787","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220787","title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220787","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","rule_id_src":"SV-220787r958412_rule","rule_id":"SV-220787","rule_version":"WN10-AU-000560","rule_title":"Windows 10 must be configured to audit other Logon/Logoff Events Successes.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Logon/Logoff >> \"Audit Other Logon/Logoff Events\" with \"Success\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN10-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nLogon/Logoff  >> Other Logon/Logoff Events - Success","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAudit Other Logon/Logoff Events determines whether Windows generates audit events for other logon or logoff events. Logon events are essential to understanding user activity and detecting potential attacks.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-99543","SV-108647","CCI-000130"],"reference_identifier":"5998","uuid":"8518b523-76e2-4ee7-91ee-a8e591bb5c21","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E33B0E81654A3741E71D714A2813974B73560860\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows 10 must be configured to audit other Logon/Logoff Events Successes.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220788","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220788","title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220788","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","rule_id_src":"SV-220788r958412_rule","rule_id":"SV-220788","rule_version":"WN10-AU-000565","rule_title":"Windows 10 must be configured to audit other Logon/Logoff Events Failures.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Logon/Logoff >> \"Audit Other Logon/Logoff Events\" with \"Failure\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN10-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nLogon/Logoff  >> Other Logon/Logoff Events - Failure","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAudit Other Logon/Logoff Events determines whether Windows generates audit events for other logon or logoff events. Logon events are essential to understanding user activity and detecting potential attacks.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-99541","SV-108645","CCI-000130"],"reference_identifier":"2901","uuid":"af42564d-c91c-4e43-8ec2-4b704c1c7c01","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 95A54F14B94FD49BD2D9F8401F9EB22E4A174A28\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows 10 must be configured to audit other Logon/Logoff Events Failures.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220789","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220789","title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220789","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","rule_id_src":"SV-220789r958412_rule","rule_id":"SV-220789","rule_version":"WN10-AU-000570","rule_title":"Windows 10 must be configured to audit Detailed File Share Failures.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Object Access >> \u201cAudit Detailed File Share\" with \"Failure\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN10-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a command prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nObject Access  >> Detailed File Share - Failure","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAudit Detailed File Share allows the auditing of attempts to access files and folders on a shared folder.\n\nThe Detailed File Share setting logs an event every time a file or folder is accessed, whereas the File Share setting only records one event for any connection established between a client and file share. Detailed File Share audit events include detailed information about the permissions or other criteria used to grant or deny access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108649","V-99545","CCI-000130"],"reference_identifier":"7444","uuid":"cbde2252-566b-4376-9073-f904c71d759e","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 96852A076EEBFCA88EB2A09AD8FFE8CF778DBCB2\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows 10 must be configured to audit Detailed File Share Failures.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220790","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220790","title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220790","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","rule_id_src":"SV-220790r958412_rule","rule_id":"SV-220790","rule_version":"WN10-AU-000575","rule_title":"Windows 10 must be configured to audit MPSSVC Rule-Level Policy Change Successes.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Policy Change >> \u201cAudit MPSSVC Rule-Level Policy Change\" with \"Success\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN10-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nPolicy Change  >> MPSSVC Rule-Level Policy Change - Success","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAudit MPSSVC Rule-Level Policy Change determines whether the operating system generates audit events when changes are made to policy rules for the Microsoft Protection Service (MPSSVC.exe).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108651","V-99547","CCI-000130"],"reference_identifier":"3236","uuid":"a3bfe2b2-15b6-44b2-9604-a7de9fb25162","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C077997B34F1D554D3CC942CD53F143C83F872FA\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows 10 must be configured to audit MPSSVC Rule-Level Policy Change Successes.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220791","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220791","title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220791","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","rule_id_src":"SV-220791r958412_rule","rule_id":"SV-220791","rule_version":"WN10-AU-000580","rule_title":"Windows 10 must be configured to audit MPSSVC Rule-Level Policy Change Failures.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Policy Change >> \u201cAudit MPSSVC Rule-Level Policy Change\" with \"Failure\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN10-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nPolicy Change  >> MPSSVC Rule-Level Policy Change - Failure","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAudit MPSSVC Rule-Level Policy Change determines whether the operating system generates audit events when changes are made to policy rules for the Microsoft Protection Service (MPSSVC.exe).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-99549","SV-108653","CCI-000130"],"reference_identifier":"8442","uuid":"eed7657c-f3e1-4d78-a9f9-a14f60a425d7","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6DCAA1692296E31F4D00EAA3948B04569359599F\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows 10 must be configured to audit MPSSVC Rule-Level Policy Change Failures.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220792","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220792","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220792","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-220792r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-220792","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000005","rule_title":"Camera access from the lock screen must be disabled.","fix_text":"If the device does not have a camera, this is NA.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Control Panel >> Personalization >> \"Prevent enabling lock screen camera\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the device does not have a camera, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Personalization\\\n\nValue Name: NoLockScreenCamera\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enabling camera access from the lock screen could allow for unauthorized use.  Requiring logon will ensure the device is only used by authorized personnel.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78035","V-63545","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5817","uuid":"440de826-9b2d-40d8-8f1d-048f119c8d8b","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 763BE47FC9301652C89325AF62F9ECBDA24856BF\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Camera access from the lock screen must be disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220793","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220793","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220793","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-220793r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-220793","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000007","rule_title":"Windows 10 must cover or disable the built-in or attached camera when not in use.","fix_text":"If the camera is not disconnected or covered, the following registry entry is required:\n \nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistryPath\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\CapabilityAccessManager\\ConsentStore\\webcam\n\nValue Name: Value\nValue Data: Deny","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the device or operating system does not have a camera installed, this requirement is not applicable.\n\nThis requirement is not applicable to mobile devices (smartphones and tablets) where the use of the camera is a local AO decision.\n\nThis requirement is not applicable to dedicated VTC suites located in approved VTC locations that are centrally managed.\n\nFor an external camera, if there is not a method for the operator to manually disconnect the camera at the end of collaborative computing sessions, this is a finding.\n\nFor a built-in camera, the camera must be protected by a camera cover (e.g., laptop camera cover slide) when not in use. \n\nIf the built-in camera is not protected with a camera cover, or if the built-in camera is not disabled in the bios, this is a finding.\n\nIf the camera is not disconnected or covered, the following registry entry is required:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistryPath\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\CapabilityAccessManager\\ConsentStore\\webcam\n\nValue Name: Value\nValue Data: Deny\n\nIf \"Value\" is set to a value other than \"Deny\" and the collaborative computing device has not been authorized for use, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"It is detrimental for operating systems to provide, or install by default, functionality exceeding requirements or mission objectives. These unnecessary capabilities or services are often overlooked and therefore may remain unsecured. They increase the risk to the platform by providing additional attack vectors.\n\nFailing to disconnect from collaborative computing devices (i.e., cameras) can result in subsequent compromises of organizational information. Providing easy methods to physically disconnect from such devices after a collaborative computing session helps to ensure that participants actually carry out the disconnect activity without having to go through complex and tedious procedures.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049, SRG-OS-000370-GPOS-00155","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-109197","V-100093","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4928","uuid":"c3e8fac8-5276-4a41-b26f-08dbd80a93d8","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1885633AE29104F250452112BC14E5D29AE218D8\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows 10 must cover or disable the built-in or attached camera when not in use.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220794","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220794","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220794","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-220794r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-220794","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000010","rule_title":"The display of slide shows on the lock screen must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Control Panel >> Personalization >> \"Prevent enabling lock screen slide show\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Personalization\\\n\nValue Name: NoLockScreenSlideshow\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Slide shows that are displayed on the lock screen could display sensitive information to unauthorized personnel.  Turning off this feature will limit access to the information to a logged on user.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78039","V-63549","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5395","uuid":"89e31904-8ba8-4865-bf94-499edf1d7ad0","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-220795","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220795","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220795","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220795r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220795","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000020","rule_title":"IPv6 source routing must be configured to highest protection.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MSS (Legacy) >> \"MSS: (DisableIPSourceRouting IPv6) IP source routing protection level (protects against packet spoofing)\" to \"Highest protection, source routing is completely disabled\".\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the MSS-Legacy custom templates included with the STIG package.  \"MSS-Legacy.admx\" and \" MSS-Legacy.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip6\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: DisableIpSourceRouting\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 2","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Configuring the system to disable IPv6 source routing protects against spoofing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78045","V-63555","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1288","uuid":"b9f478a1-f50b-4dce-a402-4a98f1c2884b","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E6D899BE170B362BFCC51DB2B2AFF35B1FEE9A7B\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'IPv6 source routing must be configured to highest protection.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220796","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220796","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220796","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220796r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220796","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000025","rule_title":"The system must be configured to prevent IP source routing.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MSS (Legacy) >> \"MSS: (DisableIPSourceRouting) IP source routing protection level (protects against packet spoofing)\" to \"Highest protection, source routing is completely disabled\".\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the MSS-Legacy custom templates included with the STIG package.  \"MSS-Legacy.admx\" and \" MSS-Legacy.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: DisableIPSourceRouting\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 2","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Configuring the system to disable IP source routing protects against spoofing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78049","V-63559","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5419","uuid":"92cc4ef4-2fec-4fd8-b6c8-6ee258298222","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A60CAB5A44CD37A846CE43480186BDD41E7981B5\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must be configured to prevent IP source routing.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220797","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220797","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220797","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220797r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220797","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000030","rule_title":"The system must be configured to prevent Internet Control Message Protocol (ICMP) redirects from overriding Open Shortest Path First (OSPF) generated routes.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MSS (Legacy) >> \"MSS: (EnableICMPRedirect) Allow ICMP redirects to override OSPF generated routes\" to \"Disabled\".\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the MSS-Legacy custom templates included with the STIG package.  \"MSS-Legacy.admx\" and \" MSS-Legacy.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: EnableICMPRedirect\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing ICMP redirect of routes can lead to traffic not being routed properly.   When disabled, this forces ICMP to be routed via shortest path first.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63563","SV-78053","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1061","uuid":"af61d681-d3d7-48b2-ab47-90472e016960","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FE6FCA3AE2EAE26CA3685A7ECA3B4376EE07AC07\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The system must be configured to prevent Internet Control Message Protocol (ICMP) redirects from overriding Open Shortest Path First (OSPF) generated routes.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220798","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220798","title":"SRG-OS-000420-GPOS-00186","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220798","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000420-GPOS-00186","rule_id_src":"SV-220798r958902_rule","rule_id":"SV-220798","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000035","rule_title":"The system must be configured to ignore NetBIOS name release requests except from WINS servers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MSS (Legacy) >> \"MSS: (NoNameReleaseOnDemand) Allow the computer to ignore NetBIOS name release requests except from WINS servers\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the MSS-Legacy custom templates included with the STIG package.  \"MSS-Legacy.admx\" and \" MSS-Legacy.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netbt\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  NoNameReleaseOnDemand\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Configuring the system to ignore name release requests, except from WINS servers, prevents a denial of service (DoS) attack. The DoS consists of sending a NetBIOS name release request to the server for each entry in the server's cache, causing a response delay in the normal operation of the servers WINS resolution capability.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63567","SV-78057","CCI-002385"],"reference_identifier":"9835","uuid":"5e8a9f24-c1cf-4047-bd98-5d542e1e2a9e","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F3A8574CCC0324E66459D61B43958DCC1BA60AA5\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The system must be configured to ignore NetBIOS name release requests except from WINS servers.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220799","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220799","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220799","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","rule_id_src":"SV-220799r958518_rule","rule_id":"SV-220799","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000037","rule_title":"Local administrator accounts must have their privileged token filtered to prevent elevated privileges from being used over the network on domain systems.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MS Security Guide >> \"Apply UAC restrictions to local accounts on network logons\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the SecGuide custom templates included with the STIG package.  \"SecGuide.admx\" and \"SecGuide.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is not a member of a domain, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: LocalAccountTokenFilterPolicy\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A compromised local administrator account can provide means for an attacker to move laterally between domain systems.\n\nWith User Account Control enabled, filtering the privileged token for built-in administrator accounts will prevent the elevated privileges of these accounts from being used over the network.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63597","SV-78087","CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"3132","uuid":"49ba88b1-4d4f-40f7-959d-5c855b9b74ad","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 50FEB17EBF9A92295A274DE064F41EF2D2401137\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Local administrator accounts must have their privileged token filtered to prevent elevated privileges from being used over the network on domain systems.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220800","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220800","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220800","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-220800r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-220800","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000038","rule_title":"WDigest Authentication must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MS Security Guide >> \"WDigest Authentication (disabling may require KB2871997)\" to \"Disabled\".\n\nThe patch referenced in the policy title is not required for Windows 10.\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the SecGuide custom templates included with the STIG package.  \"SecGuide.admx\" and \"SecGuide.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurityProviders\\Wdigest\\\n\nValue Name: UseLogonCredential\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"When the WDigest Authentication protocol is enabled, plain text passwords are stored in the Local Security Authority Subsystem Service (LSASS) exposing them to theft.  WDigest is disabled by default in Windows 10.  This setting ensures this is enforced.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-71763","SV-86387","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"1108","uuid":"0ab27192-e08f-4874-88fe-08b693452de7","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-220801","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220801","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220801","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-220801r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-220801","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000039","rule_title":"Run as different user must be removed from context menus.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MS Security Guide >> \"Remove \"Run as Different User\" from context menus\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the SecGuide custom templates included with the STIG package.  \"SecGuide.admx\" and \"SecGuide.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry values do not exist or are not configured as specified, this is a finding.\nThe policy configures the same Value Name, Type and Value under four different registry paths.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Paths:  \n\\SOFTWARE\\Classes\\batfile\\shell\\runasuser\\\n\\SOFTWARE\\Classes\\cmdfile\\shell\\runasuser\\\n\\SOFTWARE\\Classes\\exefile\\shell\\runasuser\\\n\\SOFTWARE\\Classes\\mscfile\\shell\\runasuser\\\n\nValue Name:  SuppressionPolicy\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00001000 (4096)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The \"Run as different user\" selection from context menus allows the use of credentials other than the currently logged on user.  Using privileged credentials in a standard user session can expose those credentials to theft.  Removing this option from context menus helps prevent this from occurring.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-86953","V-72329","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"6746","uuid":"03df46be-f066-4a0e-93f4-60a5857490ad","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 921C62C21F15BF6B115C0FE39ED34E23888FE75B\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Run as different user must be removed from context menus.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220802","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220802","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220802","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220802r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220802","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000040","rule_title":"Insecure logons to an SMB server must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Network >> Lanman Workstation >> \"Enable insecure guest logons\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Windows 10 v1507 LTSB version does not include this setting; it is NA for those systems.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\LanmanWorkstation\\\n\nValue Name: AllowInsecureGuestAuth\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Insecure guest logons allow unauthenticated access to shared folders.  Shared resources on a system must require authentication to establish proper access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63569","SV-78059","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7296","uuid":"c9b7fa4a-3a64-4d04-8aa5-d4627b3fce89","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 575C7C3E3C02650E4C388B4A00F78B41B8DCC815\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Insecure logons to an SMB server must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220803","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220803","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220803","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-220803r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-220803","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000044","rule_title":"Internet connection sharing must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Network >> Network Connections >> \"Prohibit use of Internet Connection Sharing on your DNS domain network\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Network Connections\\\n\nValue Name: NC_ShowSharedAccessUI\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Internet connection sharing makes it possible for an existing internet connection, such as through wireless, to be shared and used by other systems essentially creating a mobile hotspot.  This exposes the system sharing the connection to others with potentially malicious purpose.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-86389","V-71765","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"7505","uuid":"98916ac1-f245-49a0-a9ba-a8e1880e8b2c","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7AF405C9F74FFDD15DF4161DA56B2AA0F1988B46\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Internet connection sharing must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220805","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220805","title":"SRG-OS-000120-GPOS-00061","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220805","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000120-GPOS-00061","rule_id_src":"SV-220805r971535_rule","rule_id":"SV-220805","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000052","rule_title":"Windows 10 must be configured to prioritize ECC Curves with longer key lengths first.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Network >> SSL Configuration Settings >> \"ECC Curve Order\" to \"Enabled\" with \"ECC Curve Order:\" including the following in the order listed:\n\nNistP384\nNistP256","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Cryptography\\Configuration\\SSL\\00010002\\\n\nValue Name: EccCurves\n\nValue Type: REG_MULTI_SZ\nValue: NistP384 NistP256","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Use of weak or untested encryption algorithms undermines the purposes of utilizing encryption to protect data. By default Windows uses ECC curves with shorter key lengths first.  Requiring ECC curves with longer key lengths to be prioritized first helps ensure more secure algorithms are used.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-74413","SV-89087","CCI-000803"],"reference_identifier":"3881","uuid":"997db87a-dc22-457b-a3f4-bdfdfa96d488","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 83067239F0B599AE9979AAA1EA6E5D14361A5B9C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows 10 must be configured to prioritize ECC Curves with longer key lengths first.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220806","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220806","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220806","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220806r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220806","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000055","rule_title":"Simultaneous connections to the internet or a Windows domain must be limited.","fix_text":"The default behavior for \"Minimize the number of simultaneous connections to the Internet or a Windows Domain\" is \"Enabled\".\n\nIf this must be corrected, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Network >> Windows Connection Manager >> \"Minimize the number of simultaneous connections to the Internet or a Windows Domain\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nUnder \"Options\", set \"Minimize Policy Options\" to \"3 = Prevent Wi-Fi When on Ethernet\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior for \"Minimize the number of simultaneous connections to the Internet or a Windows Domain\" is \"Enabled\".\n\nIf the registry value name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"3\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WcmSvc\\GroupPolicy\\\n\nValue Name: fMinimizeConnections\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 3 (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Multiple network connections can provide additional attack vectors to a system and must be limited. The \"Minimize the number of simultaneous connections to the Internet or a Windows Domain\" setting prevents systems from automatically establishing multiple connections. When both wired and wireless connections are available, for example, the less-preferred connection (typically wireless) will be disconnected.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78071","V-63581","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8540","uuid":"74e902f4-84cf-403b-a288-659560364960","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 98202DC511420655468597FCC390C6668AD043EC\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Simultaneous connections to the internet or a Windows domain must be limited.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220807","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220807","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220807","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220807r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220807","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000060","rule_title":"Connections to non-domain networks when connected to a domain authenticated network must be blocked.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Network >> Windows Connection Manager >> \"Prohibit connection to non-domain networks when connected to domain authenticated network\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WcmSvc\\GroupPolicy\\\n\nValue Name: fBlockNonDomain\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Multiple network connections can provide additional attack vectors to a system and should be limited.  When connected to a domain, communication must go through the domain connection.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63585","SV-78075","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5841","uuid":"e6e5bb01-d9d8-4320-861e-d9124119bd66","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 331AE271228CBA3D9B9F513567D74EAEEBDABB9E\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Connections to non-domain networks when connected to a domain authenticated network must be blocked.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220808","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220808","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220808","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220808r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220808","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000065","rule_title":"Wi-Fi Sense must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Network >> WLAN Service >> WLAN Settings>> \"Allow Windows to automatically connect to suggested open hotspots, to networks shared by contacts, and to hotspots offering paid services\" to \"Disabled\".   \n\nv1507 LTSB does not include this group policy setting.  It may be configured through other means such as using group policy from a later version of Windows 10 or a registry update.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is NA as of v1803 of Windows 10; Wi-Fi sense is no longer available.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\WcmSvc\\wifinetworkmanager\\config\\\n\nValue Name: AutoConnectAllowedOEM\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Wi-Fi Sense automatically connects the system to known hotspots and networks that contacts have shared.  It also allows the sharing of the system's known networks to contacts.  Automatically connecting to hotspots and shared networks can expose a system to unsecured or potentially malicious systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63591","SV-78081","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8213","uuid":"7e9985df-b44a-4fc6-86dc-dba95edbef31","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D4F231CD1AF330B8C111380E11E778473A6E183F\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Wi-Fi Sense must be disabled.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220809","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220809","title":"SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220809","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020","rule_id_src":"SV-220809r958422_rule","rule_id":"SV-220809","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000066","rule_title":"Command line data must be included in process creation events.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Audit Process Creation >> \"Include command line in process creation events\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\Audit\\\n\nValue Name: ProcessCreationIncludeCmdLine_Enabled\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nEnabling \"Include command line data for process creation events\" will record the command line information with the process creation events in the log.  This can provide additional detail when malware has run on a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-68817","SV-83409","CCI-000135"],"reference_identifier":"4492","uuid":"5a3090b7-319c-4260-a615-64416696120c","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 36A11882766DF1A3602FACD1C61164D76AE42DF8\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Command line data must be included in process creation events.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220810","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220810","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220810","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220810r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220810","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000068","rule_title":"Windows 10 must be configured to enable Remote host allows delegation of non-exportable credentials.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Credentials Delegation >> \"Remote host allows delegation of non-exportable credentials\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is NA for Windows 10 LTSC\\B versions 1507 and 1607.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CredentialsDelegation\\\n\nValue Name: AllowProtectedCreds\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"An exportable version of credentials is provided to remote hosts when using credential delegation which exposes them to theft on the remote host.  Restricted Admin mode or Remote Credential Guard allow delegation of non-exportable credentials providing additional protection of the credentials.  Enabling this configures the host to support Restricted Admin mode or Remote Credential Guard.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89373","V-74699","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7276","uuid":"77b4e1ad-4fa9-4b8d-b708-59011ed1bbf2","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D98AEBEBD2A911CE07CE90CEE933F21CC007DF5D\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows 10 must be configured to enable Remote host allows delegation of non-exportable credentials.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220811","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220811","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220811","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220811r1016359_rule","rule_id":"SV-220811","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000070","rule_title":"Virtualization Based Security must be enabled on Windows 10 with the platform security level configured to Secure Boot or Secure Boot with DMA Protection.","fix_text":"VBS, including Credential Guard, currently cannot be implemented in virtual desktop implementations (VDI) due to specific supporting requirements including a TPM, UEFI with Secure Boot, and the capability to run the Hyper-V feature within the virtual desktop.\n\nFor VDIs where the virtual desktop instance is deleted or refreshed upon logoff, this is NA.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Device Guard >> \"Turn On Virtualization Based Security\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Secure Boot\" or \"Secure Boot and DMA Protection\" selected for \"Select Platform Security Level:\".\n\nA Microsoft article on Credential Guard system requirements can be found at the following link:\nhttps://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/itpro/windows/keep-secure/credential-guard-requirements","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Confirm virtualization-based security (VBS) is enabled and running with Secure Boot or Secure Boot and DMA Protection.\n\nFor those devices that support VBS features, including Credential Guard or protection of code integrity, this must be enabled. If the system meets the hardware and firmware dependencies for enabling VBS but it is not enabled, this is a CAT III finding.\n\nVBS, including Credential Guard, currently cannot be implemented in virtual desktop implementations (VDI) due to specific supporting requirements including a TPM, UEFI with Secure Boot, and the capability to run the Hyper-V feature within the virtual desktop.\n\nFor VDIs where the virtual desktop instance is deleted or refreshed upon logoff, this is NA.\n\nRun \"PowerShell\" with elevated privileges (run as administrator).\n\nEnter the following:\n\n\"Get-CimInstance -ClassName Win32_DeviceGuard -Namespace root\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeviceGuard\"\n\nIf \"RequiredSecurityProperties\" does not include a value of \"2\" indicating \"Secure Boot\" (e.g., \"{1, 2}\"), this is a finding.\n\nIf \"Secure Boot and DMA Protection\" is configured, \"3\" will also be displayed in the results (e.g., \"{1, 2, 3}\").\n\nIf \"VirtualizationBasedSecurityStatus\" is not a value of \"2\" indicating \"Running\", this is a finding.\n\nAlternately:\n\nRun \"System Information\".\n\nUnder \"System Summary\", verify the following:\n\nIf \"Device Guard Virtualization based security\" does not display \"Running\", this is finding.\n\nIf \"Device Guard Required Security Properties\" does not display \"Base Virtualization Support, Secure Boot\", this is finding.\n\nIf \"Secure Boot and DMA Protection\" is configured, \"DMA Protection\" will also be displayed (e.g., \"Base Virtualization Support, Secure Boot, DMA Protection\").\n\nThe policy settings referenced in the Fix section will configure the following registry values. However, due to hardware requirements, the registry values alone do not ensure proper function.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeviceGuard\\\n\nValue Name: EnableVirtualizationBasedSecurity\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nValue Name: RequirePlatformSecurityFeatures\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1 (Secure Boot only) or 3 (Secure Boot and DMA Protection)\n\nA Microsoft article on Credential Guard system requirements can be found at the following link:\n\nhttps://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/itpro/windows/keep-secure/credential-guard-requirements","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Virtualization Based Security (VBS) provides the platform for the additional security features, Credential Guard and Virtualization based protection of code integrity. Secure Boot is the minimum security level with DMA protection providing additional memory protection.  DMA Protection requires a CPU that supports input/output memory management unit (IOMMU).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1369","uuid":"1e1d5c48-b6b6-466a-92eb-65485a9ccc93","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9103E6EC19E1055A2AE51C617EC16ABB05735FC1\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Virtualization Based Security must be enabled on Windows 10 with the platform security level configured to Secure Boot or Secure Boot with DMA Protection.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220812","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220812","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220812","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220812r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220812","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000075","rule_title":"Credential Guard must be running on Windows 10 domain-joined systems.","fix_text":"Virtualization based security, including Credential Guard, currently cannot be implemented in VDIs due to specific supporting requirements including a TPM, UEFI with Secure Boot, and the capability to run the Hyper-V feature within the virtual desktop.\n\nFor VDIs where the virtual desktop instance is deleted or refreshed upon logoff, this is Not Applicable.\n\nFor VDIs with persistent desktops, this may be downgraded to a CAT II only where administrators have specific tokens for the VDI. Administrator accounts on virtual desktops must only be used on systems in the VDI; they may not have administrative privileges on any other systems such as servers and physical workstations.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Device Guard >> \"Turn On Virtualization Based Security\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Enabled with UEFI lock\" selected for \"Credential Guard Configuration:\".\n\nv1507 LTSB does not include selection options; select \"Enable Credential Guard\".\n\nA Microsoft TechNet article on Credential Guard, including system requirement details, can be found at the following link:\n\nhttps://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/access-protection/credential-guard/credential-guard","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Confirm Credential Guard is running on domain-joined systems.\n\nFor devices that support Credential Guard, this feature must be enabled. Organizations must take the appropriate action to acquire and implement compatible hardware with Credential Guard enabled.\n\nVirtualization based security, including Credential Guard, currently cannot be implemented in virtual desktop implementations (VDIs) due to specific supporting requirements including a TPM, UEFI with Secure Boot, and the capability to run the Hyper-V feature within the virtual desktop.\n\nFor VDIs where the virtual desktop instance is deleted or refreshed upon logoff, this is Not Applicable.\n\nRun \"PowerShell\" with elevated privileges (run as administrator). \n\nEnter the following:\n\"Get-CimInstance -ClassName Win32_DeviceGuard -Namespace root\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeviceGuard\"\n\nIf \"SecurityServicesRunning\" does not include a value of \"1\" (e.g., \"{1, 2}\"), this is a finding.\n\nAlternately:\n\nRun \"System Information\".\n\nUnder \"System Summary\", verify the following:\n\nIf \"Virtualization-based Security Services Running\" does not list \"Credential Guard\", this is finding.\n\nThe policy settings referenced in the Fix section will configure the following registry value. However, due to hardware requirements, the registry value alone does not ensure proper function.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeviceGuard\\\n\nValue Name: LsaCfgFlags\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1) (Enabled with UEFI lock)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Credential Guard uses virtualization based security to protect information that could be used in credential theft attacks if compromised. This authentication information, which was stored in the Local Security Authority (LSA) in previous versions of Windows, is isolated from the rest of operating system and can only be accessed by privileged system software.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78089","V-63599","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5847","uuid":"9fef2596-bcbf-4261-8eff-04bfdb93ff24","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8B79C5BCEC3C5755F68729E952E763AF5FC38E57\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Credential Guard must be running on Windows 10 domain-joined systems.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220813","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220813","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220813","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220813r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220813","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000085","rule_title":"Early Launch Antimalware, Boot-Start Driver Initialization Policy must prevent boot drivers.","fix_text":"Ensure that Early Launch Antimalware - Boot-Start Driver Initialization policy is set to enforce \"Good, unknown and bad but critical\" (preventing \"bad\").\n\nIf this needs to be corrected configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Early Launch Antimalware >> \"Boot-Start Driver Initialization Policy\" to \"Enabled\u201d with \"Good, unknown and bad but critical\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for Early Launch Antimalware - Boot-Start Driver Initialization policy is to enforce \"Good, unknown and bad but critical\" (preventing \"bad\").\n\nIf the registry value name below does not exist, this a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"7\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Policies\\EarlyLaunch\\\n\nValue Name: DriverLoadPolicy\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1, 3, or 8 \n\nPossible values for this setting are:\n8 - Good only\n1 - Good and unknown\n3 - Good, unknown and bad but critical\n7 - All (which includes \"Bad\" and would be a finding)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"By being launched first by the kernel, ELAM ( Early Launch Antimalware) is ensured to be launched before any third-party software, and is therefore able to detect malware in the boot process and prevent it from initializing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78097","V-63607","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3738","uuid":"00a24e3d-8996-4084-9f77-4b4aadc37d29","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1A07CEC4DEDF033B6BB99CDCCD3352054D3EF1D7\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Early Launch Antimalware, Boot-Start Driver Initialization Policy must prevent boot drivers.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220814","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220814","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220814","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220814r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220814","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000090","rule_title":"Group Policy objects must be reprocessed even if they have not changed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Group Policy >> \"Configure registry policy processing\" to \"Enabled\" and select the option \"Process even if the Group Policy objects have not changed\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Group Policy\\{35378EAC-683F-11D2-A89A-00C04FBBCFA2}\n\nValue Name: NoGPOListChanges\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enabling this setting and then selecting the \"Process even if the Group Policy objects have not changed\" option ensures that the policies will be reprocessed even if none have been changed. This way, any unauthorized changes are forced to match the domain-based group policy settings again.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78099","V-63609","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7341","uuid":"6afcb23e-2a8b-4f76-99a5-dfdf1758c4ed","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-220815","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220815","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220815","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-220815r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-220815","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000100","rule_title":"Downloading print driver packages over HTTP must be prevented.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Internet Communication Management >> Internet Communication settings >> \"Turn off downloading of print drivers over HTTP\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Printers\\\n\nValue Name: DisableWebPnPDownload\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature.  Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system.  This setting prevents the computer from downloading print driver packages over HTTP.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63615","SV-78105","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"1133","uuid":"5fa116db-ef0e-4a2b-9b53-8bab835cb711","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DFDB651846C99AAAEE687F2DE47C88CAF4EAA169\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Downloading print driver packages over HTTP must be prevented.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220816","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220816","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220816","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-220816r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-220816","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000105","rule_title":"Web publishing and online ordering wizards must be prevented from downloading a list of providers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Internet Communication Management >> Internet Communication settings >> \"Turn off Internet download for Web publishing and online ordering wizards\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoWebServices\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature.  Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system.  This setting prevents Windows from downloading a list of providers for the Web publishing and online ordering wizards.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63621","SV-78111","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4076","uuid":"a734e066-4146-4f74-a16d-f879caa3b345","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2172D997324766F271A4CF8832DE47948BC21FC2\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Web publishing and online ordering wizards must be prevented from downloading a list of providers.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220817","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220817","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220817","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-220817r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-220817","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000110","rule_title":"Printing over HTTP must be prevented.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Internet Communication Management >> Internet Communication settings >> \"Turn off printing over HTTP\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Printers\\\n\nValue Name: DisableHTTPPrinting\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature.  Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system.  This setting prevents the client computer from printing over HTTP, which allows the computer to print to printers on the intranet as well as the Internet.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63623","SV-78113","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"7198","uuid":"ecdf3b7c-fad2-4a82-a4c8-563c108d378e","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5D59EE7AFA3D246DE79F360E0C54BEDB087DF973\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Printing over HTTP must be prevented.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220818","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220818","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220818","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220818r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220818","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000115","rule_title":"Systems must at least attempt device authentication using certificates.","fix_text":"This requirement is applicable to domain-joined systems. For standalone or nondomain-joined systems, this is NA.\n\nThe default behavior for \"Support device authentication using certificate\" is \"Automatic\".\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Kerberos >> \"Support device authentication using certificate\" to \"Not Configured or \"Enabled\" with either option selected in \"Device authentication behavior using certificate:\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This requirement is applicable to domain-joined systems. For standalone or nondomain-joined systems, this is NA.\n\nThe default behavior for \"Support device authentication using certificate\" is \"Automatic\".\n\nIf the registry value name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\Kerberos\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  DevicePKInitEnabled\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1 (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Using certificates to authenticate devices to the domain provides increased security over passwords.  By default systems will attempt to authenticate using certificates and fall back to passwords if the domain controller does not support certificates for devices.  This may also be configured to always use certificates for device authentication.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63627","SV-78117","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7367","uuid":"d70b7412-1daa-43d5-9441-c5d07c3e1c0c","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F4F14BA6D0F688F00CB93667BE91EF22B4DF28C3\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Systems must at least attempt device authentication using certificates.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220819","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220819","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220819","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-220819r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-220819","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000120","rule_title":"The network selection user interface (UI) must not be displayed on the logon screen.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Logon >> \"Do not display network selection UI\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\System\\\n\nValue Name: DontDisplayNetworkSelectionUI\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enabling interaction with the network selection UI allows users to change connections to available networks without signing into Windows.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78119","V-63629","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3453","uuid":"13497e60-8f43-4f44-a02e-a4b1bc9ff5d7","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FDC37544D51827A8542BA4E5DF4E99806E36F2A2\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The network selection user interface (UI) must not be displayed on the logon screen.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220820","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220820","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220820","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-220820r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-220820","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000130","rule_title":"Local users on domain-joined computers must not be enumerated.","fix_text":"This requirement is applicable to domain-joined systems. For standalone or nondomain-joined systems, this is NA.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Logon >> \"Enumerate local users on domain-joined computers\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This requirement is applicable to domain-joined systems. For standalone or nondomain-joined systems, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnumerateLocalUsers\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The username is one part of logon credentials that could be used to gain access to a system. Preventing the enumeration of users limits this information to authorized personnel.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78123","V-63633","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"9123","uuid":"8a65b250-1fb4-4988-b513-fe182e3d122c","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 98509440D0053667408BFF548F4B2491F04C8051\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Local users on domain-joined computers must not be enumerated.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220821","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220821","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220821","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","rule_id_src":"SV-220821r1051027_rule","rule_id":"SV-220821","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000145","rule_title":"Users must be prompted for a password on resume from sleep (on battery).","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Power Management >> Sleep 