st be enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> App Runtime >> \"Allow Microsoft accounts to be optional\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Windows 10 LTSC\\B versions do not support the Microsoft Store and modern apps; this is NA for those systems.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: MSAOptional\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Control of credentials and the system must be maintained within the enterprise.  Enabling this setting allows enterprise credentials to be used with modern style apps that support this, instead of Microsoft accounts.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63659","SV-78149","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4470","uuid":"4a3f4e59-5b07-4375-af70-ffc83bb0d6aa","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1ACD33A0BE92633C543043A69168C3E3A654B77D\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The setting to allow Microsoft accounts to be optional for modern style apps must be enabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220826","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220826","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220826","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-220826r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-220826","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000175","rule_title":"The Application Compatibility Program Inventory must be prevented from collecting data and sending the information to Microsoft.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Application Compatibility >> \"Turn off Inventory Collector\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\AppCompat\\\n\nValue Name: DisableInventory\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature.  Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system.  This setting will prevent the Program Inventory from collecting data about a system and sending the information to Microsoft.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63663","SV-78153","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"1985","uuid":"3f563126-430c-45cd-9e6f-c073c4138f5a","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0033523DFFE6D583697965B7A9BEE9E2323CEB91\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'The Application Compatibility Program Inventory must be prevented from collecting data and sending the information to Microsoft.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220827","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220827","title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220827","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","rule_id_src":"SV-220827r958804_rule","rule_id":"SV-220827","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000180","rule_title":"Autoplay must be turned off for non-volume devices.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> AutoPlay Policies >> \"Disallow Autoplay for non-volume devices\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoAutoplayfornonVolume\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing autoplay to execute may introduce malicious code to a system.  Autoplay begins reading from a drive as soon as you insert media in the drive.  As a result, the setup file of programs or music on audio media may start.  This setting will disable autoplay for non-volume devices (such as Media Transfer Protocol (MTP) devices).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78157","V-63667","CCI-001764"],"reference_identifier":"1844","uuid":"29bda263-103b-4906-9d9c-088503f3f5bc","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status