:"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4FE5C6864EA42E99C6AC2B765E62B523435FDE53\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The default autorun behavior must be configured to prevent autorun commands.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220829","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220829","title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220829","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","rule_id_src":"SV-220829r958804_rule","rule_id":"SV-220829","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000190","rule_title":"Autoplay must be disabled for all drives.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> AutoPlay Policies >> \"Turn off AutoPlay\" to \"Enabled:All Drives\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\policies\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoDriveTypeAutoRun\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x000000ff (255)\n\nNote: If the value for NoDriveTypeAutorun is entered manually, it must be entered as \"ff\" when Hexadecimal is selected, or \"255\" with Decimal selected.  Using the policy value specified in the Fix section will enter it correctly.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing autoplay to execute may introduce malicious code to a system.  Autoplay begins reading from a drive as soon as you insert media in the drive.  As a result, the setup file of programs or music on audio media may start.  By default, autoplay is disabled on removable drives, such as the floppy disk drive (but not the CD-ROM drive) and on network drives.  If you enable this policy, you can also disable autoplay on all drives.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63673","SV-78163","CCI-001764"],"reference_identifier":"7402","uuid":"25143f45-4a93-445d-972b-d3b7d52d7834","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DC2155467E6CE9759F2D607D7880439B7364C65F\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Autoplay must be disabled for all drives.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220830","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220830","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220830","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220830r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220830","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000195","rule_title":"Enhanced anti-spoofing for facial recognition must be enabled on Window 10.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Biometrics >> Facial Features >> \"Configure enhanced anti-spoofing\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nv1607:\nThe policy name is \"Use enhanced anti-spoofing when available\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Windows 10 v1507 LTSB version does not include this setting; it is NA for those systems.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Biometrics\\FacialFeatures\\\n\nValue Name: EnhancedAntiSpoofing\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enhanced anti-spoofing provides additional protections when using facial recognition with devices that support it.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78167","V-63677","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9539","uuid":"ff14505a-9631-460c-85b8-0cedc819d4a8","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 90F9129542AA548AFDA64ABC872E45D0FD3F5AEA\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Enhanced anti-spoofing for facial recognition must be enabled on Window 10.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220831","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220831","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220831","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-220831r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-220831","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000197","rule_title":"Microsoft consumer experiences must be turned off.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Cloud Content >> \"Turn off Microsoft consumer experiences\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Windows 10 v1507 LTSB version does not include this setting; it is NA for those systems.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CloudContent\\\n\nValue Name: DisableWindowsConsumerFeatures\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Microsoft consumer experiences provides suggestions and notifications to users, which may include the installation of Windows Store apps.  Organizations may control the execution of applications through other means such as whitelisting.  Turning off Microsoft consumer experiences will help prevent the unwanted installation of suggested applications.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-71771","SV-86395","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4011","uuid":"ea274cc1-62ff-4cb3-92a0-74ee1aaf9c91","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4CAF29F87350F2AED6988709C8CF33175B5BA5B1\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Microsoft consumer experiences must be turned off.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220832","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220832","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220832","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","rule_id_src":"SV-220832r958518_rule","rule_id":"SV-220832","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000200","rule_title":"Administrator accounts must not be enumerated during elevation.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Credential User Interface >> \"Enumerate administrator accounts on elevation\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\CredUI\\\n\nValue Name: EnumerateAdministrators\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enumeration of administrator accounts when elevating can provide part of the logon information to an unauthorized user.  This setting configures the system to always require users to type in a username and password to elevate a running application.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63679","SV-78169","CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"5477","uuid":"9950b44e-d005-4340-a9e0-e8f199eac07e","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7F8C8D04465862AA108D373AE815DC1B051090C6\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Administrator accounts must not be enumerated during elevation.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220833","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220833","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220833","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220833r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220833","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000204","rule_title":"If Enhanced diagnostic data is enabled it must be limited to the minimum required to support Windows Analytics.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Data Collection and Preview Builds >> \"Limit Enhanced diagnostic data to the minimum required by Windows Analytics\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Enable Windows Analytics collection\" selected in \"Options:\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This setting requires v1709 or later of Windows 10; it is NA for prior versions.\n\nIf \"Enhanced\" level is enabled for telemetry, this must be configured. If \"Security\" or \"Basic\" are configured, this is NA. (See V-220834).\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DataCollection\\\n\nValue Name: LimitEnhancedDiagnosticDataWindowsAnalytics\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature. Limiting this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise. The \"Enhanced\" level for telemetry includes additional information beyond \"Security\" and \"Basic\" on how Windows and apps are used and advanced reliability data. Windows Analytics can use a \"limited enhanced\" level to provide information such as health data for devices.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-96859","V-82145","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1791","uuid":"bf132f04-36b8-4487-a062-090d8488ac6c","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FBA94693EC1D706863B6FEC188F0C9508F042D48\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'If Enhanced diagnostic data is enabled it must be limited to the minimum required to support Windows Analytics.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220834","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220834","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220834","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220834r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220834","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000205","rule_title":"Windows Telemetry must not be configured to Full.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Data Collection and Preview Builds >> \"Allow Telemetry\" to \"Enabled\" with \"0 - Security [Enterprise Only]\" or \"1 - Basic\" selected in \"Options:\". \n\nIf an organization is using v1709 or later of Windows 10, this may be configured to \"2 - Enhanced\" to support Windows Analytics. V-220833 must also be configured to limit the Enhanced diagnostic data to the minimum required by Windows Analytics.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DataCollection\\\n\nValue Name: AllowTelemetry\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) (Security)\n0x00000001 (1) (Basic)\n\nIf an organization is using v1709 or later of Windows 10, this may be configured to \"Enhanced\" to support Windows Analytics. V-220833 must also be configured to limit the Enhanced diagnostic data to the minimum required by Windows Analytics. This registry value will then be 0x00000002 (2).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature. Limiting this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise. The \"Security\" option for Telemetry configures the lowest amount of data, effectively none outside of the Malicious Software Removal Tool (MSRT), Defender, and telemetry client settings. \"Basic\" sends basic diagnostic and usage data and may be required to support some Microsoft services. \"Enhanced\" includes additional information on how Windows and apps are used and advanced reliability data. Windows Analytics can use a \"limited enhanced\" level to provide information such as health data for devices. This requires the configuration of an additional setting available with v1709 and later of Windows 10.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63683","SV-78173","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7307","uuid":"8955be70-e1c4-48c3-bbad-de456b9c5376","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D0DEFBCDA6920A57D2FE497E0899C8369340FF4A\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Telemetry must not be configured to Full.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220835","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220835","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220835","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220835r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220835","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000206","rule_title":"Windows Update must not obtain updates from other PCs on the internet.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Delivery Optimization >> \"Download Mode\" to \"Enabled\" with any option except \"Internet\" selected.\n\nAcceptable selections include:\nBypass (100)\nGroup (2)\nHTTP only (0)\nLAN (1)\nSimple (99)\n\nv1507 (LTSB) does not include this group policy setting locally. For domain-joined systems, configure through domain group policy as \"HTTP only (0)\" or \"Lan (1)\". \n\nFor standalone or nondomain-joined systems, configure using Settings >> Update & Security >> Windows Update >> Advanced Options >> \"Choose how updates are delivered\" with either \"Off\" or \"PCs on my local network\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeliveryOptimization\\\n\nValue Name: DODownloadMode\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) - No peering (HTTP Only)\n0x00000001 (1) - Peers on same NAT only (LAN)\n0x00000002 (2) - Local Network / Private group peering (Group)\n0x00000063 (99) - Simple download mode, no peering (Simple)\n0x00000064 (100) - Bypass mode, Delivery Optimization not used (Bypass)\n\nA value of 0x00000003 (3), Internet, is a finding.\n\nv1507 LTSB:\nDomain joined systems:\nVerify the registry value above.\nIf the value is not 0x00000000 (0) or 0x00000001 (1), this is a finding.\n\nStandalone or nondomain-joined systems (configured in Settings):\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\DeliveryOptimization\\Config\\\n\nValue Name: DODownloadMode\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) - Off\n0x00000001 (1) - LAN","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows 10 allows Windows Update to obtain updates from additional sources instead of Microsoft. In addition to Microsoft, updates can be obtained from and sent to PCs on the local network as well as on the internet. This is part of the Windows Update trusted process; however, to minimize outside exposure, obtaining updates from or sending to systems on the internet must be prevented.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-80171","V-65681","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2128","uuid":"87228165-b5b9-4165-8054-22de304c7e47","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B06C4F2ED52B18B46C774428F4DAB606417648B0\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Update must not obtain updates from other PCs on the internet.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220836","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220836","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220836","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-220836r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-220836","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000210","rule_title":"The Windows Defender SmartScreen for Explorer must be enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> File Explorer >> \"Configure Windows Defender SmartScreen\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Warn and prevent bypass\" selected. \n\nWindows 10 includes duplicate policies for this setting. It can also be configured under Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Defender SmartScreen >> Explorer.\n\nv1607 LTSB:\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> File Explorer >> \"Configure Windows SmartScreen\" to \"Enabled\". (Selection options are not available.)\n\nv1507 LTSB:\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> File Explorer >> \"Configure Windows SmartScreen\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Require approval from an administrator before running downloaded unknown software\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems, for other systems this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry values do not exist or are not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableSmartScreen\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)\n\nAnd\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\System\\\n\nValue Name: ShellSmartScreenLevel\n\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: Block\n\nv1607 LTSB:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableSmartScreen\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)\n\nv1507 LTSB:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableSmartScreen\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000002 (2)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows Defender SmartScreen helps protect systems from programs downloaded from the internet that may be malicious. Enabling Windows Defender SmartScreen will warn or prevent users from running potentially malicious programs.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63685","SV-78175","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"1683","uuid":"877a9351-f295-4862-bef3-9b6e7ae3eb03","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D2A45D267D2C9307B4D191356932B42EB54164D9\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Windows Defender SmartScreen for Explorer must be enabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220837","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220837","title":"SRG-OS-000433-GPOS-00192","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220837","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000433-GPOS-00192","rule_id_src":"SV-220837r958928_rule","rule_id":"SV-220837","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000215","rule_title":"Explorer Data Execution Prevention must be enabled.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for data execution prevention to be turned on for file explorer.\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> File Explorer >> \"Turn off Data Execution Prevention for Explorer\" to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for data execution prevention to be turned on for file explorer.\n\nIf the registry value name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoDataExecutionPrevention\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0 (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Data Execution Prevention (DEP) provides additional protection by performing  checks on memory to help prevent malicious code from running.  This setting will prevent Data Execution Prevention from being turned off for File Explorer.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63689","SV-78179","CCI-002824"],"reference_identifier":"1587","uuid":"12416ba5-5c55-4e35-abeb-82da1a1d41ca","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A1C1F5B87E2DE50654BDECF21851EA7C88C1185C\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Explorer Data Execution Prevention must be enabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220838","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220838","title":"SRG-OS-000420-GPOS-00186","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220838","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000420-GPOS-00186","rule_id_src":"SV-220838r958902_rule","rule_id":"SV-220838","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000220","rule_title":"Turning off File Explorer heap termination on corruption must be disabled.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for File Explorer heap termination on corruption to be enabled.\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> File Explorer >> \"Turn off heap termination on corruption\" to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for File Explorer heap termination on corruption to be enabled.\n\nIf the registry Value Name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoHeapTerminationOnCorruption\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Legacy plug-in applications may continue to function when a File Explorer session has become corrupt.  Disabling this feature will prevent this.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78181","V-63691","CCI-002385"],"reference_identifier":"2423","uuid":"8a682a79-66da-40fa-acdc-9a8f0bd9c23c","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D2E24DE96276B7B7E07CB3C2DEBE23FEC243A7A5\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Turning off File Explorer heap termination on corruption must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220839","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220839","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220839","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220839r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220839","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000225","rule_title":"File Explorer shell protocol must run in protected mode.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for shell protected mode to be turned on for file explorer.\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> File Explorer >> \"Turn off shell protocol protected mode\" to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for shell protected mode to be turned on for file explorer.\n\nIf the registry value name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: PreXPSP2ShellProtocolBehavior\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0 (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The shell protocol will  limit the set of folders applications can open when run in protected mode.  Restricting files an application can open, to a limited set of folders, increases the security of Windows.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78185","V-63695","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6337","uuid":"5249c6cb-1a38-467d-8f97-e106b14a68d2","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C3D04895D379B629818674BB7B22F2261B9F6D90\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'File Explorer shell protocol must run in protected mode.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220840","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220840","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220840","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220840r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220840","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000230","rule_title":"Users must not be allowed to ignore Windows Defender SmartScreen filter warnings for malicious websites in Microsoft Edge.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Edge >> \"Prevent bypassing Windows Defender SmartScreen prompts for sites\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nWindows 10 includes duplicate policies for this setting. It can also be configured under Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Defender SmartScreen >> Microsoft Edge.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems, for other systems this is NA.\n\nWindows 10 LTSC\\B versions do not include Microsoft Edge, this is NA for those systems.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\MicrosoftEdge\\PhishingFilter\\\n\nValue Name: PreventOverride\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Windows Defender SmartScreen filter in Microsoft Edge provides warning messages and blocks potentially malicious websites and file downloads.  If users are allowed to ignore warnings from the Windows Defender SmartScreen filter they could still access malicious websites.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63699","SV-78189","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8848","uuid":"de91e82e-63fa-4d84-a4ec-6af49a2f30c1","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D7114F7E86FDCFA729A2F73D66F147E113128C91\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Users must not be allowed to ignore Windows Defender SmartScreen filter warnings for malicious websites in Microsoft Edge.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220841","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220841","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220841","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220841r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220841","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000235","rule_title":"Users must not be allowed to ignore Windows Defender SmartScreen filter warnings for unverified files in Microsoft Edge.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Edge >> \"Prevent bypassing Windows Defender SmartScreen prompts for files\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nWindows 10 includes duplicate policies for this setting. It can also be configured under Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Defender SmartScreen >> Microsoft Edge.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems, for other systems this is NA.\n\nWindows 10 LTSC\\B versions do not include Microsoft Edge, this is NA for those systems.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\MicrosoftEdge\\PhishingFilter\\\n\nValue Name: PreventOverrideAppRepUnknown\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Windows Defender SmartScreen filter in Microsoft Edge provides warning messages and blocks potentially malicious websites and file downloads.  If users are allowed to ignore warnings from the Windows Defender SmartScreen filter they could still download potentially malicious files.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78191","V-63701","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8299","uuid":"592237e3-95ec-46ba-8072-584b292c375f","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E618DF883C9E02C65E58417DF75EBEC533411373\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Users must not be allowed to ignore Windows Defender SmartScreen filter warnings for unverified files in Microsoft Edge.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220842","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220842","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220842","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220842r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220842","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000238","rule_title":"Windows 10 must be configured to prevent certificate error overrides in Microsoft Edge.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Edge >> \"Prevent certificate error overrides\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This setting is applicable starting with v1809 of Windows 10; it is NA for prior versions.\n\nWindows 10 LTSC\\B versions do not include Microsoft Edge; this is NA for those systems.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\MicrosoftEdge\\Internet Settings\\\n\nValue Name: PreventCertErrorOverrides\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Web security certificates provide an indication whether a site is legitimate. This policy setting prevents the user from ignoring Secure Sockets Layer/Transport Layer Security (SSL/TLS) certificate errors that interrupt browsing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-96853","V-82139","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7792","uuid":"e2d9c4d5-3cd1-4235-a511-a69f876899ec","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8A4E2F02129C81A23C3892481E56C1314BE2C5AA\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows 10 must be configured to prevent certificate error overrides in Microsoft Edge.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220843","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220843","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220843","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220843r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220843","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000245","rule_title":"The password manager function in the Edge browser must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Edge >> \"Configure Password Manager\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Windows 10 LTSC\\B versions do not include Microsoft Edge, this is NA for those systems.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\MicrosoftEdge\\Main\\\n\nValue Name: FormSuggest Passwords\n\nType: REG_SZ\nValue: no","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Passwords save locally for re-use when browsing may be subject to compromise.  Disabling the Edge password manager will prevent this for the browser.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63709","SV-78199","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9888","uuid":"4799d4ed-bb8f-4571-a712-a6ea73466a50","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4C93926F32909B65D651282B961DA69DE52E8567\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The password manager function in the Edge browser must be disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220844","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220844","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220844","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220844r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220844","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000250","rule_title":"The Windows Defender SmartScreen filter for Microsoft Edge must be enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Edge >> \"Configure Windows Defender SmartScreen\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nWindows 10 includes duplicate policies for this setting. It can also be configured under Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Defender SmartScreen >> Microsoft Edge.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems, for other systems this is NA.\n\nWindows 10 LTSC\\B versions do not include Microsoft Edge, this is NA for those systems.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\MicrosoftEdge\\PhishingFilter\\\n\nValue Name: EnabledV9\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Windows Defender SmartScreen filter in Microsoft Edge provides warning messages and blocks potentially malicious websites.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78203","V-63713","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4469","uuid":"82c9566c-5a45-48b1-b706-2bb4cbe48f87","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 58148EE58D266718CA89910F7324804EE58540C4\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Windows Defender SmartScreen filter for Microsoft Edge must be enabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220845","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220845","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220845","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-220845r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-220845","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000252","rule_title":"Windows 10 must be configured to disable Windows Game Recording and Broadcasting.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Game Recording and Broadcasting >> \"Enables or disables Windows Game Recording and Broadcasting\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is NA for Windows 10 LTSC\\B versions 1507 and 1607.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\GameDVR\\\n\nValue Name: AllowGameDVR\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows Game Recording and Broadcasting is intended for use with games, however it could potentially record screen shots of other applications and expose sensitive data.  Disabling the feature will prevent this from occurring.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-89091","V-74417","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"2478","uuid":"b2be5572-9984-4b2e-90b8-47f36c1d130b","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E8F148AB38414A2FCC620C4EF0EB0E5B97D2B93D\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows 10 must be configured to disable Windows Game Recording and Broadcasting.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220846","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220846","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220846","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220846r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220846","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000255","rule_title":"The use of a hardware security device with Windows Hello for Business must be enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Hello for Business >> \"Use a hardware security device\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nv1507 LTSB:\nThe policy path is Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Passport for Work.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Virtual desktop implementations currently may not support the use of TPMs. For virtual desktop implementations where the virtual desktop instance is deleted or refreshed upon logoff, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\PassportForWork\\\n\nValue Name: RequireSecurityDevice\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The use of a Trusted Platform Module (TPM) to store keys for Windows Hello for Business provides additional security.  Keys stored in the TPM may only be used on that system while keys stored using software are more susceptible to compromise and could be used on other systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78207","V-63717","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3435","uuid":"8f2919c2-ed22-4b86-abfa-2a9b40b17742","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 12D657077F66D05A1B4BAC049F292C468D758FC3\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The use of a hardware security device with Windows Hello for Business must be enabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220847","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220847","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220847","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220847r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220847","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000260","rule_title":"Windows 10 must be configured to require a minimum pin length of six characters or greater.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> PIN Complexity >> \"Minimum PIN length\" to \"6\" or greater. \n\nv1607 LTSB:\nThe policy path is Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Hello for Business >> Pin Complexity.\n\nv1507 LTSB:\nThe policy path is Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Passport for Work >> Pin Complexity.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\PassportForWork\\PINComplexity\\\n\nValue Name:  MinimumPINLength\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  6 (or greater)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows allows the use of PINs as well as biometrics for authentication without sending a password to a network or website where it could be compromised.  Longer minimum PIN lengths increase the available combinations an attacker would have to attempt.  Shorter minimum length significantly reduces the strength.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78211","V-63721","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8943","uuid":"dedce24d-bb9c-4c19-bebf-b3439e3334b0","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2304071282F8787AFF36B055E62C526562B079A8\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows 10 must be configured to require a minimum pin length of six characters or greater.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220848","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220848","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220848","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","rule_id_src":"SV-220848r1051029_rule","rule_id":"SV-220848","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000270","rule_title":"Passwords must not be saved in the Remote Desktop Client.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Remote Desktop Services >> Remote Desktop Connection Client >> \"Do not allow passwords to be saved\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: DisablePasswordSaving\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Saving passwords in the Remote Desktop Client could allow an unauthorized user to establish a remote desktop session to another system. The system must be configured to prevent users from saving passwords in the Remote Desktop Client.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63729","SV-78219","CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"9907","uuid":"b4c1c596-3b47-4866-a34a-959ec8e179cb","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 3942B11B5FC5FA70CD064A35A0CA34C584B47919\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Passwords must not be saved in the Remote Desktop Client.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220849","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220849","title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220849","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","rule_id_src":"SV-220849r1137695_rule","rule_id":"SV-220849","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000275","rule_title":"Local drives must be prevented from sharing with Remote Desktop Session Hosts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Remote Desktop Services >> Remote Desktop Session Host >> Device and Resource Redirection >> \"Do not allow drive redirection\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: fDisableCdm\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Preventing users from sharing the local drives on their client computers to Remote Session Hosts that they access helps reduce possible exposure of sensitive data.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78221","V-63731","CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"2461","uuid":"016131b2-f8b6-4b6c-9edf-7c5efb31dc8c","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C1374ACC0A819E37E51221CB65E8159E727CC582\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Local drives must be prevented from sharing with Remote Desktop Session Hosts.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220850","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220850","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220850","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","rule_id_src":"SV-220850r1051030_rule","rule_id":"SV-220850","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000280","rule_title":"Remote Desktop Services must always prompt a client for passwords upon connection.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Remote Desktop Services >> Remote Desktop Session Host >> Security >> \"Always prompt for password upon connection\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: fPromptForPassword\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting controls the ability of users to supply passwords automatically as part of their remote desktop connection. Disabling this setting would allow anyone to use the stored credentials in a connection item to connect to the terminal server.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78223","V-63733","CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"8965","uuid":"787df41f-6566-48da-b44f-602ed0204e41","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 808BACD7AC927E34F7BC8FAAD3D74C55AF6C9D4F\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Remote Desktop Services must always prompt a client for passwords upon connection.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220851","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220851","title":"SRG-OS-000250-GPOS-00093","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220851","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000250-GPOS-00093","rule_id_src":"SV-220851r991554_rule","rule_id":"SV-220851","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000285","rule_title":"The Remote Desktop Session Host must require secure RPC communications.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Remote Desktop Services >> Remote Desktop Session Host >> Security \"Require secure RPC communication\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: fEncryptRPCTraffic\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing unsecure RPC communication exposes the system to man in the middle attacks and data disclosure attacks. A man in the middle attack occurs when an intruder captures packets between a client and server and modifies them before allowing the packets to be exchanged. Usually the attacker will modify the information in the packets in an attempt to cause either the client or server to reveal sensitive information.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63737","SV-78227","CCI-001453"],"reference_identifier":"8924","uuid":"742cae82-57cb-4d3e-bf7c-1860046dc4aa","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 96C40450253384EF474E82875745892C7264A682\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'The Remote Desktop Session Host must require secure RPC communications.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220852","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220852","title":"SRG-OS-000033-GPOS-00014","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220852","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000033-GPOS-00014","rule_id_src":"SV-220852r958408_rule","rule_id":"SV-220852","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000290","rule_title":"Remote Desktop Services must be configured with the client connection encryption set to the required level.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Remote Desktop Services >> Remote Desktop Session Host >> Security >> \"Set client connection encryption level\" to \"Enabled\" and \"High Level\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: MinEncryptionLevel\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 3","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Remote connections must be encrypted to prevent interception of data or sensitive information. Selecting \"High Level\" will ensure encryption of Remote Desktop Services sessions in both directions.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63741","SV-78231","CCI-000068","CCI-002890"],"reference_identifier":"5562","uuid":"8da1f72d-b653-4ec0-9575-6102f6520262","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 569492A064CF812DF3EEFB50CB5BFF3B04320CE6\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Remote Desktop Services must be configured with the client connection encryption set to the required level.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220853","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220853","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220853","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220853r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220853","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000295","rule_title":"Attachments must be prevented from being downloaded from RSS feeds.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> RSS Feeds >> \"Prevent downloading of enclosures\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Feeds\\\n\nValue Name: DisableEnclosureDownload\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Attachments from RSS feeds may not be secure.  This setting will prevent attachments from being downloaded from RSS feeds.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78233","V-63743","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3241","uuid":"58b72c1a-936a-47ec-b2db-99945f2abbf2","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9E75A0F193E1EEB7294AB96F939C245D2B10B95B\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Attachments must be prevented from being downloaded from RSS feeds.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220854","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220854","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220854","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-220854r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-220854","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000300","rule_title":"Basic authentication for RSS feeds over HTTP must not be used.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for the Windows RSS platform to not use Basic authentication over HTTP connections.\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> RSS Feeds >> \"Turn on Basic feed authentication over HTTP\" to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for the Windows RSS platform to not use Basic authentication over HTTP connections.\n\nIf the registry value name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Feeds\\\n\nValue Name: AllowBasicAuthInClear\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0 (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Basic authentication uses plain text passwords that could be used to compromise a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78237","V-63747","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3337","uuid":"bea19010-d62e-4809-9c45-ecb9d9755256","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E5B869338BA59911411DC74E94C284EF376D9C70\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Basic authentication for RSS feeds over HTTP must not be used.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220855","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220855","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220855","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-220855r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-220855","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000305","rule_title":"Indexing of encrypted files must be turned off.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Search >> \"Allow indexing of encrypted files\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Windows Search\\\n\nValue Name: AllowIndexingEncryptedStoresOrItems\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Indexing of encrypted files may expose sensitive data.  This setting prevents encrypted files from being indexed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63751","SV-78241","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"7216","uuid":"8d4e921e-3d25-477a-9c5c-d10363b6ee3e","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C03C4D72EF18342A191748E76FCFE84A157EB5CB\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Indexing of encrypted files must be turned off.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220856","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220856","title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220856","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","rule_id_src":"SV-220856r1051031_rule","rule_id":"SV-220856","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000310","rule_title":"Users must be prevented from changing installation options.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Installer >> \"Allow user control over installs\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Installer\\\n\nValue Name: EnableUserControl\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Installation options for applications are typically controlled by administrators. This setting prevents users from changing installation options that may bypass security features.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63321","SV-77811","CCI-003980","CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"7495","uuid":"e42138ca-9d17-4193-96f1-52ba2fcab060","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 15153FB51FA6FFA0937AB1A910BED2AF7856AB70\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Users must be prevented from changing installation options.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220857","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220857","title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220857","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","rule_id_src":"SV-220857r1051032_rule","rule_id":"SV-220857","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000315","rule_title":"The Windows Installer Always install with elevated privileges must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Installer >> \"Always install with elevated privileges\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Installer\\\n\nValue Name: AlwaysInstallElevated\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Standard user accounts must not be granted elevated privileges. Enabling Windows Installer to elevate privileges when installing applications can allow malicious persons and applications to gain full control of a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63325","SV-77815","CCI-003980","CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"5399","uuid":"99d7a0fa-2d0e-40a9-ad85-4d4edc0c5130","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1E287D901D705D69D018587936FB2CAB524F0E66\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Windows Installer Always install with elevated privileges must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220858","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220858","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220858","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220858r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220858","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000320","rule_title":"Users must be notified if a web-based program attempts to install software.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for Internet Explorer to warn users and select whether to allow or refuse installation when a web-based program attempts to install software on the system.\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Installer >> \"Prevent Internet Explorer security prompt for Windows Installer scripts\" to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for Internet Explorer to warn users and select whether to allow or refuse installation when a web-based program attempts to install software on the system.\n\nIf the registry value name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Installer\\\n\nValue Name: SafeForScripting\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0 (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Web-based programs may attempt to install malicious software on a system.  Ensuring users are notified if a web-based program attempts to install software allows them to refuse the installation.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63329","SV-77819","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2075","uuid":"e3a66828-fccf-4642-afb0-a85943b14981","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0C6B7895101A33495ABE6FC0F8CC72141DEA30F7\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Users must be notified if a web-based program attempts to install software.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220859","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220859","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00229","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220859","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00229","rule_id_src":"SV-220859r991591_rule","rule_id":"SV-220859","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000325","rule_title":"Automatically signing in the last interactive user after a system-initiated restart must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Logon Options >> \"Sign-in last interactive user automatically after a system-initiated restart\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: DisableAutomaticRestartSignOn\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows can be configured to automatically sign the user back in after a Windows Update restart.  Some protections are in place to help ensure this is done in a secure fashion; however, disabling this will prevent the caching of credentials for this purpose and also ensure the user is aware of the restart.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-77823","V-63333","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2067","uuid":"98218c4d-e700-481b-9725-4b4d400627d6","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 177F546A08E14D8406C5936CE0B2D8C8FB4E055E\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Automatically signing in the last interactive user after a system-initiated restart must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220860","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220860","title":"SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220860","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020","rule_id_src":"SV-220860r958422_rule","rule_id":"SV-220860","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000326","rule_title":"PowerShell script block logging must be enabled on Windows 10.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows PowerShell >> \"Turn on PowerShell Script Block Logging\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\PowerShell\\ScriptBlockLogging\\\n\nValue Name: EnableScriptBlockLogging\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nEnabling PowerShell script block logging will record detailed information from the processing of PowerShell commands and scripts.  This can provide additional detail when malware has run on a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-68819","SV-83411","CCI-000135"],"reference_identifier":"1670","uuid":"1354fa24-eb46-46e5-a9b7-555e96a9b5f9","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 276EDFBEDBBB0B11E9FDFE4CF179A20DFCE71027\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'PowerShell script block logging must be enabled on Windows 10.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220862","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220862","title":"SRG-OS-000125-GPOS-00065","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220862","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000125-GPOS-00065","rule_id_src":"SV-220862r958510_rule","rule_id":"SV-220862","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000330","rule_title":"The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) client must not use Basic authentication.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Remote Management (WinRM) >> WinRM Client >> \"Allow Basic authentication\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Client\\\n\nValue Name: AllowBasic\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Basic authentication uses plain text passwords that could be used to compromise a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63335","SV-77825","CCI-000877"],"reference_identifier":"6553","uuid":"2a6542e2-a873-4075-8dc7-c268f0c24808","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 3810333310BA3C22985F36A85F91244900BD8D39\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) client must not use Basic authentication.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220863","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220863","title":"SRG-OS-000393-GPOS-00173","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220863","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000393-GPOS-00173","rule_id_src":"SV-220863r958848_rule","rule_id":"SV-220863","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000335","rule_title":"The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) client must not allow unencrypted traffic.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Remote Management (WinRM) >> WinRM Client >> \"Allow unencrypted traffic\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Client\\\n\nValue Name: AllowUnencryptedTraffic\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unencrypted remote access to a system can allow sensitive information to be compromised.  Windows remote management connections must be encrypted to prevent this.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-77829","V-63339","CCI-002890","CCI-003123"],"reference_identifier":"5206","uuid":"cc6e8c03-d1e4-4e81-9e01-f9bcc38c226d","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DA9B0B79DDDCE01C54BE2A71A87AF3E1FE570078\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) client must not allow unencrypted traffic.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220865","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220865","title":"SRG-OS-000125-GPOS-00065","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220865","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000125-GPOS-00065","rule_id_src":"SV-220865r958510_rule","rule_id":"SV-220865","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000345","rule_title":"The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) service must not use Basic authentication.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Remote Management (WinRM) >> WinRM Service >> \"Allow Basic authentication\" to \"Disabled\".\n\nSeverity Override Guidance: The AO can allow the severity override if they have reviewed the overall protection. This would only be allowed temporarily for implementation as documented and approved. \n\u2026.\nAllowing Basic authentication to be used for the sole creation of Office 365 DoD tenants.\n\u2026.\nA documented mechanism and or script that can disable Basic authentication once administration completes. \n\u2026.\nUse of a Privileged Access Workstation (PAW) and adherence to the Clean Source principle for administration.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Service\\\n\nValue Name: AllowBasic\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Basic authentication uses plain text passwords that could be used to compromise a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-77837","V-63347","CCI-000877"],"reference_identifier":"9175","uuid":"0105af92-91ba-4d1c-a3d1-d055bedb6d67","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8D8DA1C90E88EA89EE43B60C0C2776B2C60F6294\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) service must not use Basic authentication.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220866","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220866","title":"SRG-OS-000393-GPOS-00173","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220866","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000393-GPOS-00173","rule_id_src":"SV-220866r958848_rule","rule_id":"SV-220866","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000350","rule_title":"The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) service must not allow unencrypted traffic.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Remote Management (WinRM) >> WinRM Service >> \"Allow unencrypted traffic\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Service\\\n\nValue Name: AllowUnencryptedTraffic\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unencrypted remote access to a system can allow sensitive information to be compromised.  Windows remote management connections must be encrypted to prevent this.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63369","SV-77859","CCI-002890","CCI-003123"],"reference_identifier":"8696","uuid":"855e78ae-a910-4e28-b4bc-9d93c3cc73e8","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 48F3FD14B49B87849A63212B7D03475F7896159E\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) service must not allow unencrypted traffic.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220867","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220867","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220867","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","rule_id_src":"SV-220867r1051033_rule","rule_id":"SV-220867","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000355","rule_title":"The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) service must not store RunAs credentials.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Remote Management (WinRM) >> WinRM Service >> \"Disallow WinRM from storing RunAs credentials\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Service\\\n\nValue Name: DisableRunAs\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Storage of administrative credentials could allow unauthorized access. Disallowing the storage of RunAs credentials for Windows Remote Management will prevent them from being used with plug-ins.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63375","SV-77865","CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"7963","uuid":"1b9264a6-d476-4034-bdba-f13829d2b1c2","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: ED927E90D74C63670B3AC7229103DE9C53371CE9\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) service must not store RunAs credentials.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220868","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220868","title":"SRG-OS-000125-GPOS-00065","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220868","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000125-GPOS-00065","rule_id_src":"SV-220868r958510_rule","rule_id":"SV-220868","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000360","rule_title":"The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) client must not use Digest authentication.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Remote Management (WinRM) >> WinRM Client >> \"Disallow Digest authentication\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Client\\\n\nValue Name: AllowDigest\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Digest authentication is not as strong as other options and may be subject to man-in-the-middle attacks.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63341","SV-77831","CCI-000877"],"reference_identifier":"9630","uuid":"3edca8dd-abb0-4dec-8849-5db07a01fa16","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 65758EE5EC1700C907F20859470E7C80541915A6\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) client must not use Digest authentication.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220869","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220869","title":"SRG-OS-000028-GPOS-00009","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220869","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000028-GPOS-00009","rule_id_src":"SV-220869r958400_rule","rule_id":"SV-220869","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000365","rule_title":"Windows 10 must be configured to prevent Windows apps from being activated by voice while the system is locked.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> App Privacy >> \"Let Windows apps activate with voice while the system is locked\" to \"Enabled\" with \u201cDefault for all Apps:\u201d set to \u201cForce Deny\u201d. \n\nThe requirement is NA if the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> App Privacy >> \"Let Windows apps activate with voice\" is configured to \"Enabled\" with \u201cDefault for all Apps:\u201d set to \u201cForce Deny\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This setting requires v1903 or later of Windows 10; it is NA for prior versions.  The setting is NA when the \u201cAllow voice activation\u201d policy is configured to disallow applications to be activated with voice for all users.\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\AppPrivacy\\\n\nValue Name: LetAppsActivateWithVoiceAboveLock\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000002 (2)\n\nIf the following registry value exists and is configured as specified, requirement is NA. \n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\AppPrivacy\\\n\nValue Name: LetAppsActivateWithVoice\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000002 (2)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing Windows apps to be activated by voice from the lock screen could allow for unauthorized use. Requiring logon will ensure the apps are only used by authorized personnel.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-94719","SV-104549","CCI-000056"],"reference_identifier":"7933","uuid":"3305689c-4fce-4af7-b8ee-af889ddbb483","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F30A69632FA79636D51F79004930500CF181992F\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Windows 10 must be configured to prevent Windows apps from being activated by voice while the system is locked.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220870","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220870","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220870","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-220870r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-220870","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000370","rule_title":"The convenience PIN for Windows 10 must be disabled.","fix_text":"Disable the convenience PIN sign-in. \n\nIf this needs to be corrected configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Logon >> Set \"Turn on convenience PIN sign-in\" to \"Disabled\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\System\n\nValue Name: AllowDomainPINLogon\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue data: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy controls whether a domain user can sign in using a convenience PIN to prevent enabling (Password Stuffer).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-99559","SV-108663","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"8938","uuid":"ee953894-b3fb-4087-aaf3-61ba0dfa96e8","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-220871","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220871","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220871","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-220871r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-220871","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000385","rule_title":"Windows Ink Workspace must be configured to disallow access above the lock.","fix_text":"Disable the convenience PIN sign-in. \n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Ink Workspace >> Set \"Allow Windows Ink Workspace\" to \"Enabled\u201d and set Options \"On, but disallow access above lock\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsInkWorkspace\n\nValue Name: AllowWindowsInkWorkspace\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue data: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This action secures Windows Ink, which contains applications and features oriented toward pen computing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108665","V-99561","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3945","uuid":"74cd76d8-8181-4166-8a24-e58a0bf26327","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-220872","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220872","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220872","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-220872r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-220872","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000390","rule_title":"Windows 10 should be configured to prevent users from receiving suggestions for third-party or additional applications.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Cloud Content >> \"Do not suggest third-party content in Windows spotlight\" to \"Enabled","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding: \n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CloudContent\\\n\nValue Name: DisableThirdPartySuggestions\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows spotlight features may suggest apps and content from third-party software publishers in addition to Microsoft apps and content.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-99563","SV-108667","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"8815","uuid":"b02e99d7-3173-4c2a-8eed-476a477ce84e","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-220902","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220902","title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220902","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","rule_id_src":"SV-220902r1137695_rule","rule_id":"SV-220902","rule_version":"WN10-EP-000310","rule_title":"Windows 10 Kernel (Direct Memory Access) DMA Protection must be enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Kernel DMA Protection >> \"Enumeration policy for external devices incompatible with Kernel DMA Protection\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Enumeration Policy\" set to \"Block All\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is NA prior to v1803 of Windows 10.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Kernel DMA Protection\n\nValue Name: DeviceEnumerationPolicy\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Kernel DMA Protection to protect PCs against drive-by Direct Memory Access (DMA) attacks using PCI hot plug devices connected to Thunderbolt\u2122 3 ports. Drive-by DMA attacks can lead to disclosure of sensitive information residing on a PC, or even injection of malware that allows attackers to bypass the lock screen or control PCs remotely.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108661","V-99557","CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"8621","uuid":"0dd6c59c-d075-40eb-b517-f92bb64ac2d6","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8B9BF9434DC6ED14DAAB5EB621A39A9F26621EC3\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Windows 10 Kernel (Direct Memory Access) DMA Protection must be enabled.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220903","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220903","title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220903","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","rule_id_src":"SV-220903r958448_rule","rule_id":"SV-220903","rule_version":"WN10-PK-000005","rule_title":"The DoD Root CA certificates must be installed in the Trusted Root Store.","fix_text":"Install the DoD Root CA certificates:\nDoD Root CA 3\nDoD Root CA 4\nDoD Root CA 5\nDoD Root CA 6\n\nThe InstallRoot tool is available on Cyber Exchange at https://cyber.mil/pki-pke/tools-configuration-files. Certificate bundles published by the PKI can be found at https://crl.gds.disa.mil/.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the DoD Root CA certificates are installed as Trusted Root Certification Authorities.\n\nThe certificates and thumbprints referenced below apply to unclassified systems; refer to PKE documentation for other networks.\n\nRun \"PowerShell\" as an administrator.\n\nExecute the following command:\n\nGet-ChildItem -Path Cert:Localmachine\\root | Where Subject -Like \"*DoD*\" | FL Subject, Thumbprint, NotAfter\n\nIf the following certificate \"Subject\" and \"Thumbprint\" information is not displayed, this is a finding.\n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 3, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: D73CA91102A2204A36459ED32213B467D7CE97FB\nNotAfter: 12/30/2029\n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 4, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: B8269F25DBD937ECAFD4C35A9838571723F2D026\nNotAfter: 7/25/2032\n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 5, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: 4ECB5CC3095670454DA1CBD410FC921F46B8564B\nNotAfter: 6/14/2041\n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 6, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US \nThumbprint : D37ECF61C0B4ED88681EF3630C4E2FC787B37AEF\nNotAfter: 1/24/2053\n\nAlternately, use the Certificates MMC snap-in:\n\nRun \"MMC\".\n\nSelect \"File\", \"Add/Remove Snap-in\".\n\nSelect \"Certificates\", click \"Add\".\n\nSelect \"Computer account\", click \"Next\".\n\nSelect \"Local computer: (the computer this console is running on)\", click \"Finish\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nExpand \"Certificates\" and navigate to \"Trusted Root Certification Authorities >> Certificates\".\n\nFor each of the DoD Root CA certificates noted below:\n\nRight-click on the certificate and select \"Open\".\n\nSelect the \"Details\" tab.\n\nScroll to the bottom and select \"Thumbprint\".\n\nIf the DoD Root CA certificates below are not listed or the value for the \"Thumbprint\" field is not as noted, this is a finding.\n\nDoD Root CA 3\nThumbprint: D73CA91102A2204A36459ED32213B467D7CE97FB\nValid to: Sunday, December 30, 2029\n\nDoD Root CA 4\nThumbprint: B8269F25DBD937ECAFD4C35A9838571723F2D026\nValid to: Sunday, July 25, 2032\n\nDoD Root CA 5\nThumbprint: 4ECB5CC3095670454DA1CBD410FC921F46B8564B\nValid to: Friday, June 14, 2041\n\nDoD Root CA 6\nThumbprint : D37ECF61C0B4ED88681EF3630C4E2FC787B37AEF\n Valid to: Friday, January 24, 2053","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"To ensure secure DoD websites and DoD-signed code are properly validated, the system must trust the DoD Root Certificate Authorities (CAs). The DoD root certificates will ensure the trust chain is established for server certificates issued from the DoD CAs.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63579","SV-78069","CCI-000185","CCI-002470"],"reference_identifier":"4916","uuid":"fb5a46c4-9c0e-41f2-9a25-e2fb756940d2","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7DC3362F4EB0D8E4C078D935A3199A24787C2B76\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The DoD Root CA certificates must be installed in the Trusted Root Store.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220904","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220904","title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220904","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","rule_id_src":"SV-220904r958448_rule","rule_id":"SV-220904","rule_version":"WN10-PK-000010","rule_title":"The External Root CA certificates must be installed in the Trusted Root Store on unclassified systems.","fix_text":"Install the ECA Root CA certificate on unclassified systems.\nECA Root CA 4\n\nThe InstallRoot tool is available on Cyber Exchange at https://cyber.mil/pki-pke/tools-configuration-files. Certificate bundles published by the PKI can be found at https://crl.gds.disa.mil/.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the ECA Root CA certificates are installed on unclassified systems as Trusted Root Certification Authorities.\n\nRun \"PowerShell\" as an administrator.\n\nExecute the following command:\n\nGet-ChildItem -Path Cert:Localmachine\\root | Where Subject -Like \"*ECA*\" | FL Subject, Thumbprint, NotAfter\n\nIf the following certificate \"Subject\" and \"Thumbprint\" information is not displayed, this is a finding. \n\nSubject: CN=ECA Root CA 4, OU=ECA, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: 73E8BB08E337D6A5A6AEF90CFFDD97D9176CB582\nNotAfter: 12/30/2029\n\nAlternately use the Certificates MMC snap-in:\n\nRun \"MMC\".\n\nSelect \"File\", \"Add/Remove Snap-in\".\n\nSelect \"Certificates\", click \"Add\".\n\nSelect \"Computer account\", click \"Next\".\n\nSelect \"Local computer: (the computer this console is running on)\", click \"Finish\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nExpand \"Certificates\" and navigate to \"Trusted Root Certification Authorities >> Certificates\".\n\nFor each of the ECA Root CA certificates noted below:\n\nRight-click on the certificate and select \"Open\".\n\nSelect the \"Details\" Tab.\n\nScroll to the bottom and select \"Thumbprint\".\n\nIf the ECA Root CA certificate below is not listed or the value for the \"Thumbprint\" field is not as noted, this is a finding.\n\nECA Root CA 4\nThumbprint: 73E8BB08E337D6A5A6AEF90CFFDD97D9176CB582\nValid to: Sunday, December 30, 2029","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"To ensure secure websites protected with External Certificate Authority (ECA) server certificates are properly validated, the system must trust the ECA Root CAs. The ECA root certificates will ensure the trust chain is established for server certificates issued from the External CAs. This requirement only applies to unclassified systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63583","SV-78073","CCI-000185"],"reference_identifier":"2393","uuid":"a1aa5ea6-273d-4922-a581-9bc100c6a360","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1BD0D1C43F36DA43647BFAAA2A10D92863E952B8\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The External Root CA certificates must be installed in the Trusted Root Store on unclassified systems.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220905","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220905","title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220905","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","rule_id_src":"SV-220905r958448_rule","rule_id":"SV-220905","rule_version":"WN10-PK-000015","rule_title":"The DoD Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates must be installed in the Untrusted Certificates Store on unclassified systems.","fix_text":"Install the DoD Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates on unclassified systems.\n\nIssued To - Issued By - Thumbprint\n\nDoD Root CA 3 - DoD Interoperability Root CA 2 - 49CBE933151872E17C8EAE7F0ABA97FB610F6477 \n                  \nThe certificates can be installed using the InstallRoot tool. The tool and user guide are available on Cyber Exchange at https://cyber.mil/pki-pke/tools-configuration-files. PKI can be found at https://crl.gds.disa.mil/.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the DoD Interoperability cross-certificates are installed on unclassified systems as Untrusted Certificates.\n\nRun \"PowerShell\" as an administrator.\n\nExecute the following command:\n\nGet-ChildItem -Path Cert:Localmachine\\disallowed | Where {$_.Issuer -Like \"*DoD Interoperability*\" -and $_.Subject -Like \"*DoD*\"} | FL Subject, Issuer, Thumbprint, NotAfter\n\nIf the following certificate \"Subject\", \"Issuer\", and \"Thumbprint\" information is not displayed, this is a finding.\n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 3, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nIssuer: CN=DoD Interoperability Root CA 2, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: 49CBE933151872E17C8EAE7F0ABA97FB610F6477\nNotAfter: 11/16/2024 \n\nAlternately, use the Certificates MMC snap-in:\n\nRun \"MMC\".\n\nSelect \"File\", \"Add/Remove Snap-in\".\n\nSelect \"Certificates\", click \"Add\".\n\nSelect \"Computer account\", click \"Next\".\n\nSelect \"Local computer: (the computer this console is running on)\", click \"Finish\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nExpand \"Certificates\" and navigate to Untrusted Certificates >> Certificates.\n\nFor each certificate with \"DoD Root CA\u2026\" under \"Issued To\" and \"DoD Interoperability Root CA\u2026\" under \"Issued By\":\n\nRight-click on the certificate and select \"Open\".\n\nSelect the \"Details\" tab.\n\nScroll to the bottom and select \"Thumbprint\".\n\nIf the certificates below are not listed or the value for the \"Thumbprint\" field is not as noted, this is a finding.\n\nIssued To: DoD Root CA 3\nIssued By: DoD Interoperability Root CA 2\nThumbprint: 49CBE933151872E17C8EAE7F0ABA97FB610F6477\nValid to: Wednesday, November 16, 2024","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"To ensure users do not experience denial of service when performing certificate-based authentication to DoD websites due to the system chaining to a root other than DoD Root CAs, the DoD Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates must be installed in the Untrusted Certificate Store. This requirement only applies to unclassified systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63587","SV-78077","CCI-000185","CCI-002470"],"reference_identifier":"5504","uuid":"60e45672-b572-4c15-a6da-522d3e1b372c","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8AE9CD26952224EC749C7957BEEF8D219A16BBE5\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The DoD Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates must be installed in the Untrusted Certificates Store on unclassified systems.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220906","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220906","title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220906","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","rule_id_src":"SV-220906r1081051_rule","rule_id":"SV-220906","rule_version":"WN10-PK-000020","rule_title":"The US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates must be installed in the Untrusted Certificates Store on unclassified systems.","fix_text":"Install the US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA cross-certificate on unclassified systems.\n\nIssued To - Issued By - Thumbprint\nDOD Root CA 3 - US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA 2  9B74964506C7ED9138070D08D5F8B969866560C8\nIssued To: DOD Root CA 6\nIssued By: US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA 2\nThumbprint: D471CA32F7A692CE6CBB6196BD3377FE4DBCD106\nNotAfter: 7/18/2026\n\nThe certificates can be installed using the InstallRoot tool. The tool and user guide are available on Cyber Exchange at https://cyber.mil/pki-pke/tools-configuration-files. PKI can be found at https://crl.gds.disa.mil/.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA cross-certificate is installed on unclassified systems as an Untrusted Certificate.\n\nRun \"PowerShell\" as an administrator.\n\nExecute the following command:\n\nGet-ChildItem -Path Cert:Localmachine\\disallowed | Where Issuer -Like \"*CCEB Interoperability*\" | FL Subject, Issuer, Thumbprint, NotAfter\n\nIf the following certificate \"Subject\", \"Issuer\", and \"Thumbprint\" information is not displayed, this is a finding. \n\nSubject: CN=DOD Root CA 3, OU=PKI, OU=DOD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nIssuer: CN=US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA 2, OU=PKI, OU=DOD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: 9B74964506C7ED9138070D08D5F8B969866560C8\nNotAfter: 7/18/2025 9:56:22 AM\n\nAlternately, use the Certificates MMC snap-in:\n\nRun \"MMC\".\n\nSelect \"File\", then click \"Add/Remove Snap-in\".\n\nSelect \"Certificates\", then click \"Add\".\n\nSelect \"Computer account\", then click \"Next\".\n\nSelect \"Local computer: (the computer this console is running on)\", then click \"Finish\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nExpand \"Certificates\" and navigate to Untrusted Certificates >> Certificates.\n\nFor each certificate with \"US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA \u2026\" under \"Issued By\":\n\nRight-click on the certificate and select \"Open\".\n\nSelect the \"Details\" tab.\n\nScroll to the bottom and select \"Thumbprint\".\n\nIf the certificate below is not listed or the value for the \"Thumbprint\" field is not as noted, this is a finding.\n\nSubject: CN=DOD Root CA 3, OU=PKI, OU=DOD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nIssuer: CN=US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA 2, OU=PKI, OU=DOD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: 9B74964506C7ED9138070D08D5F8B969866560C8\nNotAfter: 7/18/2025 9:56:22 AM                                                          \nSubject: CN=DOD Root CA 6, OU=PKI, OU=DOD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nIssuer: CN=US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA 2, OU=PKI, OU=DOD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: D471CA32F7A692CE6CBB6196BD3377FE4DBCD106\nNotAfter: 7/18/2026 9:56:22 AM","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"To ensure users do not experience denial of service when performing certificate-based authentication to DOD websites due to the system chaining to a root other than DOD Root CAs, the US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates must be installed in the Untrusted Certificate Store. This requirement only applies to unclassified systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78079","V-63589","CCI-000185","CCI-002470"],"reference_identifier":"5213","uuid":"e3322fc3-8756-4eb8-a1c5-4dad23bba7d0","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-220907","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220907","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220907","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-220907r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-220907","rule_version":"WN10-RG-000005","rule_title":"Default permissions for the HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE registry hive must be maintained.","fix_text":"Maintain the default permissions for the HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE registry hive.\n\nThe default permissions of the higher level keys are noted below.\n\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SECURITY\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\nSYSTEM - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nAdministrators - Special - This key and subkeys\n\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\nUsers - Read - This key and subkeys\nAdministrators - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nSYSTEM - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nCREATOR OWNER - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read - This key and subkeys\n\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\nUsers - Read - This key and subkeys\nAdministrators - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nSYSTEM - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nCREATOR OWNER - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read - This key and subkeys\n\nMicrosoft has also given Read permission to the SOFTWARE and SYSTEM registry keys in later versions of Windows 10 to the following SID.\n\nS-1-15-3-1024-1065365936-1281604716-3511738428-1654721687-432734479-3232135806-4053264122-3456934681","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the default registry permissions for the keys note below of the HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE hive.\n\nIf any non-privileged groups such as Everyone, Users or Authenticated Users have greater than Read permission, this is a finding.\n\nRun \"Regedit\".\nRight click on the registry areas noted below.\nSelect \"Permissions...\" and the \"Advanced\" button.\n\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SECURITY\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\nSYSTEM - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nAdministrators - Special - This key and subkeys\n\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\nUsers - Read - This key and subkeys\nAdministrators - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nSYSTEM - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nCREATOR OWNER - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read - This key and subkeys\n\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\nUsers - Read - This key and subkeys\nAdministrators - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nSYSTEM - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nCREATOR OWNER - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read - This key and subkeys\n\nOther subkeys under the noted keys may also be sampled. There may be some instances where non-privileged groups have greater than Read permission.\n\nMicrosoft has given Read permission to the SOFTWARE and SYSTEM registry keys in later versions of Windows 10 to the following SID, this is currently not a finding.\n\nS-1-15-3-1024-1065365936-1281604716-3511738428-1654721687-432734479-3232135806-4053264122-3456934681\n\nIf the defaults have not been changed, these are not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The registry is integral to the function, security, and stability of the Windows system.  Changing the system's registry permissions allows the possibility of unauthorized and anonymous modification to the operating system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78083","V-63593","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"4256","uuid":"8f9ab488-068e-4739-8851-44685d652daf","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: CBFF9887F7F81D0F2DB6C4809A777D3D07169A90\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Default permissions for the HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE registry hive must be maintained.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220909","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220909","title":"SRG-OS-000121-GPOS-00062","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220909","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000121-GPOS-00062","rule_id_src":"SV-220909r958504_rule","rule_id":"SV-220909","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000010","rule_title":"The built-in guest account must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Accounts: Guest account status\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Accounts: Guest account status\" is not set to \"Disabled\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A system faces an increased vulnerability threat if the built-in guest account is not disabled.  This account is a known account that exists on all Windows systems and cannot be deleted.  This account is initialized during the installation of the operating system with no password assigned.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63611","SV-78101","CCI-000804"],"reference_identifier":"8940","uuid":"bdf79c6f-5e3d-4e3d-9e63-126fce38696e","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D317DAC24F53E59C2DB5A937300EDAD6B2D20D38\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The built-in guest account must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220910","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220910","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220910","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220910r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220910","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000015","rule_title":"Local accounts with blank passwords must be restricted to prevent access from the network.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Accounts: Limit local account use of blank passwords to console logon only\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: LimitBlankPasswordUse\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"An account without a password can allow unauthorized access to a system as only the username would be required.  Password policies should prevent accounts with blank passwords from existing on a system.  However, if a local account with a blank password did exist, enabling this setting will prevent network access, limiting the account to local console logon only.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63617","SV-78107","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1584","uuid":"b47d09df-cd4c-476d-a5c8-8faa58746841","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0DA349585FE251D07D9647446FF3038687DB8E70\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Local accounts with blank passwords must be restricted to prevent access from the network.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220911","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220911","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220911","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220911r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220911","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000020","rule_title":"The built-in administrator account must be renamed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Accounts: Rename administrator account\" to a name other than \"Administrator\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Accounts: Rename administrator account\" is set to \"Administrator\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The built-in administrator account is a well-known account subject to attack.  Renaming this account to an unidentified name improves the protection of this account and the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78109","V-63619","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5798","uuid":"ace507ab-63e5-4acc-ade3-58d14f74f543","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6D7EEE96DAD63874A6C8710F2976B8F3BDD1DC90\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The built-in administrator account must be renamed.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220912","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220912","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220912","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220912r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220912","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000025","rule_title":"The built-in guest account must be renamed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Accounts: Rename guest account\" to a name other than \"Guest\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Accounts: Rename guest account\" is set to \"Guest\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The built-in guest account is a well-known user account on all Windows systems and, as initially installed, does not require a password.  This can allow access to system resources by unauthorized users.  Renaming this account to an unidentified name improves the protection of this account and the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78115","V-63625","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9008","uuid":"a05406b0-8caa-4317-860f-7ffb20e2e76b","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A7636A209FF8D90F049770B46535842BAF4623DF\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The built-in guest account must be renamed.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220913","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220913","title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220913","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","rule_id_src":"SV-220913r958442_rule","rule_id":"SV-220913","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000030","rule_title":"Audit policy using subcategories must be enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: SCENoApplyLegacyAuditPolicy\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks.  Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised.  Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.  This setting allows administrators to enable more precise auditing capabilities.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63635","SV-78125","CCI-000169"],"reference_identifier":"9755","uuid":"84fab0a9-2fa5-404d-9841-8fb4ce422c6f","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 69CB421709F4C0C487116B98F032CF33756271AC\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Audit policy using subcategories must be enabled.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220914","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220914","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220914","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","rule_id_src":"SV-220914r958908_rule","rule_id":"SV-220914","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000035","rule_title":"Outgoing secure channel traffic must be encrypted or signed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Domain member: Digitally encrypt or sign secure channel data (always)\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: RequireSignOrSeal\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Requests sent on the secure channel are authenticated, and sensitive information (such as passwords) is encrypted, but not all information is encrypted.  If this policy is enabled, outgoing secure channel traffic will be encrypted and signed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63639","SV-78129","CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"9922","uuid":"8a030129-c1ab-4cf1-a035-5c3aefbfe176","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5D346455157BB20AA814DCD9187DB6AB6140809B\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Outgoing secure channel traffic must be encrypted or signed.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220915","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220915","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220915","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","rule_id_src":"SV-220915r958908_rule","rule_id":"SV-220915","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000040","rule_title":"Outgoing secure channel traffic must be encrypted when possible.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Domain member: Digitally encrypt secure channel data (when possible)\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: SealSecureChannel\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Requests sent on the secure channel are authenticated, and sensitive information (such as passwords) is encrypted, but not all information is encrypted.  If this policy is enabled, outgoing secure channel traffic will be encrypted.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78133","V-63643","CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"8261","uuid":"7553b6d2-b69e-4c1e-be5d-0ce449c4a5b2","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D4677955D05E860C86934222CFBB6C0198B63FE8\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Outgoing secure channel traffic must be encrypted when possible.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220916","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220916","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220916","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","rule_id_src":"SV-220916r958908_rule","rule_id":"SV-220916","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000045","rule_title":"Outgoing secure channel traffic must be signed when possible.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Domain member: Digitally sign secure channel data (when possible)\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: SignSecureChannel\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Requests sent on the secure channel are authenticated, and sensitive information (such as passwords) is encrypted, but the channel is not integrity checked.  If this policy is enabled, outgoing secure channel traffic will be signed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78137","V-63647","CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"1739","uuid":"3e4d36bf-da66-4c3a-9cd6-306caaffa06f","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 645E21C6978701BC64725B745F1171FC650029F1\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Outgoing secure channel traffic must be signed when possible.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220917","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220917","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220917","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220917r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220917","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000050","rule_title":"The computer account password must not be prevented from being reset.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Domain member: Disable machine account password changes\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: DisablePasswordChange\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Computer account passwords are changed automatically on a regular basis.  Disabling automatic password changes can make the system more vulnerable to malicious access.  Frequent password changes can be a significant safeguard for your system.  A new password for the computer account will be generated every 30 days.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63653","SV-78143","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9677","uuid":"b5cf393a-a88f-4984-aa1a-1d961e136da8","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C27E5DFA80FDABBABCD05AC9859888C93EB21B61\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The computer account password must not be prevented from being reset.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220918","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220918","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220918","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220918r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220918","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000055","rule_title":"The maximum age for machine account passwords must be configured to 30 days or less.","fix_text":"This is the default configuration for this setting (30 days).\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Domain member: Maximum machine account password age\" to \"30\" or less (excluding 0 which is unacceptable).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is the default configuration for this setting (30 days).\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: MaximumPasswordAge\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x0000001e (30)  (or less, excluding 0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Computer account passwords are changed automatically on a regular basis.  This setting controls the maximum password age that a machine account may have.  This setting must be set to no more than 30 days, ensuring the machine changes its password monthly.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78151","V-63661","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2075","uuid":"787e2386-f077-4106-a45c-582fd8d08f2c","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5A6CF4FB0777316833D0263E264DB97D38D2226E\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The maximum age for machine account passwords must be configured to 30 days or less.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220919","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220919","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220919","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","rule_id_src":"SV-220919r958908_rule","rule_id":"SV-220919","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000060","rule_title":"The system must be configured to require a strong session key.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Domain member: Require strong (Windows 2000 or Later) session key\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: RequireStrongKey\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n \nWarning: This setting may prevent a system from being joined to a domain if not configured consistently between systems.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A computer connecting to a domain controller will establish a secure channel.  Requiring strong session keys enforces 128-bit encryption between systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63665","SV-78155","CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"7633","uuid":"9a2694ab-43f6-4bc6-aae9-ad3c35d01f2a","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4626A425AA774499D717435F8350CB8028AD6A1A\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The system must be configured to require a strong session key.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220920","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220920","title":"SRG-OS-000029-GPOS-00010","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220920","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000029-GPOS-00010","rule_id_src":"SV-220920r958402_rule","rule_id":"SV-220920","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000070","rule_title":"The machine inactivity limit must be set to 15 minutes, locking the system with the screensaver.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Interactive logon: Machine inactivity limit\" to \"900\" seconds\" or less, excluding \"0\" which is effectively disabled.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: InactivityTimeoutSecs\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000384 (900) (or less, excluding \"0\" which is effectively disabled)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unattended systems are susceptible to unauthorized use and should be locked when unattended.  The screen saver should be set at a maximum of 15 minutes and be password protected.  This protects critical and sensitive data from exposure to unauthorized personnel with physical access to the computer.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78159","V-63669","CCI-000057"],"reference_identifier":"5767","uuid":"d9002b51-ad93-4832-80ee-824b1d8b685f","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F4F160469E8B25BDE4D2088289AD0A8BA2217A5F\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The machine inactivity limit must be set to 15 minutes, locking the system with the screensaver.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220921","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220921","title":"SRG-OS-000023-GPOS-00006","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220921","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000023-GPOS-00006","rule_id_src":"SV-220921r958390_rule","rule_id":"SV-220921","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000075","rule_title":"The required legal notice must be configured to display before console logon.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Interactive logon: Message text for users attempting to log on\" to the following.\n\nYou are accessing a U.S. Government (USG) Information System (IS) that is provided for USG-authorized use only.\n\nBy using this IS (which includes any device attached to this IS), you consent to the following conditions:\n\n-The USG routinely intercepts and monitors communications on this IS for purposes including, but not limited to, penetration testing, COMSEC monitoring, network operations and defense, personnel misconduct (PM), law enforcement (LE), and counterintelligence (CI) investigations.\n\n-At any time, the USG may inspect and seize data stored on this IS.\n\n-Communications using, or data stored on, this IS are not private, are subject to routine monitoring, interception, and search, and may be disclosed or used for any USG-authorized purpose.\n\n-This IS includes security measures (e.g., authentication and access controls) to protect USG interests--not for your personal benefit or privacy.\n\n-Notwithstanding the above, using this IS does not constitute consent to PM, LE or CI investigative searching or monitoring of the content of privileged communications, or work product, related to personal representation or services by attorneys, psychotherapists, or clergy, and their assistants.  Such communications and work product are private and confidential.  See User Agreement for details.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: LegalNoticeText\n\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: \nYou are accessing a U.S. Government (USG) Information System (IS) that is provided for USG-authorized use only.\n\nBy using this IS (which includes any device attached to this IS), you consent to the following conditions:\n\n-The USG routinely intercepts and monitors communications on this IS for purposes including, but not limited to, penetration testing, COMSEC monitoring, network operations and defense, personnel misconduct (PM), law enforcement (LE), and counterintelligence (CI) investigations.\n\n-At any time, the USG may inspect and seize data stored on this IS.\n\n-Communications using, or data stored on, this IS are not private, are subject to routine monitoring, interception, and search, and may be disclosed or used for any USG-authorized purpose.\n\n-This IS includes security measures (e.g., authentication and access controls) to protect USG interests--not for your personal benefit or privacy.\n\n-Notwithstanding the above, using this IS does not constitute consent to PM, LE or CI investigative searching or monitoring of the content of privileged communications, or work product, related to personal representation or services by attorneys, psychotherapists, or clergy, and their assistants.  Such communications and work product are private and confidential.  See User Agreement for details.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Failure to display the logon banner prior to a logon attempt will negate legal proceedings resulting from unauthorized access to system resources.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63675","SV-78165","CCI-000048","CCI-000050","CCI-001384","CCI-001385","CCI-001386","CCI-001387","CCI-001388"],"reference_identifier":"2301","uuid":"d4eabf38-fb77-4bc0-b151-d2a3dfea5a37","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 007AA0D5D2FDB7AE5E70829E24FD9FD21A499FB0\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'The required legal notice must be configured to display before console logon.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220922","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220922","title":"SRG-OS-000023-GPOS-00006","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220922","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000023-GPOS-00006","rule_id_src":"SV-220922r958390_rule","rule_id":"SV-220922","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000080","rule_title":"The Windows dialog box title for the legal banner must be configured.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Interactive logon: Message title for users attempting to log on\" to \"DoD Notice and Consent Banner\", \"US Department of Defense Warning Statement\", or a site-defined equivalent.\n\nIf a site-defined title is used, it can in no case contravene or modify the language of the banner text required in WN10-SO-000075.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: LegalNoticeCaption\n\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: See message title above\n\n\"DoD Notice and Consent Banner\", \"US Department of Defense Warning Statement\" or a site-defined equivalent, this is a finding.\n\nIf a site-defined title is used, it can in no case contravene or modify the language of the banner text required in WN10-SO-000075.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Failure to display the logon banner prior to a logon attempt will negate legal proceedings resulting from unauthorized access to system resources.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78171","V-63681","CCI-000048","CCI-001384","CCI-001385","CCI-001386","CCI-001387","CCI-001388"],"reference_identifier":"2862","uuid":"a27767bb-a3ad-40ff-bc17-7b406cddbc34","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F28379FFBD85E94EC34E38CFD56A4C18502584B5\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'The Windows dialog box title for the legal banner must be configured.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220923","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220923","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220923","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220923r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220923","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000085","rule_title":"Caching of logon credentials must be limited.","fix_text":"This is the default configuration for this setting (10 logons to cache).\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Interactive logon: Number of previous logons to cache (in case domain controller is not available)\" to \"10\" logons or less.\n\nThis setting only applies to domain-joined systems, however, it is configured by default on all systems.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is the default configuration for this setting (10 logons to cache).\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\\n\nValue Name:  CachedLogonsCount\n\nValue Type:  REG_SZ\nValue:  10 (or less)\n\nThis setting only applies to domain-joined systems, however, it is configured by default on all systems.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The default Windows configuration caches the last logon credentials for users who log on interactively to a system.  This feature is provided for system availability reasons, such as the user's machine being disconnected from the network or domain controllers being unavailable.  Even though the credential cache is well-protected, if a system is attacked, an unauthorized individual may isolate the password to a domain user account using a password-cracking program and gain access to the domain.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78177","V-63687","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6249","uuid":"98ea41f9-3a74-41ef-97fb-7a592abddd19","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4CA8B38DCD2BE82F996A4C44E84F13A2D17356DB\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Caching of logon credentials must be limited.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220924","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220924","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220924","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220924r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220924","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000095","rule_title":"The Smart Card removal option must be configured to Force Logoff or Lock Workstation.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Interactive logon: Smart card removal behavior\" to  \"Lock Workstation\" or \"Force Logoff\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\\n\nValue Name:  SCRemoveOption\n\nValue Type:  REG_SZ\nValue:  1 (Lock Workstation) or 2 (Force Logoff)\n\nThis can be left not configured or set to \"No action\" on workstations with the following conditions.  This must be documented with the ISSO.\n-The setting cannot be configured due to mission needs, or because it interferes with applications.\n-Policy must be in place that users manually lock workstations when leaving them unattended.\n-The screen saver is properly configured to lock as required.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unattended systems are susceptible to unauthorized use and must be locked.  Configuring a system to lock when a smart card is removed will ensure the system is inaccessible when unattended.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63697","SV-78187","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1791","uuid":"bc64e612-9b8d-4fc7-8a95-f2b0f7702aab","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BB17B6B60DE028EE63E0116E513A06BA9BA5821B\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Smart Card removal option must be configured to Force Logoff or Lock Workstation.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220925","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220925","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220925","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","rule_id_src":"SV-220925r958908_rule","rule_id":"SV-220925","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000100","rule_title":"The Windows SMB client must be configured to always perform SMB packet signing.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Microsoft network client: Digitally sign communications (always)\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanmanWorkstation\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: RequireSecuritySignature\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The server message block (SMB) protocol provides the basis for many network operations.  Digitally signed SMB packets aid in preventing man-in-the-middle attacks.  If this policy is enabled, the SMB client will only communicate with an SMB server that performs SMB packet signing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63703","SV-78193","CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"9223","uuid":"bc562f31-c13d-436f-ac07-26806837cc92","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7D4E8E83360A01FE74D572C4E8A48FD2E0E59D16\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Windows SMB client must be configured to always perform SMB packet signing.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220926","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220926","title":"SRG-OS-000074-GPOS-00042","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220926","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000074-GPOS-00042","rule_id_src":"SV-220926r987796_rule","rule_id":"SV-220926","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000110","rule_title":"Unencrypted passwords must not be sent to third-party SMB Servers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Microsoft network client: Send unencrypted password to third-party SMB servers\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanmanWorkstation\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  EnablePlainTextPassword\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some non-Microsoft SMB servers only support unencrypted (plain text) password authentication.  Sending plain text passwords across the network, when authenticating to an SMB server, reduces the overall security of the environment.  Check with the vendor of the SMB server to see if there is a way to support encrypted password authentication.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63711","SV-78201","CCI-000197"],"reference_identifier":"7897","uuid":"1e2465c5-3a90-4805-977c-61f44f14ceeb","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C0836D30769E3E8C4DA54053E585D00DE360F2D7\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Unencrypted passwords must not be sent to third-party SMB Servers.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220927","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220927","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220927","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","rule_id_src":"SV-220927r958908_rule","rule_id":"SV-220927","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000120","rule_title":"The Windows SMB server must be configured to always perform SMB packet signing.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Microsoft network server: Digitally sign communications (always)\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanManServer\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: RequireSecuritySignature\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The server message block (SMB) protocol provides the basis for many network operations.  Digitally signed SMB packets aid in preventing man-in-the-middle attacks.  If this policy is enabled, the SMB server will only communicate with an SMB client that performs SMB packet signing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78209","V-63719","CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"6765","uuid":"079d9c0a-3abe-47c6-ba1a-73344f3a6b51","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0C2AB470CFB15EF4B95F16877A8657DB97ADFBDD\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Windows SMB server must be configured to always perform SMB packet signing.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220928","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220928","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220928","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220928r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220928","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000140","rule_title":"Anonymous SID/Name translation must not be allowed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network access: Allow anonymous SID/Name translation\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Network access: Allow anonymous SID/Name translation\" is not set to \"Disabled\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing anonymous SID/Name translation can provide sensitive information for accessing a system.  Only authorized users must be able to perform such translations.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63739","SV-78229","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9200","uuid":"178d6ac2-77fa-4962-830b-cd8a28f00bb8","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DE4323A2AF41D410596A43684CD6C9EF904AD94F\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Anonymous SID/Name translation must not be allowed.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220929","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220929","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220929","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220929r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220929","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000145","rule_title":"Anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts must not be allowed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network access: Do not allow anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: RestrictAnonymousSAM\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts allows anonymous log on users (null session connections) to list all accounts names, thus providing a list of potential points to attack the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78235","V-63745","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5006","uuid":"82fa9628-f9c8-4dd5-adbb-6e16c95a936e","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 440BF631DAEE2DBD39A141A42A952658CD13D573\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts must not be allowed.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220930","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220930","title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220930","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","rule_id_src":"SV-220930r1137695_rule","rule_id":"SV-220930","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000150","rule_title":"Anonymous enumeration of shares must be restricted.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network access: Do not allow anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts and shares\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: RestrictAnonymous\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing anonymous logon users (null session connections) to list all account names and enumerate all shared resources can provide a map of potential points to attack the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63749","SV-78239","CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"4427","uuid":"2377cf52-3531-4d9f-b855-97167c195855","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-220931","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220931","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220931","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220931r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220931","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000160","rule_title":"The system must be configured to prevent anonymous users from having the same rights as the Everyone group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network access: Let Everyone permissions apply to anonymous users\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: EveryoneIncludesAnonymous\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Access by anonymous users must be restricted.  If this setting is enabled, then anonymous users have the same rights and permissions as the built-in Everyone group.  Anonymous users must not have these permissions or rights.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63755","SV-78245","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5680","uuid":"dcd4f88b-15ac-423b-9a0e-861ef7417b71","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 3233D4B25222A9FE96CBE62E3E48CEF707169CA6\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The system must be configured to prevent anonymous users from having the same rights as the Everyone group.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220932","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220932","title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220932","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","rule_id_src":"SV-220932r1137695_rule","rule_id":"SV-220932","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000165","rule_title":"Anonymous access to Named Pipes and Shares must be restricted.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network access: Restrict anonymous access to Named Pipes and Shares\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanManServer\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: RestrictNullSessAccess\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing anonymous access to named pipes or shares provides the potential for unauthorized system access.  This setting restricts access to those defined in \"Network access: Named Pipes that can be accessed anonymously\" and \"Network access: Shares that can be accessed anonymously\",  both of which must be blank under other requirements.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78249","V-63759","CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"2891","uuid":"43e0f9c5-1b72-463f-9d4e-04fa36fae82d","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: EB50C4E2F4102EDA0C0C3E075440F7226EC2E6A4\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Anonymous access to Named Pipes and Shares must be restricted.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220933","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220933","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220933","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-220933r1081053_rule","rule_id":"SV-220933","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000167","rule_title":"Remote calls to the Security Account Manager (SAM) must be restricted to Administrators.","fix_text":"Navigate to the policy Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network access: Restrict clients allowed to make remote calls to SAM\".\n\nSelect \"Edit Security\" to configure the \"Security descriptor:\".\n\nAdd \"Administrators\" in \"Group or user names:\" if it is not already listed (this is the default).\n\nSelect \"Administrators\" in \"Group or user names:\".\n\nSelect \"Allow\" for \"Remote Access\" in \"Permissions for \"Administrators\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nThe \"Security descriptor:\" must be populated with \"O:BAG:BAD:(A;;RC;;;BA) for the policy to be enforced.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Windows 10 v1507 LTSB version does not include this setting, it is NA for those systems.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: RestrictRemoteSAM\n\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: O:BAG:BAD:(A;;RC;;;BA)                                                   \n\nIf a domain application account such as for a management tool requires this user right, this is not a finding.\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\nThe requirement must be documented with the ISSO.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Windows SAM stores users' passwords. Restricting remote rpc connections to the SAM to Administrators helps protect those credentials.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-86393","V-71769","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"8024","uuid":"27f7c8ec-211d-473d-91f7-578a1f8ee7b8","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 16FD268DEBF75FDBBF6BCF6B86B1F30E3D8E2890\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Remote calls to the Security Account Manager (SAM) must be restricted to Administrators.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220934","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220934","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220934","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220934r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220934","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000180","rule_title":"NTLM must be prevented from falling back to a Null session.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: Allow LocalSystem NULL session fallback\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\LSA\\MSV1_0\\\n\nValue Name: allownullsessionfallback\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"NTLM sessions that are allowed to fall back to Null (unauthenticated) sessions may gain unauthorized access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63765","SV-78255","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8469","uuid":"65b75c07-5c74-44e3-98e1-b32681fd46a7","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 940D3156AEB2174F2AC6C58BD2325616ACEF00C7\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'NTLM must be prevented from falling back to a Null session.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220935","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220935","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220935","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220935r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220935","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000185","rule_title":"PKU2U authentication using online identities must be prevented.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: Allow PKU2U authentication requests to this computer to use online identities\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\LSA\\pku2u\\\n\nValue Name: AllowOnlineID\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"PKU2U is a peer-to-peer authentication protocol.   This setting prevents online identities from authenticating to domain-joined systems.  Authentication will be centrally managed with Windows user accounts.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78257","V-63767","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6350","uuid":"cafbbdb2-e65a-4261-88d4-9504938322c6","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6B5EE9C35C7FAE0276897F53BF61DC93B20702DB\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'PKU2U authentication using online identities must be prevented.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220936","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220936","title":"SRG-OS-000120-GPOS-00061","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220936","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000120-GPOS-00061","rule_id_src":"SV-220936r971535_rule","rule_id":"SV-220936","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000190","rule_title":"Kerberos encryption types must be configured to prevent the use of DES and RC4 encryption suites.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: Configure encryption types allowed for Kerberos\" to \"Enabled\" with only the following selected:\n\nAES128_HMAC_SHA1\nAES256_HMAC_SHA1\nFuture encryption types","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\Kerberos\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: SupportedEncryptionTypes\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x7ffffff8 (2147483640)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Certain encryption types are no longer considered secure.  This setting configures a minimum encryption type for Kerberos, preventing the use of the DES and RC4 encryption suites.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78285","V-63795","CCI-000803"],"reference_identifier":"3824","uuid":"2de9018a-d27b-42a0-8746-a21c0db761a5","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: AA0BC667865149F4D563672B09BE43AA20261366\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Kerberos encryption types must be configured to prevent the use of DES and RC4 encryption suites.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220937","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220937","title":"SRG-OS-000073-GPOS-00041","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220937","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000073-GPOS-00041","rule_id_src":"SV-220937r1051034_rule","rule_id":"SV-220937","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000195","rule_title":"The system must be configured to prevent the storage of the LAN Manager hash of passwords.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: Do not store LAN Manager hash value on next password change\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: NoLMHash\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The LAN Manager hash uses a weak encryption algorithm and there are several tools available that use this hash to retrieve account passwords. This setting controls whether or not a LAN Manager hash of the password is stored in the SAM the next time the password is changed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78287","V-63797","CCI-004062","CCI-000196"],"reference_identifier":"7025","uuid":"b12f88da-8c2a-44f2-9e80-ec076c98d1fc","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 42A63ECDEB3C1268456B9D203739EA1B4C02E17B\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must be configured to prevent the storage of the LAN Manager hash of passwords.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220938","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220938","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220938","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220938r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220938","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000205","rule_title":"The LanMan authentication level must be set to send NTLMv2 response only, and to refuse LM and NTLM.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: LAN Manager authentication level\" to \"Send NTLMv2 response only. Refuse LM & NTLM\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: LmCompatibilityLevel\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 5","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Kerberos v5 authentication protocol is the default for authentication of users who are logging on to domain accounts.  NTLM, which is less secure, is retained in later Windows versions  for compatibility with clients and servers that are running earlier versions of Windows or applications that still use it.  It is also used to authenticate logons to stand-alone computers that are running later versions.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78291","V-63801","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5785","uuid":"38862dfa-bf0d-40ad-9c79-dc9bc7ebcf2f","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B9B262A26FCEA99752677E1C02DEAE8BE8A77171\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The LanMan authentication level must be set to send NTLMv2 response only, and to refuse LM and NTLM.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220939","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220939","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220939","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220939r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220939","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000210","rule_title":"The system must be configured to the required LDAP client signing level.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: LDAP client signing requirements\" to \"Negotiate signing\" at a minimum.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LDAP\\\n\nValue Name: LDAPClientIntegrity\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting controls the signing requirements for LDAP clients.  This setting must be set to Negotiate signing or Require signing, depending on the environment and type of LDAP server in use.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78293","V-63803","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9948","uuid":"e1e52fb5-bdfd-4d83-a322-95e1dd0cf4e7","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 417D6FA65B64F61D407C8F2F91CA9C24E86E0479\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must be configured to the required LDAP client signing level.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220940","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220940","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220940","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220940r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220940","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000215","rule_title":"The system must be configured to meet the minimum session security requirement for NTLM SSP based clients.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: Minimum session security for NTLM SSP based (including secure RPC) clients\" to \"Require NTLMv2 session security\" and \"Require 128-bit encryption\" (all options selected).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\MSV1_0\\\n\nValue Name: NTLMMinClientSec\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x20080000 (537395200)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Microsoft has implemented a variety of security support providers for use with RPC sessions.  All of the options must be enabled to ensure the maximum security level.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63805","SV-78295","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3620","uuid":"328af064-8f8e-4aff-a1f2-28d5c3e6b6c0","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4FF100513B81B5B6AB094DE846AF0038F66A57D3\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The system must be configured to meet the minimum session security requirement for NTLM SSP based clients.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220941","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220941","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220941","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220941r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220941","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000220","rule_title":"The system must be configured to meet the minimum session security requirement for NTLM SSP based servers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: Minimum session security for NTLM SSP based (including secure RPC) servers\" to \"Require NTLMv2 session security\" and \"Require 128-bit encryption\" (all options selected).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\MSV1_0\\\n\nValue Name: NTLMMinServerSec\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x20080000 (537395200)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Microsoft has implemented a variety of security support providers for use with RPC sessions.  All of the options must be enabled to ensure the maximum security level.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78297","V-63807","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9027","uuid":"a2035260-49c5-438a-8dd8-c8edfdeb2eba","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BA87D1357DBF546A04E1A2481F636A8AC6EB5C1C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The system must be configured to meet the minimum session security requirement for NTLM SSP based servers.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220942","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220942","title":"SRG-OS-000478-GPOS-00223","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220942","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000478-GPOS-00223","rule_id_src":"SV-220942r1137699_rule","rule_id":"SV-220942","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000230","rule_title":"The system must be configured to use FIPS-compliant algorithms for encryption, hashing, and signing.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"System cryptography: Use FIPS compliant algorithms for encryption, hashing, and signing\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\FIPSAlgorithmPolicy\\\n\nValue Name: Enabled\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n \nWarning: Clients with this setting enabled will not be able to communicate via digitally encrypted or signed protocols with servers that do not support these algorithms.  Both the browser and web server must be configured to use TLS otherwise the browser will not be able to connect to a secure site.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting ensures that the system uses algorithms that are FIPS-compliant for encryption, hashing, and signing.  FIPS-compliant algorithms meet specific standards established by the U.S. Government and must be the algorithms used for all OS encryption functions.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63811","SV-78301","CCI-002450"],"reference_identifier":"2003","uuid":"46c0f417-1d82-45d3-94f9-6ba817fd6fb0","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B6217D122C88174F1325C1005928C7BB295C7FD7\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'The system must be configured to use FIPS-compliant algorithms for encryption, hashing, and signing.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220943","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220943","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220943","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220943r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220943","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000240","rule_title":"The default permissions of global system objects must be increased.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"System objects: Strengthen default permissions of internal system objects (e.g. Symbolic links)\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Session Manager\\\n\nValue Name: ProtectionMode\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows systems maintain a global list of shared system resources such as DOS device names, mutexes, and semaphores. Each type of object is created with a default DACL that specifies who can access the objects with what permissions. If this policy is enabled, the default DACL is stronger, allowing non-admin users to read shared objects, but not modify shared objects that they did not create.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78305","V-63815","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2908","uuid":"4781afd2-538b-464a-a1d8-19839306a95c","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 104411E2E388A5E6AE83264539D8148743DE6FA6\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The default permissions of global system objects must be increased.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220944","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220944","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220944","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","rule_id_src":"SV-220944r1051035_rule","rule_id":"SV-220944","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000245","rule_title":"User Account Control approval mode for the built-in Administrator must be enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"User Account Control: Admin Approval Mode for the Built-in Administrator account\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: FilterAdministratorToken\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"User Account Control (UAC) is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized. This setting configures the built-in Administrator account so that it runs in Admin Approval Mode.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63817","SV-78307","CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"1464","uuid":"4c0cc230-75e1-48bc-b4b3-10e0777b4824","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FAA4201BF8AECCC1E849DFBF3C0D39EFCDC0C212\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'User Account Control approval mode for the built-in Administrator must be enabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220945","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220945","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220945","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","rule_id_src":"SV-220945r958518_rule","rule_id":"SV-220945","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000250","rule_title":"User Account Control must, at minimum, prompt administrators for consent on the secure desktop.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"User Account Control: Behavior of the elevation prompt for administrators in Admin Approval Mode\" to \"Prompt for consent on the secure desktop\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: ConsentPromptBehaviorAdmin\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 2 (Prompt for consent on the secure desktop)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"User Account Control (UAC) is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized.  This setting configures the elevation requirements for logged on administrators to complete a task that requires raised privileges.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63819","SV-78309","CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"8332","uuid":"7b29b8d8-7c75-4b48-bd65-45f09870004e","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2B4996C4AEDB1695C1B2F04E860E529157CD2E32\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'User Account Control must, at minimum, prompt administrators for consent on the secure desktop.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220946","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220946","title":"SRG-OS-000105-GPOS-00052","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220946","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000105-GPOS-00052","rule_id_src":"SV-220946r1153410_rule","rule_id":"SV-220946","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000251","rule_title":"Windows 10 must use multifactor authentication for local and network access to privileged and nonprivileged accounts.","fix_text":"For nondomain-joined systems, configuring Windows Hello for sign-on options is suggested based on the organization's needs and capabilities.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is not a member of a domain, this is Not Applicable.\n\nIf all of the following settings exist and are populated, this is not a finding.\n\nComputer\\HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Cryptography\\Calais\\Readers\nComputer\\HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Cryptography\\Calais\\SmartCards","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without the use of multifactor authentication, the ease of access to privileged and nonprivileged functions is greatly increased. \n\nAll domain accounts must be enabled for multifactor authentication with the exception of local emergency accounts. \n\nMultifactor authentication requires using two or more factors to achieve authentication.\n\nFactors include: \n\n1) Something a user knows (e.g., password/PIN);\n2) Something a user has (e.g., cryptographic identification device, token); and\n3) Something a user is (e.g., biometric).\n\nA privileged account is defined as an information system account with authorizations of a privileged user.\n\nNetwork access is defined as access to an information system by a user (or a process acting on behalf of a user) communicating through a network (e.g., local area network, wide area network, or the internet).\n\nLocal access is defined as access to an organizational information system by a user (or process acting on behalf of a user) communicating through a direct connection without the use of a network.\n\nThe DOD CAC with DOD-approved PKI is an example of multifactor authentication.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000106-GPOS-00053, SRG-OS-000107-GPOS-00054, SRG-OS-000108-GPOS-00055","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-111577","V-102627","CCI-000765"],"reference_identifier":"3474","uuid":"83f2869a-d991-4062-8f93-7da163b1f6f1","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 152952A04BAB375E654092BF44E7ADEB600A5635\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows 10 must use multifactor authentication for local and network access to privileged and nonprivileged accounts.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220947","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220947","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220947","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","rule_id_src":"SV-220947r1051036_rule","rule_id":"SV-220947","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000255","rule_title":"User Account Control must automatically deny elevation requests for standard users.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"User Account Control: Behavior of the elevation prompt for standard users\" to \"Automatically deny elevation requests\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: ConsentPromptBehaviorUser\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"User Account Control (UAC) is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized. Denying elevation requests from standard user accounts requires tasks that need elevation to be initiated by accounts with administrative privileges. This ensures correct accounts are used on the system for privileged tasks to help mitigate credential theft.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78311","V-63821","CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"6033","uuid":"d20645b1-90ef-4737-a499-1bee3f125145","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: CF309ABFB0EBCF20929B5D50F0A9A5BCAA00C7B6\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'User Account Control must automatically deny elevation requests for standard users.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220948","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220948","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220948","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","rule_id_src":"SV-220948r958518_rule","rule_id":"SV-220948","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000260","rule_title":"User Account Control must be configured to detect application installations and prompt for elevation.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"User Account Control: Detect application installations and prompt for elevation\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableInstallerDetection\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"User Account Control (UAC) is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized.  This setting requires Windows to respond to application installation requests by prompting for credentials.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78315","V-63825","CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"4641","uuid":"2dd2b1fe-a405-4c17-ab5d-313d02726bb9","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 51E27CEE42DE346D5A3B0CFC2E3FC4E3B0B31699\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'User Account Control must be configured to detect application installations and prompt for elevation.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220949","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220949","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220949","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","rule_id_src":"SV-220949r958518_rule","rule_id":"SV-220949","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000265","rule_title":"User Account Control must only elevate UIAccess applications that are installed in secure locations.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"User Account Control: Only elevate UIAccess applications that are installed in secure locations\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableSecureUIAPaths\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"User Account Control (UAC) is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized.  This setting configures Windows to only allow applications installed in a secure location on the file system, such as the Program Files or the Windows\\System32 folders, to run with elevated privileges.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63827","SV-78317","CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"9200","uuid":"bad1c670-b0af-4249-a5a0-13024ad0318b","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F697BF09EC71E94909EF6D90C493BEB3A58128A9\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'User Account Control must only elevate UIAccess applications that are installed in secure locations.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220950","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220950","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220950","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","rule_id_src":"SV-220950r1051037_rule","rule_id":"SV-220950","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000270","rule_title":"User Account Control must run all administrators in Admin Approval Mode, enabling UAC.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"User Account Control: Run all administrators in Admin Approval Mode\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableLUA\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"User Account Control (UAC) is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized. This setting enables UAC.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78319","V-63829","CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"7927","uuid":"7a300e87-d812-4806-8175-a070cd5fd48e","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2A769A45A3290FB2833710B61A5773E26A9E1829\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'User Account Control must run all administrators in Admin Approval Mode, enabling UAC.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220951","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220951","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220951","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","rule_id_src":"SV-220951r958518_rule","rule_id":"SV-220951","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000275","rule_title":"User Account Control must virtualize file and registry write failures to per-user locations.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"User Account Control: Virtualize file and registry write failures to per-user locations\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableVirtualization\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"User Account Control (UAC) is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized.  This setting configures non-UAC compliant applications to run in virtualized file and registry entries in per-user locations, allowing them to run.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78321","V-63831","CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"4345","uuid":"59123845-0a6a-4ab8-92a3-296d89acd179","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D0190A70F035101505AAE411C32E42FD9D25602D\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'User Account Control must virtualize file and registry write failures to per-user locations.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220952","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220952","title":"SRG-OS-000076-GPOS-00044","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220952","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000076-GPOS-00044","rule_id_src":"SV-220952r1051038_rule","rule_id":"SV-220952","rule_version":"WN10-SO-000280","rule_title":"Passwords for enabled local Administrator accounts must be changed at least every 60 days.","fix_text":"Change the enabled local Administrator account password at least every 60 days. Windows LAPS must be used to change the built-in Administrator account password. Domain-joined systems can configure this to occur more frequently. LAPS will change the password every 30 days by default. \n\nMore information is available at:\nhttps://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/windows-it-pro-blog/by-popular-demand-windows-laps-available-now/ba-p/3788747\nhttps://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows-server/identity/laps/laps-overview#windows-laps-supported-platforms-and-azure-ad-laps-preview-status","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If there are no enabled local Administrator accounts, this is Not Applicable.\n\nReview the password last set date for the enabled local Administrator account.\n\nOn the standalone or domain-joined workstation:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\".\n\nEnter \"Get-LocalUser -Name * | Select-Object *\".\n\nIf the \"PasswordLastSet\" date is greater than \"60\" days old for the local Administrator account for administering the computer/domain, this is a finding.\n\nVerify LAPS is configured and operational. \n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> LAPS >> Password Settings >> Set to enabled. Password Complexity, large letters + small letters + numbers + special, Password Length 14, Password Age 60. If not configured as shown, this is a finding. \n\nVerify LAPS Operational logs >> Event Viewer >> Applications and Services Logs >> Microsoft >> Windows >> LAPS >> Operational. Verify LAPS policy process is completing. If it is not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The longer a password is in use, the greater the opportunity for someone to gain unauthorized knowledge of the password. A local Administrator account is not generally used and its password may not be changed as frequently as necessary. Changing the password for enabled Administrator accounts on a regular basis will limit its exposure.\n\nWindows LAPS must be used to change the built-in Administrator account password.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-004066","CCI-000199"],"reference_identifier":"8663","uuid":"d2319ecf-15e1-4336-910c-49b95a729910","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 19E46C131C33B753D4608831FED0A78610423266\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Passwords for enabled local Administrator accounts must be changed at least every 60 days.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220954","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220954","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220954","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-220954r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-220954","rule_version":"WN10-UC-000015","rule_title":"Toast notifications to the lock screen must be turned off.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Start Menu and Taskbar >> Notifications >> \"Turn off toast notifications on the lock screen\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\PushNotifications\\\n\nValue Name: NoToastApplicationNotificationOnLockScreen\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Toast notifications that are displayed on the lock screen could display sensitive information to unauthorized personnel.  Turning off this feature will limit access to the information to a logged on user.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63839","SV-78329","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"7498","uuid":"344f27ad-d34f-4a7b-a2ba-a7743551a074","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F743D097249B74AF517501ECA7A03E2CCDFE5719\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Toast notifications to the lock screen must be turned off.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220955","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220955","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220955","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-220955r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-220955","rule_version":"WN10-UC-000020","rule_title":"Zone information must be preserved when saving attachments.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for Windows to mark file attachments with their zone information.\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Attachment Manager >> \"Do not preserve zone information in file attachments\" to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for Windows to mark file attachments with their zone information.\n\nIf the registry Value Name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"2\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Attachments\\\n\nValue Name: SaveZoneInformation\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000002 (2) (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Preserving zone of origin (internet, intranet, local, restricted) information on file attachments allows Windows to determine risk.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63841","SV-78331","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1631","uuid":"0c6b78e5-c510-4ef7-abb2-54853ae1d4f1","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E6A985F87E43A85FD736DE012BF8951FA39904FD\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Zone information must be preserved when saving attachments.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220956","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220956","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220956","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-220956r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-220956","rule_version":"WN10-UR-000005","rule_title":"The Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller\" to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts are granted the \"Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller\" user right, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller\" user right may be able to retrieve the credentials of other accounts from Credential Manager.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63843","SV-78333","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"7841","uuid":"133e7cb2-c16d-44fe-8859-a5ebca72a64f","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DAC193802254E3FFF73928618764744EEAAA14E8\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220957","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220957","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220957","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-220957r1137691_rule","rule_id":"SV-220957","rule_version":"WN10-UR-000010","rule_title":"The Access this computer from the network user right must only be assigned to the Administrators and Remote Desktop Users groups.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Access this computer from the network\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators   \nRemote Desktop Users","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Access this computer from the network\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\nRemote Desktop Users\n\nIf a domain application account such as for a management tool requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nThe application account, managed at the domain level, must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length and frequency of changes as defined in the Windows server STIGs.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Access this computer from the network\" user right may access resources on the system, and must be limited to those that require it.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78335","V-63845","CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"6932","uuid":"212f8d1d-db27-41d8-b97a-8ff8ae96f6ee","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7DB3BEA8E9A7BDB847D57A4916D8CAE784607855\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Access this computer from the network user right must only be assigned to the Administrators and Remote Desktop Users groups.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220958","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220958","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220958","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-220958r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-220958","rule_version":"WN10-UR-000015","rule_title":"The Act as part of the operating system user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Act as part of the operating system\" to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts (to include administrators), are granted the \"Act as part of the operating system\" user right, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Act as part of the operating system\" user right can assume the identity of any user and gain access to resources that user is authorized to access.  Any accounts with this right can take complete control of a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78337","V-63847","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"6830","uuid":"79b26bc6-e9a5-46dc-a6ab-dabdb62bc195","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8851888430B300CDDFFA015B14F63AA31C95BC63\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Act as part of the operating system user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220959","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220959","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220959","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-220959r1137691_rule","rule_id":"SV-220959","rule_version":"WN10-UR-000025","rule_title":"The Allow log on locally user right must only be assigned to the Administrators and Users groups.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Allow log on locally\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators\nUsers","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Allow log on locally\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\nUsers","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Allow log on locally\" user right can log on interactively to a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63851","SV-78341","CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"9936","uuid":"6a9e2f91-a765-433b-ab8e-8142a13b5245","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-220960","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220960","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220960","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-220960r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-220960","rule_version":"WN10-UR-000030","rule_title":"The Back up files and directories user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Back up files and directories\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Back up files and directories\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Back up files and directories\" user right can circumvent file and directory permissions and could allow access to sensitive data.\"","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63853","SV-78343","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"2647","uuid":"8236908c-e0da-4133-be94-813120148932","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0335DBFD0CC789D2E3DB17AA7B46B1B3DA7E0876\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Back up files and directories user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220961","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220961","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220961","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-220961r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-220961","rule_version":"WN10-UR-000035","rule_title":"The Change the system time user right must only be assigned to Administrators and Local Service and NT SERVICE\\autotimesvc.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Change the system time\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators\nLOCAL SERVICE\nNT SERVICE\\autotimesvc is added in v1909 cumulative update.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Change the system time\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\nLOCAL SERVICE\nNT SERVICE\\autotimesvc is added in v1909 cumulative update.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Change the system time\" user right can change the system time, which can impact authentication, as well as affect time stamps on event log entries.\n\nThe NT SERVICE\\autotimesvc is added in v1909 cumulative update.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63855","SV-78345","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"2785","uuid":"4c851968-a710-421b-ac60-ac0596e15d68","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-220962","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220962","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220962","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-220962r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-220962","rule_version":"WN10-UR-000040","rule_title":"The Create a pagefile user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Create a pagefile\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Create a pagefile\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Create a pagefile\" user right can change the size of a pagefile, which could affect system performance.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78347","V-63857","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"6415","uuid":"a6837e21-1d96-4e14-9ca0-2090a243a7c5","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D9D02C328F42BCBAB5CE15308ABD06F7CD6D74F5\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Create a pagefile user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220963","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220963","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220963","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-220963r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-220963","rule_version":"WN10-UR-000045","rule_title":"The Create a token object user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Create a token object\" to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts are granted the \"Create a token object\" user right, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Create a token object\" user right allows a process to create an access token. This could be used to provide elevated rights and compromise a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63859","SV-78349","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"8489","uuid":"b05d5086-5d08-4071-8aea-35fb0aef2c94","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 55BA6EF1E3151DF7FE5F0153DD2BF3A13202042C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Create a token object user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220964","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220964","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220964","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-220964r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-220964","rule_version":"WN10-UR-000050","rule_title":"The Create global objects user right must only be assigned to Administrators, Service, Local Service, and Network Service.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Create global objects\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators\nLOCAL SERVICE\nNETWORK SERVICE\nSERVICE","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Create global objects\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\nLOCAL SERVICE\nNETWORK SERVICE\nSERVICE","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Create global objects\" user right can create objects that are available to all sessions, which could affect processes in other users' sessions.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63861","SV-78351","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"5758","uuid":"a882440c-203a-49a2-b6f5-ea01700e0c82","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 49A45EF7CC3F37E542DA3AD4EBF8C48DEE8CCD42\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Create global objects user right must only be assigned to Administrators, Service, Local Service, and Network Service.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220965","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220965","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220965","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-220965r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-220965","rule_version":"WN10-UR-000055","rule_title":"The Create permanent shared objects user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Create permanent shared objects\" to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts are granted the \"Create permanent shared objects\" user right, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Create permanent shared objects\" user right could expose sensitive data by creating shared objects.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63863","SV-78353","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"9791","uuid":"7fd4ca1d-90e2-4cc2-9ff1-854369e0214d","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 60E6EA39E15FD9E984ECCAC3DFB05EB0CCD6EC16\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Create permanent shared objects user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220966","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220966","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220966","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-220966r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-220966","rule_version":"WN10-UR-000060","rule_title":"The Create symbolic links user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Create symbolic links\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Create symbolic links\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\n\nIf the workstation has an approved use of Hyper-V, such as being used as a dedicated admin workstation using Hyper-V to separate administration and standard user functions, \"NT VIRTUAL MACHINES\\VIRTUAL MACHINE\" may be assigned this user right and is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Create symbolic links\" user right can create pointers to other objects, which could potentially expose the system to attack.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78355","V-63865","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"3598","uuid":"330958e6-9836-4b22-916a-ad8a36d5124b","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6C676F898A0ADBBC3DDA3BB9621EBA75A288442D\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Create symbolic links user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220967","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220967","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220967","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-220967r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-220967","rule_version":"WN10-UR-000065","rule_title":"The Debug programs user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Debug programs\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Debug Programs\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Debug Programs\" user right can attach a debugger to any process or to the kernel, providing complete access to sensitive and critical operating system components.  This right is given to Administrators in the default configuration.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63869","SV-78359","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"7093","uuid":"1128a5f2-8c9d-483a-adf4-1fcc46a796bd","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0F423F951E5EF62142B207579068C47831506440\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Debug programs user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220968","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220968","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220968","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-220968r1137691_rule","rule_id":"SV-220968","rule_version":"WN10-UR-000070","rule_title":"The Deny access to this computer from the network user right on workstations must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts and local accounts on domain systems and unauthenticated access on all systems.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Deny access to this computer from the network\" to include the following.\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nEnterprise Admins group\nDomain Admins group\nLocal account (see Note below)\n\nAll Systems:\nGuests group\n\nPrivileged Access Workstations (PAWs) dedicated to the management of Active Directory are exempt from denying the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups. (See the Windows Privileged Access Workstation STIG for PAW requirements.)\n\nNote: \"Local account\" is a built-in security group used to assign user rights and permissions to all local accounts.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following groups or accounts are not defined for the \"Deny access to this computer from the network\" right, this is a finding:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nEnterprise Admins group\nDomain Admins group\nLocal account (see Note below)\n\nAll Systems:\nGuests group\n\nPrivileged Access Workstations (PAWs) dedicated to the management of Active Directory are exempt from denying the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups. (See the Windows Privileged Access Workstation STIG for PAW requirements.)\n\nNote: \"Local account\" is a built-in security group used to assign user rights and permissions to all local accounts.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny access to this computer from the network\" right defines the accounts that are prevented from logging on from the network.\n\nIn an Active Directory Domain, denying logons to the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups on lower trust systems helps mitigate the risk of privilege escalation from credential theft attacks, which could lead to the compromise of an entire domain.\n\nLocal accounts on domain-joined systems must also be assigned this right to decrease the risk of lateral movement resulting from credential theft attacks.\n\nThe Guests group must be assigned this right to prevent unauthenticated access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63871","SV-78361","CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"3998","uuid":"5c730685-43af-4659-bd64-a042cfd15d4e","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FDE91E0CE28BB65A52238759BF3855CAD0EFDE85\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Deny access to this computer from the network user right on workstations must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts and local accounts on domain systems and unauthenticated access on all systems.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220969","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220969","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220969","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-220969r1137691_rule","rule_id":"SV-220969","rule_version":"WN10-UR-000075","rule_title":"The \"Deny log on as a batch job\" user right on domain-joined workstations must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts.","fix_text":"This requirement is applicable to domain-joined systems. For standalone or nondomain-joined systems, this is NA.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Deny log on as a batch job\" to include the following:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nEnterprise Admin Group\nDomain Admin Group","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This requirement is applicable to domain-joined systems. For standalone or nondomain-joined systems, this is NA.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following groups or accounts are not defined for the \"Deny log on as a batch job\" right, this is a finding.\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nEnterprise Admin Group\nDomain Admin Group","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny log on as a batch job\" right defines accounts that are prevented from logging on to the system as a batch job, such as Task Scheduler.\n\nIn an Active Directory Domain, denying logons to the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups on lower-trust systems helps mitigate the risk of privilege escalation from credential theft attacks that could lead to the compromise of an entire domain.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78363","V-63873","CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"9044","uuid":"7b05bffa-73c2-4418-908d-2c804bf35d23","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E7CDB4CB614E3357D0C4CC3FC0FBE1D788345C20\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The \"Deny log on as a batch job\" user right on domain-joined workstations must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220970","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220970","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220970","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-220970r1137691_rule","rule_id":"SV-220970","rule_version":"WN10-UR-000080","rule_title":"The Deny log on as a service user right on Windows 10 domain-joined workstations must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts.","fix_text":"This requirement is applicable to domain-joined systems. For standalone or nondomain-joined systems, this is NA.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Deny log on as a service\" to include the following:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nEnterprise Admins Group\nDomain Admins Group","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This requirement is applicable to domain-joined systems. For standalone or nondomain-joined systems, this is NA.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following groups or accounts are not defined for the \"Deny log on as a service\" right , this is a finding.\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nEnterprise Admins Group\nDomain Admins Group","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny log on as a service\" right defines accounts that are denied log on as a service.\n\nIn an Active Directory Domain, denying logons to the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups on lower trust systems helps mitigate the risk of privilege escalation from credential theft attacks which could lead to the compromise of an entire domain.\n\nIncorrect configurations could prevent services from starting and result in a DoS.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63875","SV-78365","CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"6342","uuid":"85b8623a-de2d-41e4-a82c-d53d8774d571","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5332ABB03068C5EC1CB4A50779E85D672165753F\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Deny log on as a service user right on Windows 10 domain-joined workstations must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220971","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220971","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220971","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-220971r1137691_rule","rule_id":"SV-220971","rule_version":"WN10-UR-000085","rule_title":"The Deny log on locally user right on workstations must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts on domain systems and unauthenticated access on all systems.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Deny log on locally\" to include the following.\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nEnterprise Admins Group\nDomain Admins Group\n\nPrivileged Access Workstations (PAWs) dedicated to the management of Active Directory are exempt from denying the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups. (See the Windows Privileged Access Workstation STIG for PAW requirements.)\n\nAll Systems:\nGuests Group","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following groups or accounts are not defined for the \"Deny log on locally\" right, this is a finding.\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nEnterprise Admins Group\nDomain Admins Group\n\nPrivileged Access Workstations (PAWs) dedicated to the management of Active Directory are exempt from denying the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups. (See the Windows Privileged Access Workstation STIG for PAW requirements.)\n\nAll Systems:\nGuests Group","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny log on locally\" right defines accounts that are prevented from logging on interactively.\n\nIn an Active Directory Domain, denying logons to the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups on lower trust systems helps mitigate the risk of privilege escalation from credential theft attacks, which could lead to the compromise of an entire domain.\n\nThe Guests group must be assigned this right to prevent unauthenticated access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63877","SV-78367","CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"2185","uuid":"3205d421-c830-4ed5-9edc-0954c23d3a4c","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 67E10C0D5B85B2BF7F0DE524BC9F9244180D8100\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Deny log on locally user right on workstations must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts on domain systems and unauthenticated access on all systems.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220972","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220972","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220972","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-220972r1137691_rule","rule_id":"SV-220972","rule_version":"WN10-UR-000090","rule_title":"The Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services user right on Windows 10 workstations must at a minimum be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts and local accounts on domain systems and unauthenticated access on all systems.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services\" to include the following.\n\nIf Remote Desktop Services is not used by the organization, assign the Everyone group this right to prevent all access.\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nEnterprise Admins group\nDomain Admins group\nLocal account (see Note below)\n\nAll Systems:\nGuests group\n\nPrivileged Access Workstations (PAWs) dedicated to the management of Active Directory are exempt from denying the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups. (See the Windows Privileged Access Workstation STIG for PAW requirements.)\n\nNote: \"Local account\" is a built-in security group used to assign user rights and permissions to all local accounts.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following groups or accounts are not defined for the \"Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services\" right, this is a finding:\n\nIf Remote Desktop Services is not used by the organization, the \"Everyone\" group can replace all of the groups listed below.\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nEnterprise Admins group\nDomain Admins group\nLocal account (see Note below)\n\nAll Systems:\nGuests group\n\nPrivileged Access Workstations (PAWs) dedicated to the management of Active Directory are exempt from denying the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups. (See the Windows Privileged Access Workstation STIG for PAW requirements.)\n\nNote: \"Local account\" is a built-in security group used to assign user rights and permissions to all local accounts.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services\" right defines the accounts that are prevented from logging on using Remote Desktop Services.\n\nIf Remote Desktop Services is not used by the organization, the Everyone group must be assigned this right to prevent all access.\n\nIn an Active Directory Domain, denying logons to the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups on lower trust systems helps mitigate the risk of privilege escalation from credential theft attacks, which could lead to the compromise of an entire domain.\n\nLocal accounts on domain-joined systems must also be assigned this right to decrease the risk of lateral movement resulting from credential theft attacks.\n\nThe Guests group must be assigned this right to prevent unauthenticated access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63879","SV-78369","CCI-000213","CCI-002314"],"reference_identifier":"6576","uuid":"944fb747-b5d9-4217-9f31-cf365b763da9","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-220973","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220973","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220973","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-220973r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-220973","rule_version":"WN10-UR-000095","rule_title":"The Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation\" to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts are granted the \"Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation\" user right, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation\" user right allows the \"Trusted for Delegation\" setting to be changed. This could potentially allow unauthorized users to impersonate other users.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63881","SV-78371","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"1521","uuid":"de88b17a-2dfe-445f-8a65-37b16cf3fc04","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A6E2B82F504BE647FD51FC09E16E1E52F7BFF515\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220974","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220974","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220974","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-220974r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-220974","rule_version":"WN10-UR-000100","rule_title":"The Force shutdown from a remote system user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Force shutdown from a remote system\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Force shutdown from a remote system\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Force shutdown from a remote system\" user right can remotely shut down a system which could result in a DoS.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78373","V-63883","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"5735","uuid":"d99a7d53-d469-43aa-ab61-3fb23ee89627","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 06BCB1424C308316CFF1F06D3C6FDEB65020A23C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Force shutdown from a remote system user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220975","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220975","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220975","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-220975r1138519_rule","rule_id":"SV-220975","rule_version":"WN10-UR-000110","rule_title":"The \"Impersonate a client after authentication\" user right must only be assigned to Administrators, Service, Local Service, and Network Service.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Impersonate a client after authentication\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators\nLOCAL SERVICE\nNETWORK SERVICE\nSERVICE","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Impersonate a client after authentication\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\nLOCAL SERVICE\nNETWORK SERVICE\nSERVICE","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Impersonate a client after authentication\" user right allows a program to impersonate another user or account to run on their behalf. An attacker could potentially use this to elevate privileges.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"9691","uuid":"ebb83900-35ab-4696-9085-fb62ed79e008","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 461BBFAB7D544F0519F31AC713A96BE988D97F28\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The \"Impersonate a client after authentication\" user right must only be assigned to Administrators, Service, Local Service, and Network Service.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220976","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220976","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220976","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-220976r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-220976","rule_version":"WN10-UR-000120","rule_title":"The Load and unload device drivers user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Load and unload device drivers\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Load and unload device drivers\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Load and unload device drivers\" user right allows device drivers to dynamically be loaded on a system by a user. This could potentially be used to install malicious code by an attacker.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78407","V-63917","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"3131","uuid":"fecc818d-d15c-46c1-93aa-a3020b321bfb","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: CEB1E6773A1DF23A83EE8F6DBC9F1F7F757C55EC\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Load and unload device drivers user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220977","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220977","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220977","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-220977r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-220977","rule_version":"WN10-UR-000125","rule_title":"The Lock pages in memory user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Lock pages in memory\" to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts are granted the \"Lock pages in memory\" user right, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Lock pages in memory\" user right allows physical memory to be assigned to processes, which could cause performance issues or a DoS.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63925","SV-78415","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"6610","uuid":"6dd1ccc3-dd28-4556-b735-56ae0c587854","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9954C16EDF6C79D806F1C5B93A4F83564A97CA66\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Lock pages in memory user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220978","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220978","title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220978","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","rule_id_src":"SV-220978r958434_rule","rule_id":"SV-220978","rule_version":"WN10-UR-000130","rule_title":"The Manage auditing and security log user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Manage auditing and security log\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Manage auditing and security log\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\n\nIf the organization has an \"Auditors\" group the assignment of this group to the user right would not be a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Manage auditing and security log\" user right can manage the security log and change auditing configurations. This could be used to clear evidence of tampering.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78417","V-63927","CCI-000162","CCI-000163","CCI-000164","CCI-000171","CCI-001914"],"reference_identifier":"3318","uuid":"47a4beda-4937-493d-b7a6-8d5547ee58b3","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 67A3FB62300CB1EE24A4870D3D78C5FADC3F935C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Manage auditing and security log user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220979","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220979","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220979","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-220979r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-220979","rule_version":"WN10-UR-000140","rule_title":"The Modify firmware environment values user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Modify firmware environment values\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Modify firmware environment values\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Modify firmware environment values\" user right can change hardware configuration environment variables. This could result in hardware failures or a DoS.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63931","SV-78421","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"3988","uuid":"7d41c005-04e6-4025-ba73-e06603e8f693","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 52553DDC7604E937C0D5D6F35F0324CD65D631FB\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Modify firmware environment values user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220980","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220980","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220980","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-220980r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-220980","rule_version":"WN10-UR-000145","rule_title":"The Perform volume maintenance tasks user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Perform volume maintenance tasks\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Perform volume maintenance tasks\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Perform volume maintenance tasks\" user right can manage volume and disk configurations. They could potentially delete volumes, resulting in, data loss or a DoS.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78423","V-63933","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"1071","uuid":"a33266fe-3772-482c-bf62-280c88de210c","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FBE32351647D523D0B8A26A262E483FB64998381\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Perform volume maintenance tasks user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220981","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220981","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220981","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-220981r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-220981","rule_version":"WN10-UR-000150","rule_title":"The Profile single process user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Profile single process\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Profile single process\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Profile single process\" user right can monitor non-system processes performance. An attacker could potentially use this to identify processes to attack.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78425","V-63935","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"9163","uuid":"7db83579-91fa-4d8f-9be7-9e0deefbb0d3","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 26F20E73A3A7FD8C4CB45394C3CAB147D1A5257C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Profile single process user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220982","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220982","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220982","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-220982r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-220982","rule_version":"WN10-UR-000160","rule_title":"The Restore files and directories user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Restore files and directories\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Restore files and directories\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Restore files and directories\" user right can circumvent file and directory permissions and could allow access to sensitive data. It could also be used to over-write more current data.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63939","SV-78429","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"9840","uuid":"8ed9dfac-0bf5-429e-ae92-40e7487e84d0","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6580DA3D954B582920650B9DFBDB371980F277A1\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Restore files and directories user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-220983","group_tree":[{"id":"V-220983","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-220983","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-220983r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-220983","rule_version":"WN10-UR-000165","rule_title":"The Take ownership of files or other objects user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Take ownership of files or other objects\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Take ownership of files or other objects\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Take ownership of files or other objects\" user right can take ownership of objects and make changes.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-78431","V-63941","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"8916","uuid":"c5fb15f8-7187-4197-8dce-d628fc145c32","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-250319","group_tree":[{"id":"V-250319","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-250319","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-250319r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-250319","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000050","rule_title":"Hardened UNC paths must be defined to require mutual authentication and integrity for at least the \\\\*\\SYSVOL and \\\\*\\NETLOGON shares.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Network >> Network Provider >> \"Hardened UNC Paths\" to \"Enabled\" with at least the following configured in \"Hardened UNC Paths:\" (click the \"Show\" button to display).\n\nValue Name: \\\\*\\SYSVOL\nValue: RequireMutualAuthentication=1, RequireIntegrity=1\n\nValue Name: \\\\*\\NETLOGON\nValue: RequireMutualAuthentication=1, RequireIntegrity=1","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This requirement is applicable to domain-joined systems. For standalone or nondomain-joined systems, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry values do not exist or are not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\NetworkProvider\\HardenedPaths\\\n\nValue Name: \\\\*\\NETLOGON\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: RequireMutualAuthentication=1, RequireIntegrity=1\n\nValue Name: \\\\*\\SYSVOL\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: RequireMutualAuthentication=1, RequireIntegrity=1\n\nAdditional entries would not be a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Additional security requirements are applied to Universal Naming Convention (UNC) paths specified in Hardened UNC paths before allowing access to them. This aids in preventing tampering with or spoofing of connections to these paths.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-63577","SV-78067","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5664","uuid":"7f497d52-91e3-490d-b185-fa4aafa35bdc","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 3FB1E2236B8C77F264AB24DA64C405100D1D4D05\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Hardened UNC paths must be defined to require mutual authentication and integrity for at least the \\\\*\\SYSVOL and \\\\*\\NETLOGON shares.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-252896","group_tree":[{"id":"V-252896","title":"SRG-OS-000041-GPOS-00019","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-252896","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000041-GPOS-00019","rule_id_src":"SV-252896r958420_rule","rule_id":"SV-252896","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000327","rule_title":"PowerShell Transcription must be enabled on Windows 10.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows PowerShell >> \"Turn on PowerShell Transcription\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nSpecify the Transcript output directory to point to a Central Log Server or another secure location to prevent user access.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\PowerShell\\Transcription\\\n\nValue Name: EnableTranscripting\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nEnabling PowerShell Transcription will record detailed information from the processing of PowerShell commands and scripts. This can provide additional detail when malware has run on a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000132","CCI-000134"],"reference_identifier":"1839","uuid":"2b1eb32f-dcc7-4bf5-bda1-a3eca34b976a","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5B48BD34F10101E82593725E357AF2E907483CB8\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'PowerShell Transcription must be enabled on Windows 10.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-252903","group_tree":[{"id":"V-252903","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-252903","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-252903r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-252903","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000080","rule_title":"Virtualization-based protection of code integrity must be enabled.","fix_text":"Virtualization-based security currently cannot be implemented in VDIs due to specific supporting requirements, including a TPM, UEFI with Secure Boot, and the capability to run the Hyper-V feature within the virtual desktop.\n\nFor VDIs where the virtual desktop instance is deleted or refreshed upon logoff, this is NA.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Device Guard >> \"Turn On Virtualization Based Security\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Enabled with UEFI lock\" or \"Enabled without lock\" selected for \"Virtualization Based Protection of Code Integrity:\".\n\n\"Enabled with UEFI lock\" is preferred as more secure; however, it cannot be turned off remotely through a group policy change if there is an issue.\n\n\"Enabled without lock\" will allow this to be turned off remotely while testing for issues.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Confirm virtualization-based protection of code integrity.\n\nFor devices that support the virtualization based security (VBS) feature for protection of code integrity, this must be enabled. If the system meets the hardware, firmware, and compatible device driver dependencies for enabling virtualization-based protection of code integrity but it is not enabled, this is a CAT II finding.\n\nVirtualization based security currently cannot be implemented in virtual desktop implementations (VDI) due to specific supporting requirements including a TPM, UEFI with Secure Boot, and the capability to run the Hyper-V feature within the virtual desktop.\n\nFor VDIs where the virtual desktop instance is deleted or refreshed upon logoff, this is NA.\n\nRun \"PowerShell\" with elevated privileges (run as administrator).\nEnter the following:\n\"Get-CimInstance -ClassName Win32_DeviceGuard -Namespace root\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeviceGuard\"\n\nIf \"SecurityServicesRunning\" does not include a value of \"2\" (e.g., \"{1, 2}\"), this is a finding.\n\nAlternately:\n\nRun \"System Information\".\n\nUnder \"System Summary\", verify the following:\nIf \"Virtualization-based Security Services Running\" does not list \"Hypervisor enforced Code Integrity\", this is finding.\n\nThe policy settings referenced in the Fix section will configure the following registry value. However due to hardware requirements, the registry value alone does not ensure proper function.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeviceGuard\\\n\nValue Name: HypervisorEnforcedCodeIntegrity\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1) (Enabled with UEFI lock), or 0x00000002 (2) (Enabled without lock)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Virtualization-based protection of code integrity enforces kernel mode memory protections and protects Code Integrity validation paths. This isolates the processes from the rest of the operating system and can only be accessed by privileged system software.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7583","uuid":"a0738570-f5ee-4bbc-a6c7-6f8194e4d6d5","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 38114B508C7B309D716EA0764C7A39D3750FFE1E\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Virtualization-based protection of code integrity must be enabled.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-256894","group_tree":[{"id":"V-256894","title":"SRG-OS-000185-GPOS-00079","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-256894","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000185-GPOS-00079","rule_id_src":"SV-256894r958552_rule","rule_id":"SV-256894","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000391","rule_title":"Internet Explorer must be disabled for Windows 10.","fix_text":"For Windows 10 semi-annual channel, remove or disable the IE11 application. \n\nTo disable IE11 as a standalone browser:\n\nSet the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Windows Components/Internet Explorer/Disable Internet Explorer 11 as a standalone browser\" to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"Never\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Determine if IE11 is installed or enabled on Windows 10 semi-annual channel.\n\nIf IE11 is installed or not disabled on Windows 10 semi-annual channel, this is a finding.\n\nIf IE11 is installed on a unsupported operating system and is enabled or installed, this is a finding.\n\nFor more information, visit: https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/lifecycle/faq/internet-explorer-microsoft-edge#what-is-the-lifecycle-policy-for-internet-explorer-","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Internet Explorer 11 (IE11) is no longer supported on Windows 10 semi-annual channel.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1316","uuid":"f016e9ce-e663-4327-abcf-b494865a46f5","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4C81DB5D5F36047C1A00AE1CB53EB1DC509D3D79\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Internet Explorer must be disabled for Windows 10.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-257589","group_tree":[{"id":"V-257589","title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-257589","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","rule_id_src":"SV-257589r958412_rule","rule_id":"SV-257589","rule_version":"WN10-AU-000585","rule_title":"Windows 10 must have command line process auditing events enabled for failures.","fix_text":"Go to Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >>System Audit Policies >> Detailed Tracking >> Audit Process Creation is set to \"failure\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Ensure Audit Process Creation auditing has been enabled: \n\nComputer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >>System Audit Policies >> Detailed Tracking >> Audit Process Creation\". \n\nIf \"Audit Process Creation\" is not set to \"Failure\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"When this policy setting is enabled, the operating system generates audit events when a process fails to start and the name of the program or user that created it.\n\nThese audit events can assist in understanding how a computer is being used and tracking user activity.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002234"],"reference_identifier":"9190","uuid":"f175314a-e987-4a6d-b545-fd7602920f1f","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5A759C3298CBD9A0EEDDACC389DD79E16CBFC944\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows 10 must have command line process auditing events enabled for failures.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-257593","group_tree":[{"id":"V-257593","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-257593","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-257593r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-257593","rule_version":"WN10-00-000395","rule_title":"Windows 10 must not have portproxy enabled or in use.","fix_text":"Contact the Administrator to run \"netsh interface portproxy delete\" with elevation. Remove any enabled portproxies that may be configured.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Check the registry key for existence of proxied ports:\nHKLM\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\PortProxy\\. \n\nIf the key contains v4tov4\\tcp\\ or is populated v4tov4\\tcp\\, this is a finding. \n\nRun \"netsh interface portproxy show all\". \n\nIf the command displays any results, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Having portproxy enabled or configured in Windows 10 could allow a man-in-the-middle attack.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"7806","uuid":"710627f5-9d24-4754-b5d0-f9b7de34e264","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E649F9596EA74C6D1BA65C97DA0C1C4896740809\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows 10 must not have portproxy enabled or in use.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-268315","group_tree":[{"id":"V-268315","title":"SRG-OS-000096-GPOS-00050","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-268315","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000096-GPOS-00050","rule_id_src":"SV-268315r1135269_rule","rule_id":"SV-268315","rule_version":"WN10-00-000107","rule_title":"Copilot must be disabled for Windows 10.","fix_text":"Open PowerShell as an administrator. Run the following command:\n\nGet-AppxPackage -AllUsers *CoPilot* | Remove-AppxPackage -AllUsers","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Run the following PowerShell command as an administrator:\n\nGet-AppxPackage -AllUsers | Where-Object { $_.Name -like \"*Copilot*\" }\n\nIf Microsoft.Copilot displays, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature. Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000382"],"reference_identifier":"8653","uuid":"1aa1bdad-7c7f-49d0-a208-b62a71a597cf","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7F7DA68466CAA22AF4995DB0A76AA45389290796\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Copilot must be disabled for Windows 10.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-268319","group_tree":[{"id":"V-268319","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-268319","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-268319r1135263_rule","rule_id":"SV-268319","rule_version":"WN10-CC-000063","rule_title":"Windows 10 systems must use either Group Policy or an approved Mobile Device Management (MDM) product to enforce STIG compliance.","fix_text":"Configure the Windows 10 system to use either Group Policy or an approved MDM product to enforce STIG compliance.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the Windows 10 system is receiving policy from either Group Policy or an MDM with the following steps:\n\nFrom a command line or PowerShell:\n\ngpresult /R\nOS Configuration: Member Workstation\n\nIf the system is not being managed by GPO, ask the administrator to indicate which MDM is managing the device.\n\nFrom PowerShell: Get-Service -Name \"IntuneManagementExtension\"\n\nIf the Windows 10 system is not receiving policy from either Group Policy or an MDM, this is a finding.\n\nThis is NA for standalone, nondomain-joined systems.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without Windows 10 systems being managed, devices could be rogue and become targets of an attacker.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4449","uuid":"fa270297-1978-46e7-99fb-438f6e863135","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FDA3E89B038E5ADAA0964D929E17E5E25970E204\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows 10 systems must use either Group Policy or an approved Mobile Device Management (MDM) product to enforce STIG compliance.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-278918","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278918","title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278918","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","rule_id_src":"SV-278918r1135272_rule","rule_id":"SV-278918","rule_version":"WN10-AU-000581","rule_title":"Windows 10 must be configured to audit file system failures.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Object Access >> \"Audit File System\" with \"Failure\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that Audit File System auditing has been enabled: \n\nComputer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Object Access >> Audit File System. \n\nIf \"Audit File System\" is not set to \"Failure\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior. Credential validation records events related to validation tests on credentials for a user account logon.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"1931","uuid":"444e3336-6db4-41dc-8971-818007e9062f","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E37FD2AC37C748FDE57DAE18B7431FFA576DFD05\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows 10 must be configured to audit file system failures.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-278919","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278919","title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278919","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","rule_id_src":"SV-278919r1135275_rule","rule_id":"SV-278919","rule_version":"WN10-AU-000582","rule_title":"Windows 10 must be configured to audit file system successes.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Object Access >> \"Audit File System\" with \"Success\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that Audit File System auditing has been enabled: \n\nComputer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Object Access >> Audit File System. \n\nIf \"Audit File System\" is not set to \"Success\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior. Credential validation records events related to validation tests on credentials for a user account logon.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"5156","uuid":"7eb6cca5-feb2-49c5-a161-2ab0ef78ad28","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 26CB60B8CC73759954C8BE23044A32D375B6149C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows 10 must be configured to audit file system successes.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-278920","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278920","title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278920","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","rule_id_src":"SV-278920r1135278_rule","rule_id":"SV-278920","rule_version":"WN10-AU-000583","rule_title":"Windows 10 must be configured to audit handle manipulation failures.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Object Access >> \"Audit Handle Manipulation\" with \"Failure\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that Audit Handle Manipulation auditing has been enabled: \n\nComputer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Object Access >> Audit Handle Manipulation. \n\nIf \"Audit Handle Manipulation\" is not set to \"Failure\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior. Credential validation records events related to validation tests on credentials for a user account logon.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"6953","uuid":"9512ae96-914b-4822-ba9b-f86d2af83ecb","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0DB8467322AA20B12B1E3DB2097ED7D894C4DC60\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Windows 10 must be configured to audit handle manipulation failures.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-278921","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278921","title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278921","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","rule_id_src":"SV-278921r1135281_rule","rule_id":"SV-278921","rule_version":"WN10-AU-000584","rule_title":"Windows 10 must be configured to audit handle manipulation successes.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Object Access >> \"Audit Handle Manipulation\" with \"Success\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that Audit Handle Manipulation auditing has been enabled: \n\nComputer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Object Access >> Audit Handle Manipulation. \n\nIf \"Audit Handle Manipulation\" is not set to \"Success\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior. Credential validation records events related to validation tests on credentials for a user account logon.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"9774","uuid":"869d5769-1af6-4795-b884-b8c79b258c12","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 63FAF5E25683620320B9890264A21F000182C474\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows 10 must be configured to audit handle manipulation successes.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-278922","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278922","title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278922","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","rule_id_src":"SV-278922r1135284_rule","rule_id":"SV-278922","rule_version":"WN10-AU-000586","rule_title":"Windows 10 must be configured to audit registry successes.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Object Access >> \"Audit Registry\" with \"Success\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that Audit Registry auditing has been enabled: \n\nComputer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Object Access >> Audit Registry. \n\nIf \"Audit Registry\" is not set to \"Success\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior. Credential validation records events related to validation tests on credentials for a user account logon.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"7598","uuid":"5be31cf1-f3f0-4a60-b62e-839d46a233f2","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7654304F373264853AA375F16C534AFD58F03079\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows 10 must be configured to audit registry successes.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-278923","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278923","title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278923","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","rule_id_src":"SV-278923r1135287_rule","rule_id":"SV-278923","rule_version":"WN10-AU-000589","rule_title":"Windows 10 must be configured to audit registry failures.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Object Access >> \"Audit Registry\" with \"Failure\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that Audit Registry auditing has been enabled: \n\nComputer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Object Access >> Audit Registry. \n\nIf \"Audit Registry\" is not set to \"Failure\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior. Credential validation records events related to validation tests on credentials for a user account logon.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"3197","uuid":"a1d89cf8-85be-47ab-bd9e-b73584734768","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5B55AAC207D458E3C6295148DD9C2BAE44475F47\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows 10 must be configured to audit registry failures.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-278924","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278924","title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278924","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","rule_id_src":"SV-278924r1141910_rule","rule_id":"SV-278924","rule_version":"WN10-AU-000587","rule_title":"Windows 10 must be configured to audit sensitive privilege use successes.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Privilege Use >> Audit Sensitive Privilege Use with \"Success\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that Audit Sensitive Privilege Use auditing has been enabled: \n\nComputer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Privilege Use >> Audit Sensitive Privilege Use. \n\nIf \"Audit Sensitive Privilege Use\" is not set to \"Success\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior. Credential validation records events related to validation tests on credentials for a user account logon.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"8322","uuid":"abf42904-dca7-43ce-a657-d8902f99ec59","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DE9A027930F0AC59E0883282289612D00FA83BC6\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows 10 must be configured to audit sensitive privilege use successes.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-278925","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278925","title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278925","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","rule_id_src":"SV-278925r1141913_rule","rule_id":"SV-278925","rule_version":"WN10-AU-000588","rule_title":"Windows 10 must be configured to audit sensitive privilege use failures.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Privilege Use >> Audit Sensitive Privilege Use with \"Failure\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that Audit Sensitive Privilege Use auditing has been enabled: \n\nComputer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Privilege Use >> Audit Sensitive Privilege Use. \n\nIf \"Audit Sensitive Privilege Use\" is not set to \"Failure\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior. Credential validation records events related to validation tests on credentials for a user account logon.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"5243","uuid":"4aecce7c-9ef1-42b8-b749-b2a9b15488f6","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 94BCEBC0C16354A4B7DC87EE24C6EF9414F68A55\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows 10 must be configured to audit sensitive privilege use failures.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-279687","group_tree":[{"id":"V-279687","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-279687","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-279687r1154974_rule","rule_id":"SV-279687","rule_version":"WN10-00-000126","rule_title":"Windows 10 systems must block consumer account user authentication.","fix_text":"Configure the following Group Policy:\nComputer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Account \"block all consumer Microsoft account user authentication\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nFor systems managed by Intune, apply the DOD Windows 10 STIG Settings Catalog (or equivalent Intune policy) found in the Intune policy package available on cyber.mil.\nSteps to create an Intune policy:\n1. Sign in to the Intune admin center >> Devices >> Configuration >> Create >> New Policy.\n2. Platform: Windows 10 and later. Profile type: Settings Catalog, then click \"Create\".\n3. Basics: Provide a Name and Description of the profile, then click \"Next\".\n4. Configuration settings: Click \"+ Add settings\" and search for consumer under the Settings picker. Under the Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft account category, check the box next to \"Block all consumer Microsoft account user authentication\". Click the \"Enabled\" radio button, then click \"Next\".\n5. Scope tags: (optional), then click \"Next\".\n6. Assignments: Assign the policy to Entra security groups that contain the target users or devices, then click \"Next\".\n7. Review + create: Review the deployment summary, then click \"Create\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the \"block all consumer Microsoft account user authentication\" is enabled.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\MicrosoftAccount\n\nValue Name: DisableUserAuth\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)\n\nIf the registry value is not \"1\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"It is detrimental for operating systems to provide, or install by default, functionality exceeding requirements or mission objectives. These unnecessary capabilities or services are often overlooked and therefore, may remain unsecured. They increase the risk to the platform by providing additional attack vectors.\n\nOperating systems are capable of providing a wide variety of functions and services. Some of the functions and services, provided by default, may not be necessary to support essential organizational operations (e.g., key missions, functions).\n\nThe Copilot Rewrite functionality within Notepad and Image Generation within Paint is dependent upon the use of AI credits from a Microsoft 365 Personal or Family subscription. Organizational users must not use personal accounts to login to applications on enterprise machines.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"6169","uuid":"88b8186b-b085-46cc-902c-09c93157a807","stig_uuid":"bdc79de2-f231-4be5-9610-60ab816466d5","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C3FB37A9C8A0E774E1DFCF6597F3CA32752AEB1D\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows 10 systems must block consumer account user authentication.' matches the expected value on the Windows 10 workstation."}]},{"evaluate-stig":{"time":"2026-07-23T17:12:42.0000000+00:00","module":{"name":"Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks","version":"1.2604.2"}},"stig_name":"Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus Security Technical Implementation Guide","display_name":"Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus","stig_id":"MS_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG","release_info":"Release: 5 Benchmark Date: 01 Apr 2026","version":"3","uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","reference_identifier":"2659","size":139,"rules":[{"group_id_src":"V-223280","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223280","title":"SRG-APP-000179","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223280","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000179","rule_id_src":"SV-223280r961050_rule","rule_id":"SV-223280","rule_version":"O365-AC-000001","rule_title":"Macros must be blocked from running in Access files from the Internet.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Access 2016 >> Application Settings >> Security >> Trust Center \"Block macros from running in Office files from the Internet\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Access 2016 >> Application Settings >> Security >> Trust Center \"Block macros from running in Office files from the Internet\" is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\access\\security\n\nIf the value blockcontentexecutionfrominternet is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to block macros from running in Office files that come from the Internet.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, macros are blocked from running, even if \u201cEnable all macros\u201d is selected in the Macro Settings section of the Trust Center. Also, instead of having the choice to \u201cEnable Content\u201d, users will receive a notification that macros are blocked from running. If the Office file is saved to a trusted location or was previously trusted by the user, macros will be allowed to run.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the settings configured in the Macro Settings section of the Trust Center determine whether macros run in Office files that come from the Internet.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108737","V-99633","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"1668","uuid":"4b8fb493-7fa4-436b-9b13-06389f4e5b76","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-223281","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223281","title":"SRG-APP-000131","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223281","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000131","rule_id_src":"SV-223281r1016166_rule","rule_id":"SV-223281","rule_version":"O365-AC-000002","rule_title":"Trust Bar Notifications for unsigned application add-ins in Access must be disabled and blocked.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Access 2016 >> Application Settings >> Security >> Trust Center \"Disable Trust Bar Notification for unsigned application add-ins and block them\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Access 2016 >> Application Settings >> Security >> Trust Center \"Disable Trust Bar Notification for unsigned application add-ins and block them\" is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\access\\security\n\nIf the value NoTBPromptUnsignedAddin is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether the specified Office application notifies users when unsigned application add-ins are loaded or silently disable such add-ins without notification. This policy setting only applies if the \"Require that application add-ins are signed by Trusted Publisher\" policy setting is enabled, which prevents users from changing this policy setting.\n\nIf users enable this policy setting, applications automatically disable unsigned add-ins without informing users.\n\nIf this policy setting is disabled, if this application is configured to require that all add-ins be signed by a trusted publisher, any unsigned add-ins the application loads will be disabled and the application will display the Trust Bar at the top of the active window. The Trust Bar contains a message that informs users about the unsigned add-in.\n\nIf users do not configure this policy setting, the disable behavior applies, and in addition, users can configure this requirement themselves in the \"Add-ins\" category of the Trust Center for the application.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108739","V-99635","CCI-003992","CCI-001749"],"reference_identifier":"7238","uuid":"c82e03a2-2dd0-49a7-878f-076b8be006ca","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0C7DD3A13EC8F4A9CFCDCCD4132F6F93447DDB3C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Trust Bar Notifications for unsigned application add-ins in Access must be disabled and blocked.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223282","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223282","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223282","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223282r1082349_rule","rule_id":"SV-223282","rule_version":"O365-AC-000003","rule_title":"VBA macros not digitally signed must be blocked in Access.","fix_text":"Set User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Access 2016 >> Application Settings >> Security >> Trust Center >> VBA Macro Notification Settings to \"Disable all except digitally signed macros\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Access 2016 >> Application Settings >> Security >> Trust Center >> VBA Macro Notification Settings is set to \"Disable all except digitally signed macros\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\Microsoft\\office\\16.0\\access\\security\n\nIf the value vbawarnings is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding. A value of REG_DWORD = 2 or REG_DWORD =  4 is also acceptable. If the registry key does not exist, or is not configured properly, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls how the specified applications warn users when Visual Basic for Applications (VBA) macros are present.\n\nIf this policy setting is enabled, choose from four options for determining how the specified applications will warn the user about macros:\n\n- Disable all with notification: The application displays the Trust Bar for all macros, whether signed or unsigned. This option enforces the default configuration in Office. This option also allows users to potentially enable unsigned/untrusted macros. If a site requires the use of macros, they must be signed/approved and added to appropriate locations listed in the Trust Center Settings. \n- Disable all except digitally signed macros: The application displays the Trust Bar for digitally signed macros, allowing users to enable them or leave them disabled. Any unsigned macros are disabled, and users are not notified.\n- Disable all without notification: The application disables all macros, whether signed or unsigned, and does not notify users.\n- Enable all macros (not recommended): All macros are enabled, whether signed or unsigned. This option can significantly reduce security by allowing dangerous code to run undetected.\n\nIf this policy setting is disabled, \"Disable all with notification\" will be the default setting.\n\nIf this policy setting is not configured, when users open files in the specified applications that contain VBA macros, the applications open the files with the macros disabled and display the Trust Bar with a warning that macros are present and have been disabled. Users can inspect and edit the files if appropriate, but cannot use any disabled functionality until they enable it by clicking \"Enable Content\" on the Trust Bar. If the user clicks \"Enable Content\", then the document is added as a trusted document.\n\nImportant: If \"Disable all except digitally signed macros\" is selected, users will not be able to open unsigned Access databases.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108741","V-99637","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3471","uuid":"11fd228f-49f7-46a2-b86d-b4e366df601f","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A0A93069CC13078456A92552D045F10C8C09B4F7\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'VBA macros not digitally signed must be blocked in Access.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223284","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223284","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223284","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223284r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223284","rule_version":"O365-CO-000001","rule_title":"The Macro Runtime Scan Scope must be enabled for all documents.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016>> Security Settings \"Macro Runtime Scan Scope\" to \"Enable for all documents\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016>> Security Settings \"Macro Runtime Scan Scope\" is set to \"Enable for all documents\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\common\\security\n\nIf the value for macroruntimescanscope is REG_DWORD = 2, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting specifies for which documents the VBA Runtime Scan feature is enabled.\n\nIf the feature is disabled for all documents, no runtime scanning of enabled macros will be performed.\n\nIf the feature is enabled for low trust documents, the feature will be enabled for all documents for which macros are enabled except:\n - Documents opened while macro security settings are set to \"Enable All Macros\"\n - Documents opened from a Trusted Location\n - Documents that are Trusted Documents\n - Documents that contain VBA that is digitally signed by a Trusted Publisher\n\nIf the feature is enabled for all documents, then the above class of documents are not excluded from the behavior.\n\nThis protocol allows the VBA runtime to report to the Anti-Virus system certain high-risk code behaviors it is about to execute and allows the Anti-Virus to report back to the process if the sequence of observed behaviors indicates likely malicious activity so the Office application can take appropriate action.\n\nWhen this feature is enabled, affected VBA projects' runtime performance may be reduced.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108745","V-99641","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"5593","uuid":"2467f06a-14c2-4ade-9620-4100a06e92f4","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4E8C5EE433FFD3495F94314E7F8CCEB8A085135B\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Macro Runtime Scan Scope must be enabled for all documents.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223285","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223285","title":"SRG-APP-000429","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223285","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-APP-000429","rule_id_src":"SV-223285r1067544_rule","rule_id":"SV-223285","rule_version":"O365-CO-000002","rule_title":"Document metadata for rights managed Office Open XML files must be protected.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Security Settings \"Protect document metadata for rights managed Office Open XML Files\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Security Settings \"Protect document metadata for rights managed Office Open XML Files\" is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\security\n\nIf the value DRMEncryptProperty is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether metadata is encrypted in Office Open XML files that are protected by Information Rights Management (IRM). If this policy setting is enabled, Excel, PowerPoint, and Word encrypt metadata stored in rights-managed Office Open XML files and override any configuration changes on users' computers. \n\nIf this policy setting is enabled, Office 2016 applications cannot encrypt metadata in rights-managed Office Open XML files, which can reduce security. If this policy setting is not configured when Information Rights Management (IRM) is used to restrict access to an Office Open XML document, any metadata associated with the document is not encrypted.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108747","V-99643","CCI-002476"],"reference_identifier":"7567","uuid":"33791b38-f90d-4a1f-bbc7-02ad5d176d38","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A16693D1DC5C8247542E0EE6D08BC529BD188CDE\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Document metadata for rights managed Office Open XML files must be protected.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223286","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223286","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223286","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223286r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223286","rule_version":"O365-CO-000003","rule_title":"The Office client must be prevented from polling the SharePoint Server for published links.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Server Settings >> Disable the Office client from polling the SharePoint Server for published links to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Server Settings >> Disable the Office client from polling the SharePoint Server for published links is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\common\\portal\n\nIf the value for linkpublishingdisabled is REG_DWORD = \"1\", this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether Office 365 ProPlus applications can poll Office servers to retrieve lists of published links. \n\nIf this policy setting is enabled, Office 365 ProPlus applications cannot poll an Office server for published links. \n\nIf this policy setting is disabled or not configured, users of Office 365 ProPlus applications can see and use links to Microsoft SharePoint Server sites from those applications. Published links can be configured to Office applications during initial deployment, and can add or change links as part of regular operations. These links appear on the My SharePoint Sites tab of the Open, Save, and Save As dialog boxes when opening and saving documents from these applications. Links can be targeted so they only appear to users who are members of particular audiences. \n\nNote: This policy setting applies to Microsoft SharePoint Server specifically. It does not apply to Microsoft SharePoint Foundation.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108749","V-99645","CCI-000381","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"9353","uuid":"23389a27-e2ae-4c4c-ac3d-0b849d78c154","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 04FA76DEA3C0D255D54CD37E6923DDA2CA51FA42\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Office client must be prevented from polling the SharePoint Server for published links.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223287","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223287","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223287","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","rule_id_src":"SV-223287r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223287","rule_version":"O365-CO-000004","rule_title":"Custom user interface (UI) code must be blocked from loading in all Office applications.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Global Options >> Customize >> Disable UI extending from documents and templates to Enabled: Disallow in Word; Excel; PowerPoint; Access; Outlook; Publisher; Project; Visio; InfoPath.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Global Options >> Customize >> Disable UI extending from documents and templates is set to Enabled: Disallow in Word; Excel; PowerPoint; Access; Outlook; Publisher; Project; Visio; InfoPath\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\n\nIf the value noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument is REG_DWORD = 1 for all installed Office programs, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether Office 365 ProPlus applications load any custom user interface (UI) code included with a document or template. Office 365 ProPlus allows developers to extend the UI with customization code that is included in a document or template. \n\nIf this policy setting is enabled, Office 365 ProPlus applications cannot load any UI customization code included with documents and templates. \n\nIf this policy setting is not configured or disabled, Office 365 ProPlus applications load any UI customization code included with a document or template when opening it.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108751","V-99647","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2980","uuid":"c8b9804b-85f3-43ef-b94f-246ca951d84b","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E86C848DF49E3F21847D1874928F6A10CBCEBF06\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Custom user interface (UI) code must be blocked from loading in all Office applications.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223288","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223288","title":"SRG-APP-000488","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223288","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000488","rule_id_src":"SV-223288r961779_rule","rule_id":"SV-223288","rule_version":"O365-CO-000005","rule_title":"ActiveX Controls must be initialized in Safe Mode.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Security Settings \"ActiveX Control Initialization\" to \"Enabled + 6\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Security Settings \"ActiveX Control Initialization\" is set to \"Enabled (If SFI, load the control in safe mode and use persisted values (if any). If not SFI, prompt the user and advise them that it is marked unsafe. If the user chooses No at the prompt, do not load the control. Otherwise, load it with persisted values.)\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\Common\\Security\n\nIf the value UFIControls is set to REG_DWORD=6, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting specifies the Microsoft ActiveX initialization security level for all Microsoft Office applications. ActiveX controls can adversely affect a computer directly. In addition, malicious code can be used to compromise an ActiveX control and attack a computer. \n\nTo indicate the safety of an ActiveX control, developers can denote them as Safe for Initialization (SFI). SFI indicates that a control is safe to open and run, and that it is not capable of causing a problem for any computer, regardless of whether it has persisted data values or not. If a control is not marked SFI, it is possible that the control could adversely affect a computer--or it could mean that the developers did not test the control in all situations and are not sure whether it might be compromised in the future. If you enable this policy setting, you can set the ActiveX security level to a number between 1 and 6. These security levels are as follows:\n \n1. Regardless of how the control is marked, load it and use the persisted values (if any). This setting does not prompt the user. \n\n2. If SFI, load the control in safe mode and use persisted values (if any). If not SFI, load in unsafe mode with persisted values (if any), or use the default (first-time initialization) settings. This level is similar to the default configuration, but does not prompt the user. \n\n3. If SFI, load the control in unsafe mode and use persisted values (if any). If not SFI, prompt the user and advise them that it is marked unsafe. If the user chooses No at the prompt, do not load the control. Otherwise, load it with default (first-time initialization) settings. \n\n4. If SFI, load the control in safe mode and use persisted values (if any). If not SFI, prompt the user and advise them that it is marked unsafe. If the user chooses No at the prompt, do not load the control. Otherwise, load it with default (first-time initialization) settings. \n\n5. If SFI, load the control in unsafe mode and use persisted values (if any). If not SFI, prompt the user and advise them that it is marked unsafe. If the user chooses No at the prompt, do not load the control. Otherwise, load it with persisted values. \n\n6. If SFI, load the control in safe mode and use persisted values (if any). If not SFI, prompt the user and advise them that it is marked unsafe. If the user chooses No at the prompt, do not load the control. Otherwise, load it with persisted values. \n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, if a control is marked SFI, the application loads the control in safe mode and uses persisted values (if any). If the control is not marked SFI, the application loads the control in unsafe mode with persisted values (if any), or uses the default (first-time initialization) settings. In both situations, the Message Bar informs users that the controls have been disabled and prompts them to respond. \n\nImportant: Some ActiveX controls do not respect the safe mode registry setting, and therefore might load persisted data even though you configure this setting to instruct the control to use safe mode. This setting only increases security for ActiveX controls that are accurately marked as SFI. In situations that involve malicious or poorly designed code, an ActiveX control might be inaccurately marked as SFI.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108753","V-99649","CCI-002460"],"reference_identifier":"5121","uuid":"f09d523d-358b-409a-96b9-28a0feec3a0e","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4158627CDFCBBAF423B850AD3734BD6498ECEBA3\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'ActiveX Controls must be initialized in Safe Mode.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223289","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223289","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223289","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223289r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223289","rule_version":"O365-CO-000006","rule_title":"Macros in all Office applications that are opened programmatically by another application must be opened based upon macro security level.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Security Settings \"Automation Security\" to \"Enabled (Use application macro security level)\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Security Settings \"Automation Security\" is set to \"Enabled (Use application macro security level)\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\Common\\Security\n\nIf the value AutomationSecurity is REG_DWORD = 2, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether macros can run in an Office 365 ProPlus application that is opened programmatically by another application. If this policy setting is enabled, the user can choose from three options for controlling macro behavior in Excel, PowerPoint, and Word when the application is opened programmatically:\n\n- Disable macros by default \u00ac- all macros are disabled in the programmatically opened application. \n- Macros enabled (default) - macros can run in the programmatically opened application. This option enforces the default configuration in Excel, PowerPoint, and Word. \n- User application macro security level - macro functionality is determined by the setting in the \"Macro Settings\" section of the Trust Center. \n\nIf this policy setting is disabled or not configured, when a separate program is used to launch Microsoft Excel, PowerPoint, or Word programmatically, any macros can run in the programmatically opened application without being blocked.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108755","V-99651","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"2153","uuid":"66662c39-e6d4-4df7-b54c-57d5b97d9e61","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-223290","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223290","title":"SRG-APP-000131","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223290","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000131","rule_id_src":"SV-223290r1016167_rule","rule_id":"SV-223290","rule_version":"O365-CO-000007","rule_title":"Trust Bar notifications must be configured to display information in the Message Bar about the content that has been automatically blocked.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Security Settings \"Disable all Trust Bar notifications for security issues\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Security Settings >> Disable all Trust Bar notifications for security issues is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\common\\trustcenter\n\nIf the value trustbar is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether Office 365 ProPlus applications notify users when potentially unsafe features or content are detected, or whether such features or content are silently disabled without notification. \n\nThe Message Bar in Office 365 ProPlus applications is used to identify security issues, such as unsigned macros or potentially unsafe add-ins. When such issues are detected, the application disables the unsafe feature or content and displays the Message Bar at the top of the active window. The Message Bar informs the users about the nature of the security issue and, in some cases, provides the users with an option to enable the potentially unsafe feature or content, which could harm the user's computer. \n\nIf this policy setting is enabled, Office 365 ProPlus applications do not display information in the Message Bar about potentially unsafe content that has been detected or has automatically been blocked.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108757","V-99653","CCI-003992","CCI-001749"],"reference_identifier":"6099","uuid":"64a1b93e-ea71-468c-9c7d-a2e8993d5a3a","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 58E68D14A339E10B0D9BA566A6ECBAFAA7F0FFE2\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Trust Bar notifications must be configured to display information in the Message Bar about the content that has been automatically blocked.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223291","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223291","title":"SRG-APP-000231","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223291","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000231","rule_id_src":"SV-223291r961128_rule","rule_id":"SV-223291","rule_version":"O365-CO-000008","rule_title":"Office applications must be configured to specify encryption type in password-protected Office 97-2003 files.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Security Settings >> Encryption type for password protected Office 97-2003 files to Microsoft Enhanced RSA and AES Cryptographic Provider,AES 256,256.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Security Settings >> Encryption type for password protected Office 97-2003 files is set to Microsoft Enhanced RSA and AES Cryptographic Provider,AES 256,256.\n \nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\common\\security\n\nIf the value defaultencryption12 is set to REG_SZ = \"Microsoft Enhanced RSA and AES Cryptographic Provider,AES 256,256\", this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting enables you to specify an encryption type for password-protected Office 97-2003 files.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can specify the type of encryption that Office applications will use to encrypt password-protected files in the older Office 97-2003 file formats. The chosen encryption type must have a corresponding cryptographic service provider (CSP) installed on the computer that encrypts the file. See the HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Cryptography\\Defaults\\Provider\\ registry key for a list of CSPs installed on the local computer. Specify the encryption type to use by entering it in the provided text box in the following form:\n\n<Encryption Provider>,<Encryption Algorithm>,<Encryption Key Length>.\nFor example, Microsoft Enhanced Cryptographic Provider v1.0,RC4,128\n\nIf you do not configure this policy setting, Excel, PowerPoint, and Word use Office 97/2000 Compatible encryption, a proprietary encryption method, to encrypt password-protected Office 97-2003 files.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108759","V-99655","CCI-001199"],"reference_identifier":"8928","uuid":"4face4f6-d348-4bc3-b3b1-39c7552539b7","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 238B1C3D0985E462BAD6A8D866EABC1844014652\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Office applications must be configured to specify encryption type in password-protected Office 97-2003 files.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223292","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223292","title":"SRG-APP-000231","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223292","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000231","rule_id_src":"SV-223292r961128_rule","rule_id":"SV-223292","rule_version":"O365-CO-000009","rule_title":"Office applications must be configured to specify encryption type in password-protected Office Open XML files.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Security Settings >> Encryption type for password protected Office Open XML files to Microsoft Enhanced RSA and AES Cryptographic Provider,AES 256,256.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Security Settings >> Encryption type for password protected Office Open XML files is set to Microsoft Enhanced RSA and AES Cryptographic Provider,AES 256,256.\n \nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\common\\security\n\nIf the value OpenXMLEncryption is REG_SZ = \"Microsoft Enhanced RSA and AES Cryptographic Provider,AES 256,256\", this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to specify an encryption type for Office Open XML files.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can specify the type of encryption that Office applications use to encrypt password-protected files in the Office Open XML file formats used by Excel, PowerPoint, and Word. The chosen encryption type must have a corresponding cryptographic service provider (CSP) installed on the computer that encrypts the file. See the HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Cryptography\\Defaults\\Provider\\ registry key for a list of CSPs installed on the local computer. Specify the encryption type to use by entering it in the provided text box in the following form:\n\n<Encryption Provider>,<Encryption Algorithm>,<Encryption Key Length>\n\nFor example: Microsoft Enhanced Cryptographic Provider v1.0,RC4,128\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the default CSP is used. The default cryptographic service provider (CSP) is Microsoft Enhanced RSA and AES Cryptographic Provider, AES-128, 128-bit.\n\nNote: This policy setting does not take effect unless the registry key \nHKEY_CURRENT_USER\\Software\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\<office application name>\\Security\\Crypto\\CompatMode is set to 0. By default the CompatMode registry key is set to 1.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108761","V-99657","CCI-001199"],"reference_identifier":"4599","uuid":"94dec2b8-bbe4-48a4-bb2a-baca5468b2ae","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E180C37AABA3690CADC78F2D442F7F46CA1E39F0\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Office applications must be configured to specify encryption type in password-protected Office Open XML files.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223293","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223293","title":"SRG-APP-000340","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223293","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000340","rule_id_src":"SV-223293r961353_rule","rule_id":"SV-223293","rule_version":"O365-CO-000010","rule_title":"Users must be prevented from creating new trusted locations in the Trust Center.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Security Settings >> Trust Center >> Allow mix of policy and user locations to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016\\Security Settings\\Trust Center >> Allow mix of policy and user locations is set to \"Disabled\".\n \nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\common\\security\\trusted locations\n\nIf the value for allow user locations is set to REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether trusted locations can be defined by users, the Office Customization Tool (OCT), and Group Policy, or if they must be defined by Group Policy alone.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, users can specify any location as a trusted location, and a computer can have a combination of user-created, OCT-created, and Group Policy-created trusted locations.\n\nIf you disable this policy setting, all trusted locations that are not created by Group Policy are disabled and users cannot create new trusted locations in the Trust Center.\n\nIf you do not configure this policy setting, the behavior is the equivalent of setting the policy to Enabled.\n\nNote: InfoPath and Outlook do not recognize trusted locations, and therefore are unaffected by this policy setting.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108763","V-99659","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"7115","uuid":"0d08cb11-f3cf-4bfb-a217-ff1ab776e846","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 3A2C0D87F0BAF2149B366B46636626B82D194D21\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Users must be prevented from creating new trusted locations in the Trust Center.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223294","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223294","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223294","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","rule_id_src":"SV-223294r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223294","rule_version":"O365-CO-000012","rule_title":"Office applications must not load XML expansion packs with Smart Documents.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Smart Documents (Word, Excel) >> Disable Smart Document's use of manifests to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Smart Documents (Word, Excel) >> Disable Smart Document's use of manifests is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\common\\smart tag\n\nIf the value for neverloadmanifests is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether Office 365 ProPlus applications can load an XML expansion pack manifest file with a Smart Document.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108767","V-99663","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7579","uuid":"ac85251d-d4ef-430f-b5f7-30c3329c6d69","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7693DD011C266827F903C72BA0010681F8B5D178\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Office applications must not load XML expansion packs with Smart Documents.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223295","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223295","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223295","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223295r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223295","rule_version":"O365-CO-000013","rule_title":"The load of controls in Forms3 must be blocked.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Security Settings \"Load Controls in Forms3\" to \"Enabled:1\" or set it to \"Disabled.\"","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Security Settings \"Load Controls in Forms3\" is set to Enabled and 1 from drop down. (For a UFI or SFI signed control that supports safe and unsafe mode, load the control in unsafe mode. For an SFI signed control that only supports a safe mode configuration, load the control in safe mode. This option enforces the default configuration.)\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\VBA\\Security\n\nIf the value LoadControlsInForms is REG_DWORD=1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value LoadControlsInForms does not exist, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows the user to control how ActiveX controls in UserForms should be initialized based upon whether they are Safe for Initialization (SFI) or Unsafe for Initialization (UFI). \n \nActiveX controls are Component Object Model (COM) objects and have unrestricted access to users' computers. ActiveX controls can access the local file system and change the registry settings of the operating system. If a malicious user repurposes an ActiveX control to take over a user's computer, the effect could be significant. To help improve security, ActiveX developers can mark controls as SFI, which means that the developer states that the controls are safe to open and run and not capable of causing harm to any computers. If a control is not marked SFI, the control could adversely affect a computer, or the developers may not have tested the control in all situations and are not sure whether their control might be compromised at some future date. SFI controls run in safe mode, which limits their access to the computer. For example, a worksheet control can both read and write files when it is in unsafe mode, but perhaps only read from files when it is in safe mode. This functionality allows the control to be used in very powerful ways when safety was not important, but the control would still be safe for use in a Web page. If a control is not marked as SFI, it is marked UFI, which means that it is capable of affecting a user's computer. If UFI ActiveX controls are loaded, they are always loaded in unsafe mode. \n \nIf this policy setting is enabled, choose from four options for loading controls in UserForms: \n \n1. For a UFI or SFI signed control that supports safe and unsafe mode, load the control in unsafe mode. For an SFI signed control that only supports a safe mode configuration, load the control in safe mode. This option enforces the default configuration. \n \n2. Users are prompted to determine how UserForm forms will load. The prompt only displays once per session within an application. When users respond to the prompt, loading continues based on whether the control is UFI or SFI: \n \n- For a UFI signed control, if users respond \"Yes\" to the prompt, load the control in unsafe mode. If users respond \"No\", load the control using the default properties. \n- For an SFI signed control that supports both safe and unsafe modes, if users respond \"Yes\" to the prompt, load the control in unsafe mode. If users respond \"No\", load the control using safe mode. If the SFI control can only support safe mode, load the control in safe mode. This option is the default configuration in the Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus release. \n \n3. Users are prompted to determine how UserForm forms will load. The prompt only displays once per session within an application. When users respond to the prompt, loading continues based on whether the control is UFI or SFI: \n \n- For a UFI signed control, if users respond \"Yes\" to the prompt, load the control in unsafe mode. If users respond \"No\", load the control with its default properties. \n- For an SFI signed control, load in safe mode. \n \n4. For a UFI signed control, load with the default properties of the control. For an SFI signed control, load in safe mode (considered to be the safest mode). \n \nIf  this policy setting is disabled or not configured, the behavior is as if this policy setting is enabled and then select option \"1\".","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108769","V-99665","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"5210","uuid":"5007f632-31be-4919-8d86-8366f7eb2367","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2AAD4C7CD6A3D3B4D716CE9A460E43AB20FA4EC6\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The load of controls in Forms3 must be blocked.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223296","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223296","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223296","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223296r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223296","rule_version":"O365-CO-000014","rule_title":"Add-on Management must be enabled for all Office 365 ProPlus programs.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security \"Add-on Management\" to \"Enabled\" and select the check boxes for  all installed Office programs.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security \"Add-on Management\" is set to \"Enabled\" and the check box is selected for every installed Office program.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ADDON_MANAGEMENT\n\nIf the value for each installed Office Program is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Internet Explorer add-ons are pieces of code, run in Internet Explorer, to provide additional functionality. Rogue add-ons may contain viruses or other malicious code. Disabling or not configuring this setting could allow malicious code or users to become active on user computers or the network. For example, a malicious user can monitor and then use keystrokes that user's type into Internet Explorer. Even legitimate add-ons may demand resources, compromising the performance of Internet Explorer and the operating systems for user computers.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108771","V-99667","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"6348","uuid":"e88a93d0-e112-4df2-9db3-53f29098ea90","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1F118B20C9F6C08309649F33248B6E026FB1B007\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Add-on Management must be enabled for all Office 365 ProPlus programs.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223297","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223297","title":"SRG-APP-000179","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223297","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000179","rule_id_src":"SV-223297r961050_rule","rule_id":"SV-223297","rule_version":"O365-CO-000015","rule_title":"Consistent MIME handling must be enabled for all Office 365 ProPlus programs.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security \"Consistent Mime Handling\" to \"Enabled\" and select the check boxes for all installed Office programs.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Consistent Mime Handling is set to \"Enabled\" and the check box is selected for every installed Office program.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\software\\microsoft\\internet explorer\\main\\featurecontrol\\feature_mime_handling\n\nIf the value for all installed Office programs is set to is REG_DWORD=1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Encryption is only as good as the encryption modules utilized. Unapproved cryptographic module algorithms cannot be verified and cannot be relied on to provide confidentiality or integrity, and DoD data may be compromised due to weak algorithms. The use of TLS provides confidentiality of data in transit between the application server and client. FIPS 140-2 approved TLS versions include TLS V1.0 or greater. \n\nTLS must be enabled and non-FIPS-approved SSL versions must be disabled. NIST SP 800-52 specifies the preferred configurations for government systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108773","V-99669","CCI-000803"],"reference_identifier":"5811","uuid":"c625dde5-25e8-4f55-b078-6d843a6cab0f","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-223298","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223298","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223298","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223298r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223298","rule_version":"O365-CO-000016","rule_title":"User name and password must be disabled in all Office programs.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security \"Disable user name and password\" to \"Enabled\" and select the check boxes for  all installed Office programs.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security \"Disable user name and password\" is set to \"Enabled\" and the check box is selected for every installed Office program.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_HTTP_USERNAME_PASSWORD_DISABLE\n\nIf the value for all installed programs is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Uniform Resource Locator (URL) standard allows user authentication to be included in URL strings in the form http://username:password@example.com. A malicious user might use this URL syntax to create a hyperlink that appears to open a legitimate website but actually opens a deceptive (spoofed) website. For example, the URL http://www.wingtiptoys.com@example.com appears to open http://www.wingtiptoys.com but actually opens http://example.com. To protect users from such attacks, Internet Explorer usually blocks any URLs using this syntax.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108775","V-99671","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"7984","uuid":"81d91fc9-59c0-48e2-b137-0224b6268937","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 3B393A83B2842AED8998979DA8DBD91C2C9A3E7A\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'User name and password must be disabled in all Office programs.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223299","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223299","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223299","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223299r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223299","rule_version":"O365-CO-000017","rule_title":"The Information Bar must be enabled in all Office programs.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Information Bar to \"Enabled\" and select the check boxes for  all installed Office programs.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Information Bar is set to \"Enabled\" and the check box is selected for every installed Office program.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\software\\microsoft\\internet explorer\\main\\featurecontrol\\feature_securityband\n\nIf the value for all installed programs is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether Office 365 ProPlus applications notify users when potentially unsafe features or content are detected, or whether such features or content are silently disabled without notification. The Message Bar in Office 2016 applications is used to identify security issues, such as unsigned macros or potentially unsafe add-ins. When such issues are detected, the application disables the unsafe feature or content and displays the Message Bar at the top of the active window. The Message Bar informs the users about the nature of the security issue and, in some cases, provides the users with an option to enable the potentially unsafe feature or content, which could harm the user's computer. \n\nIf you enable this policy setting, Office 365 ProPlus applications do not display information in the Message Bar about potentially unsafe content that has been detected or has automatically been blocked. \n\nIf you disable this policy setting, Office 365 ProPlus applications display information in the Message Bar about content that has automatically been blocked. \n\nIf you do not configure this policy setting, if an Office 365 ProPlus application detects a security issue, the Message Bar is displayed. However, this configuration can be modified by users in the Trust Center.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108777","V-99673","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"5275","uuid":"5608b40a-a32c-4501-98ee-a38378da34aa","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 37BC5B031AA362DA62BB0139A966CB0FC609163C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Information Bar must be enabled in all Office programs.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223300","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223300","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223300","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","rule_id_src":"SV-223300r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223300","rule_version":"O365-CO-000018","rule_title":"The Local Machine Zone Lockdown Security must be enabled in all Office programs.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Local Machine Zone Lockdown to \"Enabled\" and select the check boxes for  all installed Office programs.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Local Machine Zone Lockdown Security is set to \"Enabled\" and the check box is selected for every installed Office program.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\software\\microsoft\\internet explorer\\main\\featurecontrol\\feature_localmachine_lockdown\n\nIf the value for all installed Office programs is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Internet Explorer places restrictions on each web page users can use the browser to open. Web pages on a user's local computer have the fewest security restrictions and reside in the Local Machine zone, making this security zone a prime target for malicious users and code. Disabling or not configuring this setting could allow pages in the Internet zone to navigate to pages in the Local Machine zone to then run code to elevate privileges. This could allow malicious code or users to become active on user computers or the network.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108779","V-99675","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6338","uuid":"faadde8c-0fb3-421b-9946-85bf45d605bb","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F3CF26A9F34D33EF4C241C7409ABA4C41385A6D8\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Local Machine Zone Lockdown Security must be enabled in all Office programs.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223301","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223301","title":"SRG-APP-000179","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223301","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000179","rule_id_src":"SV-223301r961050_rule","rule_id":"SV-223301","rule_version":"O365-CO-000019","rule_title":"The MIME Sniffing safety feature must be enabled in all Office programs.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Mime Sniffing Safety Feature to \"Enabled\" for all installed Office programs.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Mime Sniffing Safety Feature is set to \"Enabled\" and the check box is selected for every installed Office program.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\software\\microsoft\\internet explorer\\main\\featurecontrol\\feature_mime_sniffing\n\nIf the value for all installed Office Programs is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Encryption is only as good as the encryption modules utilized. Unapproved cryptographic module algorithms cannot be verified and cannot be relied upon to provide confidentiality or integrity, and DoD data may be compromised due to weak algorithms. The use of TLS provides confidentiality of data in transit between the application server and client. FIPS 140-2 approved TLS versions include TLS V1.0 or greater. \n\nTLS must be enabled and non-FIPS-approved SSL versions must be disabled. NIST SP 800-52 specifies the preferred configurations for government systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108781","V-99677","CCI-000803"],"reference_identifier":"7642","uuid":"ab6cbf6d-5879-43cc-b6dd-34f72f03a240","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F65B3D7ABE86D9CF7D1C6ECC7AB68B7215E7EEDE\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'The MIME Sniffing safety feature must be enabled in all Office programs.' is not present or not in use on this Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223302","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223302","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223302","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223302r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223302","rule_version":"O365-CO-000020","rule_title":"Navigate URL must be enabled in all Office programs.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Navigate URL to \"Enabled\" and select the check boxes for all installed Office programs.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Navigate URL is set to \"Enabled\" and the check box is selected for every installed Office program.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\software\\microsoft\\internet explorer\\main\\featurecontrol\\feature_validate_navigate_url\n\nIf the value for all installed programs is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"To protect users from attacks, Internet Explorer usually does not attempt to load malformed URLs. This functionality can be controlled separately for instances of Internet Explorer spawned by Office applications (for example, if a user clicks a link in an Office document or selects a menu option that loads a web page). If Internet Explorer attempts to load a malformed URL, a security risk could occur.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108783","V-99679","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"4657","uuid":"9879bda3-502d-47c9-ac1e-0ee6780f5645","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: AF15C7446CC2F4D279E0D5C36F1F7CB8FEFB9837\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Navigate URL must be enabled in all Office programs.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223303","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223303","title":"SRG-APP-000179","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223303","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000179","rule_id_src":"SV-223303r961050_rule","rule_id":"SV-223303","rule_version":"O365-CO-000021","rule_title":"Object Caching Protection must be enabled in all Office programs.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Object Caching Protection to \"Enabled\" and select the check boxes for all installed Office programs.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Object Caching Protection is set to \"Enabled\" and the check box is selected for every installed Office program.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\software\\microsoft\\internet explorer\\main\\featurecontrol\\feature_object_caching\n\nIf the value for all installed programs is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Encryption is only as good as the encryption modules utilized. Unapproved cryptographic module algorithms cannot be verified and cannot be relied upon to provide confidentiality or integrity, and DoD data may be compromised due to weak algorithms. The use of TLS provides confidentiality of data in transit between the application server and client. FIPS 140-2 approved TLS versions include TLS V1.0 or greater. \n\nTLS must be enabled and non-FIPS-approved SSL versions must be disabled. NIST SP 800-52 specifies the preferred configurations for government systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108785","V-99681","CCI-000803"],"reference_identifier":"5082","uuid":"d85b6611-f0ec-4778-bcb3-b745acac2777","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8F417235F99A637A5764855299CC3BA8B37F7F45\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Object Caching Protection must be enabled in all Office programs.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223304","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223304","title":"SRG-APP-000112","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223304","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000112","rule_id_src":"SV-223304r960921_rule","rule_id":"SV-223304","rule_version":"O365-CO-000022","rule_title":"Protection from zone elevation must be enabled in all Office programs.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Protection from Zone Elevation to \"Enabled\" and select the check boxes for all installed Office programs.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Protection from Zone Elevation is set to \"Enabled\" and the check box is selected for every installed Office program.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\software\\microsoft\\internet explorer\\main\\featurecontrol\\feature_zone_elevation\n\nIf the value for all installed programs is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Internet Explorer places restrictions on each web page users can use the browser to open. Web pages on a user's local computer have the fewest security restrictions and reside in the Local Machine zone, making this security zone a prime target for malicious users and code. Disabling or not configuring this setting could allow pages in the Internet zone to navigate to pages in the Local Machine zone to then run code to elevate privileges. This could allow malicious code or users to become active on user computers or the network.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108787","V-99683","CCI-001695"],"reference_identifier":"6946","uuid":"ade894ee-bfa7-4ca9-9cc9-be3d3723f31e","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: AC04A73C1D8035F018B445B29FF2F65B2D4E2865\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Protection from zone elevation must be enabled in all Office programs.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223305","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223305","title":"SRG-APP-000488","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223305","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000488","rule_id_src":"SV-223305r961779_rule","rule_id":"SV-223305","rule_version":"O365-CO-000023","rule_title":"ActiveX installation restriction must be enabled in all Office programs.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Restrict ActiveX Install to \"Enabled\" and select the check boxes for  all installed Office programs.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Restrict ActiveX Install is set to \"Enabled\" and the check box is selected for every installed Office program.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\software\\microsoft\\internet explorer\\main\\featurecontrol\\feature_restrict_activexinstall\n\nIf the value for all installed programs is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Microsoft ActiveX controls allow unmanaged, unprotected code to run on the user computers. ActiveX controls do not run within a protected container in the browser like the other types of HTML or Microsoft Silverlight-based controls. Disabling or not configuring this setting does not block prompts for ActiveX control installations, and these prompts display to users. This could allow malicious code to become active on user computers or the network.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108789","V-99685","CCI-002460"],"reference_identifier":"6094","uuid":"ef9a0d71-c7f3-457d-ab59-c5dc82132b60","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F95DAE16DA24CDE15D7CD21FA2C685BCD77DE5EF\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'ActiveX installation restriction must be enabled in all Office programs.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223306","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223306","title":"SRG-APP-000112","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223306","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000112","rule_id_src":"SV-223306r960921_rule","rule_id":"SV-223306","rule_version":"O365-CO-000024","rule_title":"File Download Restriction must be enabled in all Office programs.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Restrict File Download to \"Enabled\" and select the check boxes for  all installed Office programs.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Restrict File Download is set to \"Enabled\" and the check box is selected for every installed Office program.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\software\\microsoft\\internet explorer\\main\\featurecontrol\\feature_restrict_filedownload\n\nIf the value for all installed programs is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Disabling this setting allows websites to present file download prompts via code without the user specifically initiating the download. User preferences may also allow the download to occur without prompting or interaction with the user. Even if Internet Explorer prompts the user to accept the download, some websites abuse this functionality. Malicious websites may continually prompt users to download a file or present confusing dialog boxes to trick users into downloading or running a file. If the download occurs and it contains malicious code, the code could become active on user computers or the network.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108791","V-99687","CCI-001695"],"reference_identifier":"7953","uuid":"1244060b-9bf4-4722-91ad-e6e0febbea61","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FE8E7978AA7291E0345F340E165C695F0175F486\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'File Download Restriction must be enabled in all Office programs.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223307","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223307","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223307","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223307r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223307","rule_version":"O365-CO-000025","rule_title":"The Save from URL feature must be enabled in all Office programs.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Saved from URL to \"Enabled\" and select the check boxes for  all installed Office programs.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Saved from URL is set to \"Enabled\" and the check box is selected for every installed Office program.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\software\\microsoft\\internet explorer\\main\\featurecontrol\\feature_unc_savedfilecheck\n\nIf the value for all installed programs is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Typically, when Internet Explorer loads a web page from a Universal Naming Convention (UNC) share that contains a Mark of the Web (MOTW) comment, indicating the page was saved from a site on the Internet, Internet Explorer runs the page in the Internet security zone instead of the less restrictive Local Intranet security zone. This functionality can be controlled separately for instances of Internet Explorer spawned by Office applications (for example, if a user clicks a link in an Office document or selects a menu option that loads a web page). If Internet Explorer does not evaluate the page for a MOTW, potentially dangerous code could be allowed to run.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108793","V-99689","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"2329","uuid":"455f7ff9-ee85-4101-98b7-ce9c20906284","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7096E0B5BF16B1D308A002243B70620990A7085E\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Save from URL feature must be enabled in all Office programs.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223308","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223308","title":"SRG-APP-000112","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223308","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000112","rule_id_src":"SV-223308r960921_rule","rule_id":"SV-223308","rule_version":"O365-CO-000026","rule_title":"Scripted Windows Security restrictions must be enabled in all Office programs.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >>Scripted Window Security Restrictions to \"Enabled\" and select the check boxes for  all installed Office programs.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Scripted Window Security Restrictions is set to \"Enabled\" and the check box is selected for every installed Office program.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS\n\nIf the value for all installed programs is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Malicious websites often try to confuse or trick users into giving a site permission to perform an action allowing the site to take control of the users' computers in some manner. Disabling or not configuring this setting allows unknown websites to:\n- Create browser windows appearing to be from the local operating system.\n- Draw active windows displaying outside of the viewable areas of the screen capturing keyboard input.\n- Overlay parent windows with their own browser windows to hide important system information, choices, or prompts.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108795","V-99691","CCI-001695"],"reference_identifier":"1779","uuid":"3d3e3a42-4f19-4444-9315-8973e3dd43ce","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2F8D33AA319E92BFD0CB78CF519DAF5D90F94088\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Scripted Windows Security restrictions must be enabled in all Office programs.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223309","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223309","title":"SRG-APP-000488","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223309","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000488","rule_id_src":"SV-223309r961779_rule","rule_id":"SV-223309","rule_version":"O365-CO-000027","rule_title":"Flash player activation must be disabled in all Office programs.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MS Security Guide >> Block Flash activation in Office documents >> Enabled >> Block all activation to \"Enabled\" (Block all activation).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MS Security Guide >> Block Flash activation in Office documents >> Enabled >> Block all activation is set to \"Enabled\" Block all activation.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Office\\Common\\COM Compatibility\n\nIf the value for COMMENT is REG_SZ = Block all Flash activation, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether the Adobe Flash control can be activated by Office documents. Note that activation blocking applies only within Office processes.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can choose from three options to control whether and how Flash is blocked from activation:\n\n1. \"Block all activation\" prevents the Flash control from being loaded, whether directly referenced by the document or indirectly by another embedded object.\n2. \"Block embedding/linking, allow other activation\" prevents the Flash control from being loaded when directly referenced by the document, but does not prevent activation through another object.\n3. \"Allow all activation\" restores Office's default behavior, allowing the Flash control to be activated.\n\nBecause this setting is not a true Group Policy setting and \"tattoos\" the registry, enabling the \"Allow all activation\" option is the only way to restore default behavior after either of the \"Block\" options has been applied. It is not recommended to configure this setting to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\" after it has been enabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108797","V-99693","CCI-002460"],"reference_identifier":"3573","uuid":"99d0c491-a52a-49c6-bc2b-5b88e41fdca0","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6F69067B16F435CAAA5242B7F8A3D35B633F8B18\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Flash player activation must be disabled in all Office programs.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223310","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223310","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223310","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223310r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223310","rule_version":"O365-EX-000001","rule_title":"Trusted Locations on the network must be disabled in Excel.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Trusted Locations \"Allow Trusted Locations on the network\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Trusted Locations \"Allow Trusted Locations on the network\" is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\trusted locations\n\nIf the value AllowNetworkLocations is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether trusted locations on the network can be used.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, users can specify trusted locations on network shares or in other remote locations that are not under their direct control by selecting the \"Allow Trusted Locations on my network (not recommended)\" check box in the Trusted Locations section of the Trust Center. Content, code, and add-ins are allowed to load from trusted locations with minimal security and without prompting the user for permission.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the selected application ignores any network locations listed in the Trusted Locations section of the Trust Center. Disabling this policy setting does not delete any network locations from the Trusted Locations list. Instead, it forces the selected application to treat the locations as non-trusted and prevents users from adding new network locations to the list.\n\nIf you also deploy Trusted Locations via Group Policy, you should verify whether any of them are remote locations. If any of them are remote locations and you do not allow remote locations via this policy setting, those policy keys that point to remote locations will be ignored on client computers.\n\nDisabling this policy setting will cause disruption for users who add network locations to the Trusted Locations list. However, it is not recommended to enable this policy setting (as the \"Allow Trusted Locations on my network (not recommended)\" check box itself states), so in practice it should be possible to disable this policy setting in most situations without causing significant usability issues for most users.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108799","V-99695","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"1727","uuid":"8e8a05d6-e159-405f-9a82-c060b5589875","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2D8904451A8461371369EB1544783A77F97F06AF\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Trusted Locations on the network must be disabled in Excel.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223311","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223311","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223311","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223311r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223311","rule_version":"O365-EX-000002","rule_title":"VBA Macros not digitally signed must be blocked in Excel.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> \"Macro Notification Settings\" is set to \"Enabled\" and select \"Disable VBA macros except digitally signed macros\" from the Options.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> \"Macro Notification Settings\" is set to \"Enabled\" and \"Disable VBA macros except digitally signed macros\" from the Options is selected.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\Microsoft\\office\\16.0\\excel\\security\n\nIf the value vbawarnings is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding. A value of REG_DWORD =  4 is also acceptable. If the registry key does not exist or is not configured properly, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls how the specified applications warn users when Visual Basic for Applications (VBA) macros are present.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can choose from four options for determining how the specified applications will warn the user about macros:\n\n- Disable all with notification: The application displays the Trust Bar for all macros, whether signed or unsigned. This option enforces the default configuration in Office. This option also allows users to potentially enable unsigned/untrusted macros.  If a site requires the use of macros, they must be signed /approved and added to appropriate locations listed in the Trust Center Settings. \n- Disable all except digitally signed macros: The application displays the Trust Bar for digitally signed macros, allowing users to enable them or leave them disabled. Any unsigned macros are disabled, and users are not notified.\n- Disable all without notification: The application disables all macros, whether signed or unsigned, and does not notify users.\n- Enable all macros (not recommended): All macros are enabled, whether signed or unsigned. This option can significantly reduce security by allowing dangerous code to run undetected.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108801","V-99697","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"6589","uuid":"9b4c0ff3-3f09-41e6-8e0a-2d0b3306c06f","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 084BB53E870FBE7018985608504276B727DBD46F\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'VBA Macros not digitally signed must be blocked in Excel.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223312","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223312","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223312","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223312r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223312","rule_version":"O365-EX-000003","rule_title":"Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server launch in Excel must be blocked.","fix_text":"Set policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> External Content >> Don't allow Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server launch in Excel to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> External Content >> Don't allow Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server launch in Excel is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\external content\n\nIf the value for \"disableddeserverlaunch\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to control whether Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server launch is allowed.\n\nBy default, DDE server launch is turned off, but users can turn on DDE server launch by going to File >> Options >> Trust Center >> Trust Center Settings >> External Content.\n\nFor security reasons, turning on DDE server launch is not recommended.\n\nNote: For DDE server launch to work, Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server lookup must be turned on. Be sure that the \u201cDon't allow Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server lookup\u201d policy setting is not enabled, because enabling that policy setting turns off DDE server lookup.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, DDE server launch is not allowed, and users cannot turn on DDE server launch in the Trust Center.\n\nIf you disable this policy setting, DDE server launch is allowed, and users cannot turn off DDE server launch in the Trust Center. For security reasons, this is not recommended.\n\nIf you do not configure this policy setting, DDE server launch is turned off, but users can turn on DDE server launch in the Trust Center.\n\nNote: This policy setting only applies to subscription versions of Office, such as Office 365 ProPlus.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108803","V-99699","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"1923","uuid":"9bbe913b-0ade-4ebf-80e8-53b44722e50f","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 90652686E41DDBF22E0E85379FBABF4613A7F0B0\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server launch in Excel must be blocked.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223313","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223313","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223313","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223313r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223313","rule_version":"O365-EX-000004","rule_title":"Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server lookup in Excel must be blocked.","fix_text":"Set policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> External Content >> Don't allow Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server lookup in Excel to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> External Content >> Don't allow Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server lookup in Excel is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\external content\n\nIf the value for \"disableddeserverlookup\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to control whether Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server lookup is allowed.\n\nBy default, DDE server lookup is turned on, but users can turn off DDE server lookup by going to File >> Options >> Trust Center >> Trust Center Settings >> External Content.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, DDE server lookup is not allowed, and users cannot turn on DDE server lookup in the Trust Center.\n\nNote: If you are using Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server launch, which is not recommended, do not enable this policy setting, because DDE server launch requires DDE server lookup to be on.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, DDE server lookup is turned on, but users can turn off DDE server lookup in the Trust Center.\n\nNote: This policy setting only applies to subscription versions of Office, such as Office 365 ProPlus.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108805","V-99701","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"3602","uuid":"9e90a2fd-6921-4cef-9956-0a4df64a89c6","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C38595D0A567BB3AB68D42A1246DC16EA51EE836\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server lookup in Excel must be blocked.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223314","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223314","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223314","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223314r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223314","rule_version":"O365-EX-000005","rule_title":"Open/save of dBase III / IV format files must be blocked.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings \"dBase III / IV files\" to \"Enabled: Open/Save blocked, use open policy\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings \"dBase III / IV files\" is set to \"Enabled: Open/Save blocked, use open policy\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\fileblock\n\nIf the value DBaseFiles is REG_DWORD = 2, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to determine whether users can open, view, edit, or save Excel files with the format specified by the title of this policy setting.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can specify whether users can open, view, edit, or save files.\n\nThe options that can be selected are below. Note: Not all options may be available for this policy setting.\n\n- Do not block: The file type will not be blocked.\n- Save blocked: Saving of the file type will be blocked.\n- Open/Save blocked, use open policy: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked. The file will open based on the policy setting configured in the \"default file block behavior\" key.\n- Block: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the file will not open.\n- Open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit the file type will not be enabled.\n- Allow editing and open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit will be enabled.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the file type will not be blocked.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108807","V-99703","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"2207","uuid":"10d70b26-8926-4259-9d3a-41f445947484","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 56E209DA9E670E3C9632747B19A763AC022EE85D\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Open/save of dBase III / IV format files must be blocked.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223315","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223315","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223315","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223315r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223315","rule_version":"O365-EX-000006","rule_title":"Open/save of Dif and Sylk format files must be blocked.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings \"Dif and Sylk files\" to \"Enabled: Open/Save blocked, use open policy\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings \"Dif and Sylk files\" is set to \"Enabled: Open/Save blocked, use open policy\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\fileblock\n\nIf the value DifandSylkFiles is REG_DWORD = 2, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to determine whether users can open, view, edit, or save Excel files with the format specified by the title of this policy setting. If you enable this policy setting, you can specify whether users can open, view, edit, or save files. The options that can be selected are below. Note: Not all options may be available for this policy setting.\n\n- Do not block: The file type will not be blocked.\n- Save blocked: Saving of the file type will be blocked.\n- Open/Save blocked, use open policy: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked. The file will open based on the policy setting configured in the \"default file block behavior\" key.\n- Block: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the file will not open.\n- Open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit the file type will not be enabled.\n- Allow editing and open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit will be enabled. \n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the file type will not be blocked.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108809","V-99705","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"2539","uuid":"527b3c4a-9687-425b-9476-2403a25d3cb9","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A8F11555418838CE56F00A911F62E0DC390D591F\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Open/save of Dif and Sylk format files must be blocked.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223316","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223316","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223316","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223316r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223316","rule_version":"O365-EX-000007","rule_title":"Open/save of Excel 2 macrosheets and add-in files must be blocked.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings \"Excel 2 macrosheets and add-in files\" to \"Enabled: Open/Save blocked, use open policy\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings \"Excel 2 macrosheets and add-in files\" is set to \"Enabled: Open/Save blocked, use open policy\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\fileblock\n\nIf the value XL2Macros is REG_DWORD = 2, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to determine whether users can open, view, edit, or save Excel files with the format specified by the title of this policy setting. If you enable this policy setting, you can specify whether users can open, view, edit, or save files. The options that can be selected are below. Note: Not all options may be available for this policy setting.\n\n- Do not block: The file type will not be blocked.\n- Save blocked: Saving of the file type will be blocked.\n- Open/Save blocked, use open policy: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked. The file will open based on the policy setting configured in the \"default file block behavior\" key.\n- Block: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the file will not open.\n- Open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit the file type will not be enabled.\n- Allow editing and open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit will be enabled. \n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the file type will not be blocked.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108811","V-99707","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"2717","uuid":"479dcbb8-2ea9-4dd6-9aa5-d2afbab5c742","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 64FCE9830B187A79FC83CC62B05196D55A21B563\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Open/save of Excel 2 macrosheets and add-in files must be blocked.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223317","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223317","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223317","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223317r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223317","rule_version":"O365-EX-000008","rule_title":"Open/save of Excel 2 worksheets must be blocked.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings \"Excel 2 worksheets\" to \"Enabled: Open/Save blocked, use open policy\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings \"Excel 2 worksheets\" is set to \"Enabled: Open/Save blocked, use open policy\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\fileblock\n\nIf the value XL2Worksheets is REG_DWORD = 2, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to determine whether users can open, view, edit, or save Excel files with the format specified by the title of this policy setting. If you enable this policy setting, you can specify whether users can open, view, edit, or save files. The options that can be selected are below. Note: Not all options may be available for this policy setting.\n\n- Do not block: The file type will not be blocked.\n- Save blocked: Saving of the file type will be blocked.\n- Open/Save blocked, use open policy: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked. The file will open based on the policy setting configured in the \"default file block behavior\" key.\n- Block: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the file will not open.\n- Open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit the file type will not be enabled.\n- Allow editing and open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit will be enabled. \n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the file type will not be blocked.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108813","V-99709","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"2126","uuid":"d782c4bd-8e85-48b0-a13d-fdb8dc377ebe","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FD3F1A3FFBE5597D717140508D92B1967DB1F4C7\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Open/save of Excel 2 worksheets must be blocked.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223318","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223318","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223318","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223318r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223318","rule_version":"O365-EX-000009","rule_title":"Open/save of Excel 3 macrosheets and add-in files must be blocked.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings \"Excel 3 macrosheets and add-in files\" to \"Enabled: Open/Save blocked, use open policy\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings \"Excel 3 macrosheets and add-in files\" is set to \"Enabled: Open/Save blocked, use open policy\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\fileblock\n\nIf the value XL3Macros is REG_DWORD = 2, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to determine whether users can open, view, edit, or save Excel files with the format specified by the title of this policy setting. If you enable this policy setting, you can specify whether users can open, view, edit, or save files. The options that can be selected are below. Note: Not all options may be available for this policy setting.\n\n- Do not block: The file type will not be blocked.\n- Save blocked: Saving of the file type will be blocked.\n- Open/Save blocked, use open policy: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked. The file will open based on the policy setting configured in the \"default file block behavior\" key.\n- Block: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the file will not open.\n- Open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit the file type will not be enabled.\n- Allow editing and open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit will be enabled. \n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the file type will not be blocked.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108815","V-99711","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"1878","uuid":"97c4adcf-e5ea-4e0b-9e36-ed17ee5fc043","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C880B0E288A14B47C1DCADD4710C7F75D2499635\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Open/save of Excel 3 macrosheets and add-in files must be blocked.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223319","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223319","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223319","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223319r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223319","rule_version":"O365-EX-000010","rule_title":"Open/save of Excel 3 worksheets must be blocked.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings \"Excel 3 worksheets\" to \"Enabled: Open/Save blocked, use open policy\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings \"Excel 3 worksheets\" is set to \"Enabled: Open/Save blocked, use open policy\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\fileblock\n\nIf the value XL3Worksheets is REG_DWORD = 2, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsof