pecified by the title of this policy setting. If you enable this policy setting, you can specify whether users can open, view, edit, or save files. The options that can be selected are below. Note: Not all options may be available for this policy setting.\n\n- Do not block: The file type will not be blocked.\n- Save blocked: Saving of the file type will be blocked.\n- Open/Save blocked, use open policy: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked. The file will open based on the policy setting configured in the \"default file block behavior\" key.\n- Block: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the file will not open.\n- Open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit the file type will not be enabled.\n- Allow editing and open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit will be enabled. \n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the file type will not be blocked.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108827","V-99723","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"4265","uuid":"61b1e6b4-e3e6-4c72-a270-05dc74505bc0","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 88F0B2147915EB7FC7A8170C742BF40C5AFD8448\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Open/save of Excel 95-97 workbooks and templates must be blocked.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223325","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223325","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223325","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223325r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223325","rule_version":"O365-EX-000016","rule_title":"The default file block behavior must be set to not open blocked files in Excel.","fix_text":"Set policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings >> Set default file block behavior to \"Enabled:Blocked files are not opened\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings >> Set default file block behavior is set to \"Blocked files are not opened\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\fileblock\n\nIf the value OpenInProtectedView is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to determine whether users can open, view, edit, or save Excel files with the format specified by the title of this policy setting. If you enable this policy setting, you can specify whether users can open, view, edit, or save files. The options that can be selected are below. Note: Not all options may be available for this policy setting.\n\n- Do not block: The file type will not be blocked.\n- Save blocked: Saving of the file type will be blocked.\n- Open/Save blocked, use open policy: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked. The file will open based on the policy setting configured in the \"default file block behavior\" key.\n- Block: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the file will not open.\n- Open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit the file type will not be enabled.\n- Allow editing and open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit will be enabled. \n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the file type will not be blocked.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108829","V-99725","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"4646","uuid":"e48310f8-49bd-434f-b65e-c7775a8924bd","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: CFF626ECAE86590525CBBC20772DDA8087526BD9\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The default file block behavior must be set to not open blocked files in Excel.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223326","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223326","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223326","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223326r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223326","rule_version":"O365-EX-000017","rule_title":"Open/save of Web pages and Excel 2003 XML spreadsheets must be blocked.","fix_text":"Set policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings >> Web pages and Excel 2003 XML spreadsheets to \"Open/Save blocked, use open policy\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings >> Web pages and Excel 2003 XML spreadsheets is set to \"Open/Save blocked, use open policy\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\fileblock\n\nIf the value for htmlandxmlssfiles is REG_DWORD = 2, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to determine whether users can open, view, edit, or save Excel files with the format specified by the title of this policy setting. If you enable this policy setting, you can specify whether users can open, view, edit, or save files. The options that can be selected are below. Note: Not all options may be available for this policy setting.\n\n- Do not block: The file type will not be blocked.\n- Save blocked: Saving of the file type will be blocked.\n- Open/Save blocked, use open policy: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked. The file will open based on the policy setting configured in the \"default file block behavior\" key.\n- Block: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the file will not open.\n- Open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit the file type will not be enabled.\n- Allow editing and open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit will be enabled. \n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the file type will not be blocked.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108831","V-99727","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"9254","uuid":"888f0db8-f1d3-4ee8-82a6-d312dfadf392","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: EC5E749932DE412BC571B47478427E67C5B467DC\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Open/save of Web pages and Excel 2003 XML spreadsheets must be blocked.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223327","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223327","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223327","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223327r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223327","rule_version":"O365-EX-000018","rule_title":"Extraction options must be blocked when opening corrupt Excel workbooks.","fix_text":"Set policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Data Recovery >> Do not show data extraction options when opening corrupt workbooks to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Data Recovery >> Do not show data extraction options when opening corrupt workbooks is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\excel\\options\n\nIf the value for extractdatadisableui is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether Excel presents users with a list of data extraction options before beginning an Open and Repair operation when users choose to open a corrupt workbook in repair or extract mode.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, Excel opens the file using the Safe Load process and does not prompt users to choose between repairing or extracting data.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Excel prompts the user to select either to repair or to extract data, and to select either to convert to values or to recover formulas.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108833","V-99729","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"3563","uuid":"7e6c8141-13d4-48e4-a9a6-ff51fa1806cb","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-223328","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223328","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223328","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223328r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223328","rule_version":"O365-EX-000019","rule_title":"Updating of links in Excel must be prompted and not automatic.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Advanced >> Ask to update automatic links to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Advanced >> Ask to update automatic links is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\excel\\options\\binaryoptions\n\nIf the value for fupdateext_78_1 is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether Excel prompts users to update automatic links, or whether the updates occur in the background with no prompt.\n\nIf you enable or do not configure this policy setting, Excel will prompt users to update automatic links. In addition, the \"Ask to update automatic links\" user interface option under File tab >> Advanced >> General is selected.\n\nIf you disable this policy setting, Excel updates automatic links without prompting or informing users, which could compromise the integrity of some of the information in the workbook.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108835","V-99731","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3622","uuid":"9f7e748e-0a86-406c-9345-d1844a2d7220","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 35D37F3F20F450334577331C2C0F6B4FE210C286\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Updating of links in Excel must be prompted and not automatic.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223329","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223329","title":"SRG-APP-000488","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223329","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000488","rule_id_src":"SV-223329r961779_rule","rule_id":"SV-223329","rule_version":"O365-EX-000020","rule_title":"Loading of pictures from Web pages not created in Excel must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Advanced >> Web Options... >> General >> Load pictures from Web pages not created in Excel to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Advanced >> Web Options... >> General.\n\nLoad pictures from Web pages not created in Excel is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\excel\\internet\n\nIf the value for donotloadpictures is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether Excel loads graphics when opening Web pages that were not created in Excel. It configures the \"Load pictures from Web pages not created in Excel\" option under the File tab >> Options >> Advanced >> General >> Web Options... >> General tab.\n\nIf you enable or do not configure this policy setting, Excel loads any graphics that are included in the pages, regardless of whether they were originally created in Excel.\n\nIf you disable this policy setting, Excel will not load any pictures from Web pages that were not created in Excel.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108837","V-99733","CCI-002460"],"reference_identifier":"3077","uuid":"b4244e6d-2663-4fac-b577-f17a59a18fe1","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 70F17E0C3FEE816CB3161C4D97F65EC4D0CDAC9C\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Loading of pictures from Web pages not created in Excel must be disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223330","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223330","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223330","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","rule_id_src":"SV-223330r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223330","rule_version":"O365-EX-000021","rule_title":"AutoRepublish in Excel must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Save >> Disable AutoRepublish to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Save >> Disable AutoRepublish is to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\excel\\options\n\nIf the value for disableautorepublish is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows administrators to disable the AutoRepublish feature in Excel. If users choose to publish Excel data to a static Web page and enable the AutoRepublish feature, Excel saves a copy of the data to the Web page every time the user saves the workbook. By default, a message dialog displays every time the user saves a published workbook when AutoRepublish is enabled. From this dialog, the user can disable AutoRepublish temporarily or permanently, or select \"Do not show this message again\" to prevent the dialog from appearing after every save. If the user selects \"Do not show this message again\", Excel will continue to automatically republish the data after every save without informing the user.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, the AutoRepublish feature is turned off and Excel users will need to publish data to the Web manually.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, users can enable the AutoRepublish feature to automatically republish workbooks saved as type Web Page.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108839","V-99735","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1689","uuid":"df0444dd-1970-4d57-8cf4-cf343a76887d","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 57A3F26C96A6026A0D3FAF41683409EC9A5DD015\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'AutoRepublish in Excel must be disabled.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223331","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223331","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223331","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","rule_id_src":"SV-223331r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223331","rule_version":"O365-EX-000022","rule_title":"AutoRepublish warning alert in Excel must be enabled.","fix_text":"Set policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Save >> Do not show AutoRepublish warning alert to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Save >> Do not show AutoRepublish warning alert is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\excel\\options\n\nIf value for disableautorepublishwarning is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows administrators to disable the AutoRepublish feature in Excel. If users choose to publish Excel data to a static Web page and enable the AutoRepublish feature, Excel saves a copy of the data to the Web page every time the user saves the workbook. By default, a message dialog displays every time the user saves a published workbook when AutoRepublish is enabled. From this dialog, the user can disable AutoRepublish temporarily or permanently, or select \"Do not show this message again\" to prevent the dialog from appearing after every save. If the user selects \"Do not show this message again\", Excel will continue to automatically republish the data after every save without informing the user.\n \nIf you enable this policy setting, the AutoRepublish feature is turned off and Excel users will need to publish data to the Web manually.\n \nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, users can enable the AutoRepublish feature to automatically republish workbooks saved as type Web Page.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108841","V-99737","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2638","uuid":"90f9f36d-eb33-47ed-937a-ac7ff61e0788","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 397F7A7A568F427AE5F8BF2A225AD1AB9763555F\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'AutoRepublish warning alert in Excel must be enabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223332","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223332","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223332","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","rule_id_src":"SV-223332r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223332","rule_version":"O365-EX-000023","rule_title":"File extensions must be enabled to match file types in Excel.","fix_text":"Set policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Force file extension to match file type to \"Enabled\" and select the option \"Always match file type\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Force file extension to match file type is set to \"Always match file type\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\excel\\security\n\nIf value for extensionhardening is REG_DWORD = 2, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls how Excel loads file types that do not match their extension. Excel can load files with extensions that do not match the files' type. For example, if a comma-separated values (CSV) file named example.csv is renamed example.xls (or any other file extension supported by Excel 2003 and earlier only), Excel can properly load it as a CSV file.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can choose from three options for working with files that have non-matching extensions:\n- Allow different - Excel opens the files properly without warning users that the files have non-matching extensions. If users subsequently edit and save the files, Excel preserves both the true, underlying file format and the incorrect file extension.\n- Allow different, but warn - Excel opens the files properly, but warns users about the file type mismatch. This option is the default configuration in Excel.\n- Always match file type - Excel does not open any files that have non-matching extensions.\n\nIf this policy setting is disabled or not configured or if users attempt to open files with the wrong extension, Excel opens the file and displays a warning that the file type is not what Excel expected.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108843","V-99739","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6226","uuid":"f0869d3c-20b2-41ca-9781-d74354bf9a91","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 798785E1F816903DC2695C06A34C8F1620F779C1\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'File extensions must be enabled to match file types in Excel.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223333","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223333","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223333","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223333r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223333","rule_version":"O365-EX-000024","rule_title":"Scan of encrypted macros in Excel Open XML workbooks must be enabled.","fix_text":"Set policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Scan encrypted macros in Excel Open XML workbooks to \"Scan encrypted macros (default)\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Scan encrypted macros in Excel Open XML workbooks is set to \"Scan encrypted macros (default)\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\excel\\security\n\nIf the value excelbypassencryptedmacroscan does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value for excelbypassencryptedmacroscan is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether encrypted macros in Open XML workbooks be are required to be scanned with anti-virus software before being opened.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you may choose one of these options:\n- Scan encrypted macros: encrypted macros are disabled unless anti-virus software is installed. Encrypted macros are scanned by your anti-virus software when you attempt to open an encrypted workbook that contains macros.\n- Scan if anti-virus software available: if anti-virus software is installed, scan the encrypted macros first before allowing them to load. If anti-virus software is not available, allow encrypted macros to load.\n- Load macros without scanning: do not check for anti-virus software and allow macros to be loaded in an encrypted file.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the behavior will be similar to the \"Scan encrypted macros\" option.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108845","V-99741","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"2185","uuid":"1cf58363-3cbc-40cf-b82e-2c484fda09f6","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FA0EFC0795C4143B6B7263B7D09E784E508F8CB2\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Scan of encrypted macros in Excel Open XML workbooks must be enabled.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223334","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223334","title":"SRG-APP-000112","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223334","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000112","rule_id_src":"SV-223334r960921_rule","rule_id":"SV-223334","rule_version":"O365-EX-000025","rule_title":"File validation in Excel must be enabled.","fix_text":"Set policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Turn off file validation to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Turn off file validation is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\filevalidation\n\nIf the value for enableonload is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you turn off the file validation feature.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, file validation will be turned off.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, file validation will be turned on. Office Binary Documents (97-2003) are checked to see if they conform against the file format schema before they are opened.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108847","V-99743","CCI-001695"],"reference_identifier":"6360","uuid":"6960009a-9440-4046-8464-b394e7bb644e","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4AFA2B7EB2053D13F6171BDF95E5779BC8D6AA71\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'File validation in Excel must be enabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223335","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223335","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223335","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223335r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223335","rule_version":"O365-EX-000026","rule_title":"WEBSERVICE Function Notification in Excel must be configured to disable all, with notifications.","fix_text":"Set policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> WEBSERVICE Function Notification Settings to \"Enabled\" and \"Disable all with notification\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> WEBSERVICE Function Notification Settings is set to \"Enabled\" and \"Disable all with notification\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\excel\\security\n\nIf the value webservicefunctionwarnings does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value for webservicefunctionwarnings is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value for webservicefunctionwarnings is REG_DWORD = 2, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls how Excel will warn users when WEBSERVICE functions are present.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can choose from three options for determining how the specified applications will warn the user about WEBSERVICE functions:\n- Disable all with notification: The application displays the Trust Bar for all WEBSERVICE functions. This option enforces the default configuration in Office.\n- Disable all without notification: The application disables all WEBSERVICE functions and does not notify users.\n- Enable all WEBSERVICE functions (not recommended): The application enables all WEBSERVICE functions and does not notify users. This option can significantly reduce security by allowing information disclosure to third-party web services.\n\nIf you disable this policy setting, the \u201cDisable all with notification\u201d will be the default setting.\n\nIf you do not configure this policy setting, when users open workbooks that contain WEBSERVICE functions, Excel will open the files with the WEBSERVICE functions disabled and display the Trust Bar with a warning that WEBSERVICE functions are present and have been disabled. Users can inspect and edit the files if appropriate, but cannot use any disabled functionality until they enable it by clicking \"Enable Content\" on the Trust Bar. If the user clicks \"Enable Content,\" then the document is added as a trusted document.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108849","V-99745","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"5119","uuid":"9e9cd50b-8f42-4000-87e7-32252f714b3f","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0000D6CB5F12F402963A367C24239A7292D918E4\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'WEBSERVICE Function Notification in Excel must be configured to disable all, with notifications.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223336","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223336","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223336","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223336r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223336","rule_version":"O365-EX-000027","rule_title":"Macros must be blocked from running in Excel files from the Internet.","fix_text":"Set policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Block macros from running in Office files from the Internet to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Block macros from running in Office files from the Internet is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\excel\\security\n\nIf the value blockcontentexecutionfrominternet is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to block macros from running in Office files that come from the Internet.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, macros are blocked from running, even if \u201cEnable all macros\u201d is selected in the Macro Settings section of the Trust Center. Also, instead of having the choice to \u201cEnable Content\u201d, users will receive a notification that macros are blocked from running. If the Office file is saved to a trusted location or was previously trusted by the user, macros will be allowed to run.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the settings configured in the Macro Settings section of the Trust Center determine whether macros run in Office files that come from the Internet.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108851","V-99747","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3617","uuid":"4857967b-9c0e-4c8b-96e3-deba674b0c3a","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A29784C81F5AF1A8A12FD4E72A2B6BC83A3D57C7\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Macros must be blocked from running in Excel files from the Internet.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223337","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223337","title":"SRG-APP-000131","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223337","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000131","rule_id_src":"SV-223337r1016168_rule","rule_id":"SV-223337","rule_version":"O365-EX-000028","rule_title":"Trust Bar notification must be enabled for unsigned application add-ins in Excel and blocked.","fix_text":"Set policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Disable Trust Bar Notification for unsigned application add-ins and block them to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Disable Trust Bar Notification for unsigned application add-ins and block them is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\excel\\security\n\nIf the value for notbpromptunsignedaddin is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether the specified Office 2016 applications notify users when unsigned application add-ins are loaded or silently disable such add-ins without notification. This policy setting only applies if the ''Require that application add-ins are signed by Trusted Publisher'' policy setting is enabled, which prevents users from changing this policy setting.\n\nIf this policy setting is enabled, applications automatically disable unsigned add-ins without informing users.\n \nIf this policy setting is disabled, if an application is configured to require that all add-ins be signed by a trusted publisher, any unsigned add-ins the application loads will be disabled and the application will display the Trust Bar at the top of the active window. The Trust Bar contains a message that informs users about the unsigned add-in.\n\nIf this policy setting is not configured, the disable behavior applies, and in addition, users can configure this requirement themselves in the ''Add-ins'' category of the Trust Center for the application.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108853","V-99749","CCI-003992","CCI-001749"],"reference_identifier":"4297","uuid":"b46e1e93-2274-4b10-b118-b18bedf892e6","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9F8B8EA98B891A2B62516243792BDD6540DEAEE7\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Trust Bar notification must be enabled for unsigned application add-ins in Excel and blocked.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223338","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223338","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223338","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223338r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223338","rule_version":"O365-EX-000029","rule_title":"Untrusted Microsoft Query files must be blocked from opening in Excel.","fix_text":"Set policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> External Content >> Always prevent untrusted Microsoft Query files from opening to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> External Content >> Always prevent untrusted Microsoft Query files from opening is set to \"Enabled\".\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\external content.\nValue for enableblockunsecurequeryfiles should be REG_DWORD = 1\n\nIf the value for enableblockunsecurequeryfiles is Reg_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether Microsoft Query files (.iqy, oqy, .dqy, and .rqy) in an untrusted location are prevented from opening.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, Microsoft Query files in an untrusted location are prevented from opening. Users will not be able to change this setting under File >> Options >> Trust Center >> Trust Center Settings >> External Content.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Microsoft Query files in an untrusted location are not prevented from opening, unless users have changed this setting in the Trust Center.\n\nNote: This policy setting only applies to subscription versions of Office, such as Office 365 ProPlus.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108855","V-99751","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"2951","uuid":"999d8353-8446-43a7-b0b0-9147b842dbac","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BEA74B105DF46CB75F916CCFF6C06DCD35760D4C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Untrusted Microsoft Query files must be blocked from opening in Excel.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223339","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223339","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223339","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223339r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223339","rule_version":"O365-EX-000030","rule_title":"Untrusted database files must be opened in Excel in Protected View mode.","fix_text":"Set policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Protected View >> Always open untrusted database files in Protected View to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Protected View >> Always open untrusted database files in Protected View is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\protectedview\n\nIf the value for enabledatabasefileprotectedview is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether database files (.dbf) opened from an untrusted location are always opened in Protected View.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, database files opened from an untrusted location are always opened in Protected View. Users will not be able to change this setting under File >> Options >> Trust Center >> Trust Center Settings >> Protected View.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, database files opened from an untrusted location are not opened in Protected View, unless users have changed this setting in the Trust Center.\n\nNote: This policy setting only applies to subscription versions of Office, such as Office 365 ProPlus.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108857","V-99753","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"9190","uuid":"eee6524b-383e-44be-be22-c38825c8b9cb","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-223340","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223340","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223340","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223340r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223340","rule_version":"O365-EX-000031","rule_title":"Files from Internet zone must be opened in Excel in Protected View mode.","fix_text":"Set policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Protected View >> Do not open files from the Internet zone in Protected View to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Protected View >> Do not open files from the Internet zone in Protected View is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\protectedview\n\nIf the value DisableInternetFilesInPV is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding. \n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is REG_DWORD = 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to determine if files downloaded from the Internet zone open in Protected View.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, files downloaded from the Internet zone do not open in Protected View.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, files downloaded from the Internet zone open in Protected View.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108859","V-99755","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"5601","uuid":"fa3b4313-1710-41e6-9362-a33d57304cd9","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 66102B37354FEFAE3EA5DBEA34660C5550DBB807\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Files from Internet zone must be opened in Excel in Protected View mode.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223341","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223341","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223341","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223341r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223341","rule_version":"O365-EX-000032","rule_title":"Files from unsafe locations must be opened in Excel in Protected View mode.","fix_text":"Set policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Protected View >> Do not open files in unsafe locations in Protected View to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Protected View >> Do not open files in unsafe locations in Protected View is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\protectedview\n\nIf the value DisableUnsafeLocationsInPV is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is REG_DWORD = 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting lets you determine if files located in unsafe locations will open in Protected View. If you have not specified unsafe locations, only the \"Downloaded Program Files\" and \"Temporary Internet Files\" folders are considered unsafe locations.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, files located in unsafe locations do not open in Protected View.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, files located in unsafe locations open in Protected View.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108861","V-99757","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"9658","uuid":"74a60c79-b7a1-422b-b567-47105f7ec2f6","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 560D80A8E6D05F31EDF063858BACB856FF7C8824\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Files from unsafe locations must be opened in Excel in Protected View mode.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223342","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223342","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223342","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223342r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223342","rule_version":"O365-EX-000033","rule_title":"Files failing file validation must be opened in Excel in Protected view mode and disallow edits.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Protected View >> Set document behavior if file validation fails to \"Enabled: Open in Protected View\". \n\nUncheck the \"Allow edit\" check box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Protected View >> Set document behavior if file validation fails is set to \"Enabled: Open in Protected View\". Verify the check box for \"Allow edit\" is not selected.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\Excel\\security\\filevalidation\n\nIf the value openinprotectedview does not exist, this is not a finding. \n\nIf both the value for openinprotectedview is REG_DWORD = 1 and the value for DisableEditFromPV is set to REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls how Office handles documents when they fail file validation. \n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can configure the following options for files that fail file validation:\n- Block files completely. Users cannot open the files.\n- Open files in Protected View and disallow edit. Users cannot edit the files. This is also how Office handles the files if you disable this policy setting.\n- Open files in Protected View and allow edit. Users can edit the files. This is also how Office handles the files if you do not configure this policy setting.\n\nIf you disable this policy setting, Office follows the \"Open files in Protected View and disallow edit\" behavior.\n\nIf you do not configure this policy setting, Office follows the \"Open files in Protected View and allow edit\" behavior.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108863","V-99759","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"9028","uuid":"a55475c4-9576-45ad-878e-17b8227fcde7","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C9B87A7454701FDCCA07C9661FFEAAFA800B042F\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Files failing file validation must be opened in Excel in Protected view mode and disallow edits.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223343","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223343","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223343","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223343r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223343","rule_version":"O365-EX-000034","rule_title":"File attachments from Outlook must be opened in Excel in Protected mode.","fix_text":"Set policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Protected View >> Turn off Protected View for attachments opened from Outlook to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Protected View >> Turn off Protected View for attachments opened from Outlook is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\protectedview\n\nIf the value DisableAttachmentsInPV is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to determine if Excel files in Outlook attachments open in Protected View.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, Outlook attachments do not open in Protected View.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Outlook attachments open in Protected View.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108865","V-99761","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"2722","uuid":"4ee4d1b0-9995-47cd-ac41-2c72e8b504cf","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7744D343D789ED6E9328E688D7C6A084BA5CC84D\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'File attachments from Outlook must be opened in Excel in Protected mode.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223344","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223344","title":"SRG-APP-000219","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223344","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000219","rule_id_src":"SV-223344r1043178_rule","rule_id":"SV-223344","rule_version":"O365-LY-000001","rule_title":"The SIP security mode in Lync must be enabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Skype for Business 2016 >> Microsoft Lync Feature Policies \"Configure SIP security mode\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Skype for Business 2016 >> Microsoft Lync Feature Policies \"Configure SIP security mode\" is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\office\\16.0\\lync\n\nIf the value enablesiphighsecuritymode is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"When Lync connects to the server, it supports various authentication mechanisms. This policy allows the user to specify whether Digest and Basic authentication are supported. Disabled (default): NTLM/Kerberos/TLS-DSK/Digest/Basic Enabled: Authentication mechanisms: NTLM/Kerberos/TLS-DSK Gal Download: Requires HTTPS if user is not logged in as an internal user.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108867","V-99763","CCI-001184"],"reference_identifier":"6226","uuid":"a9dc9b2d-3bfd-4787-a703-98ab64e73034","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C593CC04E8F202A9F28909C72978BEE453C24DF3\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The SIP security mode in Lync must be enabled.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223345","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223345","title":"SRG-APP-000219","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223345","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000219","rule_id_src":"SV-223345r1043178_rule","rule_id":"SV-223345","rule_version":"O365-LY-000002","rule_title":"The HTTP fallback for SIP connection in Lync must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Skype for Business 2016 >> Microsoft Lync Feature Policies \"Disable HTTP fallback for SIP connection\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Skype for Business 2016 >> Microsoft Lync Feature Policies \"Disable HTTP fallback for SIP connection\" is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\office\\16.0\\lync\n\nIf the value disablehttpconnect is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Prevents from HTTP being used for SIP connection in case TLS or TCP fail.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108869","V-99765","CCI-001184"],"reference_identifier":"3687","uuid":"b8f207e5-4a61-447a-ab35-7f2662be1b9c","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 39C63369BA278188EF42B981AECE57A9F4663A3B\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The HTTP fallback for SIP connection in Lync must be disabled.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223346","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223346","title":"SRG-APP-000575","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223346","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000575","rule_id_src":"SV-223346r961878_rule","rule_id":"SV-223346","rule_version":"O365-OU-000001","rule_title":"The Exchange client authentication with Exchange servers must be enabled to use Kerberos Password Authentication.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Account Settings >> Exchange >> Authentication with Exchange Server to Kerberos Password Authentication.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Account Settings >> Exchange >> Authentication with Exchange Server is set to Kerberos Password Authentication.\n \nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\outlook\\security\n\nIf the value authenticationservice is set to REG_DWORD = 16 (decimal) or 10 (hex), this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls which authentication method Outlook uses to authenticate with Microsoft Exchange Server. Note: Exchange Server supports the Kerberos authentication protocol and NTLM for authentication. The Kerberos protocol is the more secure authentication method and is supported on Windows 2000 Server and later versions. NTLM authentication is supported in pre-Windows 2000 environments.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can choose from three different options for controlling how Outlook authenticates with Microsoft Exchange Server:\n\n- Kerberos/NTLM password authentication. Outlook attempts to authenticate using the Kerberos authentication protocol. If this attempt fails, Outlook attempts to authenticate using NTLM. This option is the default configuration.\n- Kerberos password authentication. Outlook attempts to authenticate using the Kerberos protocol only.\n- NTLM password authentication. Outlook attempts to authenticate using NTLM only.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Outlook will attempt to authenticate using the Kerberos authentication protocol. If it cannot (because no Windows 2000 or later domain controllers are available), it will authenticate using NTLM.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108871","V-99767","CCI-001967"],"reference_identifier":"3427","uuid":"3361a06b-6b95-46a2-811e-94835f3d1467","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6F53093498AE772A5289913F0B93DC61D9D1E5D5\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Exchange client authentication with Exchange servers must be enabled to use Kerberos Password Authentication.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223347","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223347","title":"SRG-APP-000575","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223347","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000575","rule_id_src":"SV-223347r961878_rule","rule_id":"SV-223347","rule_version":"O365-OU-000002","rule_title":"Outlook must use remote procedure call (RPC) encryption to communicate with Microsoft Exchange servers.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Account Settings >> Exchange >> Enable RPC encryption to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Account Settings >> Exchange >> Enable RPC encryption is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\outlook\\rpc\n\nIf the value for enablerpcencryption is set to REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether Outlook uses remote procedure call (RPC) encryption to communicate with Microsoft Exchange servers. \n\nIf you enable this policy setting, Outlook uses RPC encryption when communicating with an Exchange server. Note: RPC encryption only encrypts the data from the Outlook client computer to the Exchange server. It does not encrypt the messages themselves as they traverse the Internet. \n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, RPC encryption is still used by default. This setting allows you to override the corresponding per-profile setting.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108873","V-99769","CCI-001967"],"reference_identifier":"9424","uuid":"b841a9b5-1bb3-4eab-9f8e-1530d477a324","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F65417B2678830965C0041590413D63570DBD66D\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Outlook must use remote procedure call (RPC) encryption to communicate with Microsoft Exchange servers.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223348","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223348","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223348","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223348r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223348","rule_version":"O365-OU-000003","rule_title":"Scripts associated with public folders must be prevented from execution in Outlook.","fix_text":"Set the policy for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Outlook Options >> Other >> Advanced >> Do not allow Outlook object model scripts to run for public folders to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy for Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Outlook Options >> Other >> Advanced >> Do not allow Outlook object model scripts to run for public folders is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\outlook\\security\n\nIf the value for publicfolderscript is set to REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether Outlook executes scripts that are associated with custom forms or folder home pages for public folders.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108875","V-99771","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"5927","uuid":"b6ee6577-cfae-4a26-b4c9-2fb1d79366f3","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A043CB1C9013957BDE6BB0674FC0EA1A581731F9\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Scripts associated with public folders must be prevented from execution in Outlook.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223349","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223349","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223349","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223349r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223349","rule_version":"O365-OU-000004","rule_title":"Scripts associated with shared folders must be prevented from execution in Outlook.","fix_text":"Set the policy for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Outlook Options >> Other >> Advanced >> Do not allow Outlook object model scripts to run for shared folders to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Outlook Options >> Other >> Advanced >> Do not allow Outlook object model scripts to run for shared folders is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\outlook\\security\n\nIf the value for sharedfolderscript is set to REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether Outlook executes scripts associated with custom forms or folder home pages for shared folders.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108877","V-99773","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"8232","uuid":"2425017b-f7c8-484e-8c08-5ac1c2227ef0","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DB0CED618A7B4740BFE0587EED8E561A1365906E\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Scripts associated with shared folders must be prevented from execution in Outlook.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223350","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223350","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223350","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","rule_id_src":"SV-223350r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223350","rule_version":"O365-OU-000005","rule_title":"Files dragged from an Outlook e-mail to the file system must be created in ANSI format.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Outlook Options >> Other >> Advanced >> Use Unicode format when dragging e-mail message to file system to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Outlook Options >> Other >> Advanced >> Use Unicode format when dragging e-mail message to file system is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\outlook\\options\\general\n\nIf the value for msgformat is set to REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether e-mail messages dragged from Outlook to the file system are saved in Unicode or ANSI format.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108879","V-99775","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7398","uuid":"a3666573-ad49-4941-b8c7-fbb6bc3c2760","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 80552AB9EFD804AFCDC71282696FC42B1502FCFD\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Files dragged from an Outlook e-mail to the file system must be created in ANSI format.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223351","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223351","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223351","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","rule_id_src":"SV-223351r1188335_rule","rule_id":"SV-223351","rule_version":"O365-OU-000006","rule_title":"The junk email protection level must be set to No Automatic Filtering.","fix_text":"In Outlook, click Home tab >> Delete group >> Junk >> Junk E-mail Options.\n\nSet the Junk E-mail protection level to \"No Automatic Filtering\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Note: If the Outlook client application is not used to access Office 365 email (i.e., email is only accessed via Outlook Web Access [OWA]), this is not applicable.  \n\nVerify Outlook Junk E-mail protection is set to \"No Automatic Filtering\".\n\nIn Outlook, click Home tab >> Delete group >> Junk >> Junk E-mail Options.\n\nVerify Junk E-mail protection is set to \"No Automatic Filtering\".\n \nIf the system being inspected is not behind EEMSG, CBII, or O365 EOP, the Junk E-mail protection level must be set to \"High\". Otherwise, \"Low\" is acceptable.\n\nIf Junk E-mail protection is not set to \"No Automatic Filtering\", this is a finding.\n\nIf the system is not behind enterprise-level capabilities such as EEMSG, CBII, or O365 EOP and the Junk E-mail protection is not set to \"High\", this is a  finding.\n\nIf the system is behind enterprise-level capabilities such as EEMSG, CBII, or O365 EOP, and the Junk E-mail protection is not at least \"Low\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls the Junk E-mail protection level. The Junk E-mail Filter in Outlook helps to prevent junk email messages, also known as spam, from cluttering a user's Inbox. The filter evaluates each incoming message based on several factors, including the time when the message was sent and the content of the message. The filter does not single out any particular sender or message type, but instead analyzes each message based on its content and structure to determine if it is likely spam.\n\nA Junk E-mail filtering option of \"No Automatic Filtering\" will evaluate emails against domain names and email addresses in the blocked sender list and send them to the Junk E-mail folder. \n\nA Junk E-mail filtering option of \"High\" is not recommended when behind enterprise-level capabilities such as Enterprise Email Security Gateway (EEMSG), Cloud-Based Internet Isolation (CBII), and O365 Exchange Online Protection (EOP).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108881","V-99777","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6667","uuid":"406fbad5-8908-4817-9e47-40d63e0ada88","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4B1A2F4ED83BA90CDBA093BE7E976B273CAA450C\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The junk email protection level must be set to No Automatic Filtering.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223352","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223352","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223352","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223352r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223352","rule_version":"O365-OU-000007","rule_title":"Active X One-Off forms must only be enabled to load with Outlook Controls.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Allow Active X One Off Forms to \"Enabled\" \"Load only Outlook Controls\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Allow Active X One Off Forms is set to \"Enabled\" \"Load only Outlook Controls\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\outlook\\security\n\nIf the value for allowactivexoneoffforms is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"By default, third-party ActiveX controls are not allowed to run in one-off forms in Outlook. You can change this behavior so that Safe Controls (Microsoft Forms 2.0 controls and the Outlook Recipient and Body controls) are allowed in one-off forms, or so that all ActiveX controls are allowed to run.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108883","V-99779","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"1960","uuid":"31e57f45-0fb8-40b3-8570-808299d3ea3a","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0F2BB45A641D31CC166A2422A16441E37EDC151F\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Active X One-Off forms must only be enabled to load with Outlook Controls.' is not present or not in use on this Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223353","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223353","title":"SRG-APP-000340","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223353","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000340","rule_id_src":"SV-223353r961353_rule","rule_id":"SV-223353","rule_version":"O365-OU-000008","rule_title":"Outlook must be configured to prevent users overriding attachment security settings.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Prevent users from customizing attachment security settings to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Prevent users from customizing attachment security settings is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\outlook\n\nIf the value for disallowattachmentcustomization is set to REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting prevents users from overriding the set of attachments blocked by Outlook.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting users will be prevented from overriding the set of attachments blocked by Outlook. Outlook also checks the \"Level1Remove\" registry key when this setting is specified. \n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, users will be allowed to override the set of attachments blocked by Outlook.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108885","V-99781","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"9707","uuid":"d5805d20-03e9-4106-b2bc-fb1bca62b43b","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9B4CE3D02F8526623752F7E1005D262D9AAA6FEC\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Outlook must be configured to prevent users overriding attachment security settings.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223354","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223354","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223354","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","rule_id_src":"SV-223354r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223354","rule_version":"O365-OU-000009","rule_title":"Internet must not be included in Safe Zone for picture download in Outlook.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Automatic Picture Download Settings >> Include Internet in Safe Zones for Automatic Picture Download to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Automatic Picture Download Settings >> Include Internet in Safe Zones for Automatic Picture Download is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\outlook\\options\\mail\n\nIf the value for Internet is set to REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether pictures and external content in HTML e-mail messages from untrusted senders on the Internet are downloaded without Outlook users explicitly choosing to do so. \n\nIf you enable this policy setting, Outlook will automatically download external content in all e-mail messages sent over the Internet and users will not be able to change the setting. \n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Outlook does not consider the Internet a safe zone, which means that Outlook will not automatically download content from external servers unless the sender is included in the Safe Senders list. Recipients can choose to download external content from untrusted senders on a message-by-message basis.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108887","V-99783","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6747","uuid":"8286a561-d127-48a6-a045-f26a63fc4a93","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 44133ECBB828AEDAF3958FCD5D6C612D11BA605A\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Internet must not be included in Safe Zone for picture download in Outlook.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223355","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223355","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223355","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","rule_id_src":"SV-223355r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223355","rule_version":"O365-OU-000010","rule_title":"The Publish to Global Address List (GAL) button must be disabled in Outlook.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Cryptography >> Do not display 'Publish to GAL' button to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Cryptography >> Do not display 'Publish to GAL' button is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\outlook\\security\n\nIf the value for publishtogaldisabled is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether Outlook users can publish e-mail certificates to the Global Address List (GAL). \n\nIf you enable this policy setting, the \"Publish to GAL\" button does not display in the \"E-mail Security\" section of the Trust Center. \n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Outlook users can publish their e-mail certificates to the GAL through the \"E-mail Security\" section of the Trust Center.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108889","V-99785","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9953","uuid":"8431164d-35da-42e7-9572-1412fed2bd69","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 441F9BAC0A9D48BA3D9E5E2D2764218418744C56\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Publish to Global Address List (GAL) button must be disabled in Outlook.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223356","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223356","title":"SRG-APP-000630","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223356","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000630","rule_id_src":"SV-223356r1117184_rule","rule_id":"SV-223356","rule_version":"O365-OU-000011","rule_title":"The minimum encryption key length in Outlook must be at least 168.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Cryptography >> Minimum encryption settings to \"Enabled\"and a Minimum key size (in bits) of \"168\" or above.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Cryptography >> Minimum encryption settings is set to \"Enabled\" and a Minimum key size (in bits) of \"168\" or above.\n\nUse the Windows Registry to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\outlook\\security\n\nIf the value for minenckey is set to 168 or above, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to set the minimum key length for an encrypted e-mail message.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you may set the minimum key length for an encrypted e-mail message. Outlook will display a warning dialog if the user tries to send a message using an encryption key that is below the minimum encryption key value set. The user can still choose to ignore the warning and send using the encryption key originally chosen.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, a dialog warning will be shown to the user if the user attempts to send a message using encryption. The user can still choose to ignore the warning and send using the encryption key originally chosen.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108891","V-99787","CCI-002450"],"reference_identifier":"7040","uuid":"06933096-d9fa-4f53-ac64-ea1d29485f58","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1BB87E7064709FF5B0CFE59D528F0F2B09C95DCD\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The minimum encryption key length in Outlook must be at least 168.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223357","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223357","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223357","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223357r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223357","rule_version":"O365-OU-000012","rule_title":"The warning about invalid digital signatures must be enabled to warn Outlook users.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Cryptography >> Signature Warning to \"Enabled\" \"Always warn about invalid signatures\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Cryptography >> Signature Warning is set to \"Enabled\" \"Always warn about invalid signatures\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\outlook\\security\n\nIf the value for warnaboutinvalid is set to REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls how Outlook warns users about messages with invalid digital signatures.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can choose from three options for controlling how Outlook users are warned about invalid signatures:\n- Let user decide if they want to be warned. This option enforces the default configuration.\n- Always warn about invalid signatures.\n- Never warn about invalid signatures.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, if users open e-mail messages that include invalid digital signatures, Outlook displays a warning dialog. Users can decide whether they want to be warned about invalid signatures in the future.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108893","V-99789","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"6938","uuid":"fa64c991-4a58-428d-b701-bedcd95435a6","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-223358","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223358","title":"SRG-APP-000605","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223358","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000605","rule_id_src":"SV-223358r961893_rule","rule_id":"SV-223358","rule_version":"O365-OU-000013","rule_title":"Outlook must be configured to allow retrieving of Certificate Revocation Lists (CRLs) always when online.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Cryptography >> Signature Status dialog box >> Retrieving CRLs (Certificate Revocation Lists) to \"Enabled\" \"When online always retrieve the CRL\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Cryptography >> Signature Status dialog box >> Retrieving CRLs (Certificate Revocation Lists) is set to \"Enabled\" \"When online always retrieve the CRL\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\outlook\\security\n\nIf the value for usecrlchasing is set to REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls how Outlook retrieves Certificate Revocation Lists to verify the validity of certificates. Certificate revocation lists (CRLs) are lists of digital certificates that have been revoked by their controlling certificate authorities (CAs), typically because the certificates were issued improperly or their associated private keys were compromised. \n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can choose from three options to govern how Outlook uses CRLs: \n- Use system Default. Outlook relies on the CRL download schedule that is configured for the operating system. \n- When online always retrieve the CRL. This option is the default configuration in Outlook. \n- Never retrieve the CRL. Outlook will not attempt to download the CRL for a certificate, even if it is online. This option can reduce security. \n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, when Outlook handles a certificate that includes a URL from which a CRL can be downloaded, Outlook will retrieve the CRL from the provided URL if Outlook is online.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108895","V-99791","CCI-000185"],"reference_identifier":"2886","uuid":"6455f9ff-74d9-4488-a3a9-238118a3950e","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F4904DD4706B7E4422F67C42674C56FA7EB3A570\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Outlook must be configured to allow retrieving of Certificate Revocation Lists (CRLs) always when online.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223359","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223359","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223359","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","rule_id_src":"SV-223359r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223359","rule_version":"O365-OU-000014","rule_title":"The Outlook Security Mode must be enabled to always use the Outlook Security Group Policy.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Security Form Settings >> Outlook Security Mode to \"Enabled (Use Outlook Security Group Policy)\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Security Form Settings >> Outlook Security Mode is set to \"Enabled (Use Outlook Security Group Policy)\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\outlook\\security\n\nIf the value for adminsecuritymode is set to REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls which set of security settings are enforced in Outlook. If you enable this policy setting, you can choose from four options for enforcing Outlook security settings: \n \n- Outlook Default Security - This option is the default configuration in Outlook. Users can configure security themselves, and Outlook ignores any security-related settings configured in Group Policy. \n- Use Security Form from \"Outlook Security Settings\" Public Folder - Outlook uses the settings from the security form published in the designated public folder. \n- Use Security Form from \"Outlook 10 Security Settings\" Public Folder - Outlook uses the settings from the security form published in the designated public folder. \n- Use Outlook Security Group Policy - Outlook uses security settings from Group Policy. Important: You must enable this policy setting if you want to apply the other Outlook security policy settings mentioned in this guide. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Outlook users can configure security for themselves, and Outlook ignores any security-related settings that are configured in Group Policy. \n\nNote: In previous versions of Outlook, when security settings were published in a form in Exchange Server public folders, users who needed these settings required the HKEY_CURRENT_USER >> Software >> Policies >> Microsoft >> Security >> CheckAdminSettings registry key to be set on their computers for the settings to apply. In Outlook, the CheckAdminSettings registry key is no longer used to determine users' security settings. Instead, the Outlook Security Mode setting can be used to determine whether Outlook security should be controlled directly by Group Policy, by the security form from the Outlook Security Settings Public Folder, or by the settings on users' own computers.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108897","V-99793","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6713","uuid":"e655ac66-d58b-4907-94c3-83e7e6363b2a","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-223360","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223360","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223360","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223360r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223360","rule_version":"O365-OU-000015","rule_title":"The ability to demote attachments from Level 2 to Level 1 must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Security Form Settings >> Attachment Security >> Allow users to demote attachments to Level 2 to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Security Form Settings >> Attachment Security >> Allow users to demote attachments to Level 2 is set to \"Disabled\".\n \nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\outlook\\security\n\nIf the value allowuserstolowerattachments is set to REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether Outlook users can demote attachments to Level 2 by using a registry key, which will allow them to save files to disk and open them from that location. Outlook uses two levels of security to restrict access to files attached to e-mail messages or other items. Files with specific extensions can be categorized as Level 1 (users cannot view the file) or Level 2 (users can open the file after saving it to disk). Users can freely open files of types that are not categorized as Level 1 or Level 2. \n\nIf you enable this policy setting, users can create a list of Level 1 file types to demote to Level 2 by adding the file types to the following registry key: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\\Software\\Microsoft\\Office\\14.0\\Outlook\\Security\\Level1Remove. \n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, users cannot demote level 1 attachments to level 2, and the HKEY_CURRENT_USER\\Software\\Microsoft\\Office\\14.0\\Outlook\\Security\\Level1Remove registry key has no effect.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108899","V-99795","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"2959","uuid":"62610b1c-4815-4e0d-918e-db9779ef4f18","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D44AF44E16CDF08155231B24C2A5EB6722330C3B\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The ability to demote attachments from Level 2 to Level 1 must be disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223361","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223361","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223361","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223361r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223361","rule_version":"O365-OU-000016","rule_title":"The display of Level 1 attachments must be disabled in Outlook.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Security Form Settings >> Attachment Security \"Display Level 1 attachments\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Security Form Settings >> Attachment Security >> Display Level 1 attachments is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\outlook\\security\n\nIf the value ShowLevel1Attach is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether Outlook blocks potentially dangerous attachments designated Level 1. Outlook uses two levels of security to restrict users' access to files attached to e-mail messages or other items. Files with specific extensions can be categorized as Level 1 (users cannot view the file) or Level 2 (users can open the file after saving it to disk). Users can freely open files of types that are not categorized as Level 1 or Level 2. \n\nIf you enable this policy setting, Outlook users can gain access to Level 1 file type attachments by first saving the attachments to disk and then opening them, as with Level 2 attachments. If you disable this policy setting, Level 1 attachments do not display under any circumstances. If you do not configure this policy setting, Outlook completely blocks access to Level 1 files, and requires users to save Level 2 files to disk before opening them.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108901","V-99797","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"6437","uuid":"c5917f1e-2c8b-4b21-82d4-25ee546e6384","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 26DC06AB8123F3EC6B932173DE68D99A2B5C51AC\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The display of Level 1 attachments must be disabled in Outlook.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223362","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223362","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223362","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223362r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223362","rule_version":"O365-OU-000017","rule_title":"Level 1 file attachments must be blocked from being delivered.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Security Form Settings >> Attachment Security >> Remove file extensions blocked as Level 1 to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Security Form Settings >> Attachment Security >> Remove file extensions blocked as Level 1 is set to \"Disabled\".\n \nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\outlook\\security\\FileExtensionsRemoveLevel1\n\nIf the registry key exists, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether Outlook users can demote attachments to Level 2 by using a registry key, which will allow them to save files to disk and open them from that location. Outlook uses two levels of security to restrict access to files attached to email messages or other items. Files with specific extensions can be categorized as Level 1 (users cannot view the file) or Level 2 (users can open the file after saving it to disk). Users can freely open files of types that are not categorized as Level 1 or Level 2. \n\nIf you enable this policy setting, users can create a list of Level 1 file types to demote to Level 2 by adding the file types to the following registry key: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\\Software\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\Outlook\\Security\\Level1Remove. \n\nIf this policy setting is disabled or not configured, users cannot demote Level 1 attachments to Level 2, and the HKEY_CURRENT_USER\\Software\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\Outlook\\Security\\Level1Remove registry key has no effect.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108903","V-99799","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"5150","uuid":"99b55091-3f0f-4a4e-bbf9-8df89b6769b7","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 3D43B92B9C954C8AD67089CEA2EB0ED9F302C87D\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Level 1 file attachments must be blocked from being delivered.' is not present or not in use on this Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223363","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223363","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223363","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223363r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223363","rule_version":"O365-OU-000018","rule_title":"Level 2 file attachments must be blocked from being delivered.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Security Form Settings >> Attachment Security >> Remove file extensions blocked as Level 2 to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Security Form Settings >> Attachment Security >> Remove file extensions blocked as Level 2 is set to \"Disabled\".\n \nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\outlook\\security\\FileExtensionsRemoveLevel2\n\nIf the registry key exists, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls which types of attachments (determined by file extension) must be saved to disk before users can open them. Files with specific extensions can be categorized as Level 1 (users cannot view the file) or Level 2 (users can open the file after saving it to disk). Users can freely open files of types that are not categorized as Level 1 or Level 2. \n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can specify a list of attachment file types to classify as Level 2, which forces users to actively decide to download the attachment to view it. \n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Outlook does not classify any file type extensions as Level 2. \n\nImportant: This policy setting only applies if the \"Outlook Security Mode\" policy setting under \"Microsoft Outlook 2016\\Security\\Security Form Settings\" is configured to \"Use Outlook Security Group Policy\".","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108905","V-99801","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"6123","uuid":"02e93b06-babb-4f32-b472-7ddd7beaf989","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F9BF6992C53B0EE0FED10229A0922E383D0FE8C7\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Level 2 file attachments must be blocked from being delivered.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223364","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223364","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223364","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223364r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223364","rule_version":"O365-OU-000019","rule_title":"Outlook must be configured to not run scripts in forms in which the script and the layout are contained within the message.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Security Form Settings >> Custom Form Security \"Allow scripts in one-off Outlook forms\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Security Form Settings >> Custom Form Security \"Allow scripts in one-off Outlook forms\" is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\outlook\\security\n\nIf the value EnableOneOffFormScripts is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether scripts can run in Outlook forms in which the script and layout are contained within the message. If you enable this policy setting, scripts can run in one-off Outlook forms. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Outlook does not run scripts in forms in which the script and the layout are contained within the message. Important: This policy setting only applies if the \"Outlook Security Mode\" policy setting under \"Microsoft Outlook 2016\\Security\\Security Form Settings\" is configured to \"Use Outlook Security Group Policy\".","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108907","V-99803","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"8009","uuid":"81f80106-eb63-4246-b805-1e5938baf904","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: ED0BC50BA405B1A4E0288EF20FAD6FD1905A75FC\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Outlook must be configured to not run scripts in forms in which the script and the layout are contained within the message.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223365","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223365","title":"SRG-APP-000488","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223365","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000488","rule_id_src":"SV-223365r961779_rule","rule_id":"SV-223365","rule_version":"O365-OU-000020","rule_title":"When a custom action is executed that uses the Outlook object model, Outlook must automatically deny it.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Security Form Settings >> Custom Form Setting >> Set Outlook object model custom actions execution prompt to \"Enabled\" and select \"Automatically Deny\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Security Form Settings >> Custom Form Security >> Set Outlook object model custom actions execution prompt is set to \"Enabled\" and \"Automatically Deny\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\outlook\\security\n\nIf the value for \"promptoomcustomaction\" is set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether Outlook prompts users before executing a custom action. Custom actions add functionality to Outlook that can be triggered as part of a rule. Among other possible features, custom actions can be created that reply to messages in ways that circumvent the Outlook model's programmatic send protections. If this policy is enabled, four options are available to control how Outlook functions when a custom action is executed that uses the Outlook object model: \n- Prompt User\n- Automatically Approve\n- Automatically Deny \n- Prompt user based on computer security. This option enforces the default configuration in Outlook. \n\nIf this policy is disabled or not configured, when Outlook or another program initiates a custom action using the Outlook object model, users are prompted to allow or reject the action. If this configuration is changed, malicious code can use the Outlook object model to compromise sensitive information or otherwise cause data and computing resources to be at risk. This is the equivalent of choosing Enabled -- Prompt user based on computer security.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108909","V-99805","CCI-002460"],"reference_identifier":"3413","uuid":"b979c97f-346c-4704-a04e-d69485d356d2","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 991051326C2A8F0B03317DFDDA77A6FB00E5070E\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'When a custom action is executed that uses the Outlook object model, Outlook must automatically deny it.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223366","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223366","title":"SRG-APP-000488","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223366","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000488","rule_id_src":"SV-223366r961779_rule","rule_id":"SV-223366","rule_version":"O365-OU-000021","rule_title":"When an untrusted program attempts to programmatically access an Address Book using the Outlook object model, Outlook must automatically deny it.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Security Form Settings >> Programmatic Security >> Configure Outlook object model prompt when accessing an address book to \"Enabled (Automatically Deny)\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Security Form Settings >> Programmatic Security >> Configure Outlook object model prompt when accessing an address book is set to \"Enabled (Automatically Deny)\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\outlook\\security\n\nIf the value for promptoomaddressbookaccess is set to REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls what happens when an untrusted program attempts to gain access to an Address Book using the Outlook object model. \n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can choose from four different options when an untrusted program attempts to programmatically access an Address Book using the Outlook object model:\n- Prompt user - Users are prompted to approve every access attempt. \n- Automatically approve - Outlook will automatically grant programmatic access requests from any program. This option can create a significant vulnerability, and is not recommended. \n- Automatically deny - Outlook will automatically deny programmatic access requests from any program.\n- Prompt user based on computer security - Outlook will rely on the setting in the ''Programmatic Access'' section of the Trust Center. This is the default behavior.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, when an untrusted application attempts to access the address book programmatically, Outlook relies on the setting configured in the ''Programmatic Access'' section of the Trust Center.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108911","V-99807","CCI-002460"],"reference_identifier":"7455","uuid":"08c27a60-091f-4663-836c-73d3f0c2b57b","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A0F8CDD38E78487DE823461BF1DF1F24DD5FC04E\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'When an untrusted program attempts to programmatically access an Address Book using the Outlook object model, Outlook must automatically deny it.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223367","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223367","title":"SRG-APP-000488","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223367","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000488","rule_id_src":"SV-223367r961779_rule","rule_id":"SV-223367","rule_version":"O365-OU-000022","rule_title":"When a user designs a custom form in Outlook and attempts to bind an Address Information field to a combination or formula custom field, Outlook must automatically deny it.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Security Form Settings >> Programmatic Security >> Configure Outlook object model prompt When accessing the Formula property of a UserProperty object to \"Enabled (Automatically Deny)\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Security Form Settings >> Programmatic Security >> Configure Outlook object model prompt when accessing the Formula property of a UserProperty object is set to \"Enabled (Automatically Deny)\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\outlook\\security\n\nIf the value PromptOOMFormulaAccess is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls what happens when a user designs a custom form in Outlook and attempts to bind an Address Information field to a combination or formula custom field. If you enable this policy setting, you can choose from four different options when an untrusted program attempts to access address information using the UserProperties. Find method of the Outlook object model: \n\n- Prompt user. The user will be prompted to approve every access attempt. - Automatically approve. Outlook will automatically grant programmatic access requests from any program. This option can create a significant vulnerability, and is not recommended. \n- Automatically deny. Outlook will automatically deny programmatic access requests from any program. \n- Prompt user based on computer security. Outlook will only prompt users when antivirus software is out of date or not running. \n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, when a user tries to bind an address information field to a combination or formula custom field in a custom form, Outlook relies on the setting configured in the \"Programmatic Access\" section of the Trust Center.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108913","V-99809","CCI-002460"],"reference_identifier":"4863","uuid":"4b02f517-16db-407c-81b2-112d8738df74","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6CCEE1745FAE45646E8238F56A3A8E8C67C13336\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'When a user designs a custom form in Outlook and attempts to bind an Address Information field to a combination or formula custom field, Outlook must automatically deny it.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223368","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223368","title":"SRG-APP-000488","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223368","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000488","rule_id_src":"SV-223368r961779_rule","rule_id":"SV-223368","rule_version":"O365-OU-000023","rule_title":"When an untrusted program attempts to use the Save As command to programmatically save an item, Outlook must automatically deny it.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Security Form Settings >> Programmatic Security >> Configure Outlook object model prompt when executing Save As to \"Enabled (Automatically Deny)\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Security Form Settings >> Programmatic Security >> Configure Outlook object model prompt when executing Save As is set to \"Enabled (Automatically Deny)\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\outlook\\security\n\nIf the value for promptoomsaveas is set to REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls what happens when an untrusted program attempts to use the Save As command to programmatically save an item. \n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can choose from four different options when an untrusted program attempts to use the Save As command to programmatically save an item:\n- Prompt user. The user will be prompted to approve every access attempt. \n- Automatically approve. Outlook will automatically grant programmatic access requests from any program. This option can create a significant vulnerability, and is not recommended. \n- Automatically deny. Outlook will automatically deny programmatic access requests from any program.\n- Prompt user based on computer security. Outlook will only prompt users when antivirus software is out of date or not running. This is the default configuration.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, when an untrusted application attempts to use the Save As command, Outlook relies on the setting configured in the ''Programmatic Access'' section of the Trust Center.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108915","V-99811","CCI-002460"],"reference_identifier":"4050","uuid":"da2acfdc-f090-4521-b11c-35d51b62ad6d","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 54BB273EAA3C71471C4115618A6B25D41F582B95\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'When an untrusted program attempts to use the Save As command to programmatically save an item, Outlook must automatically deny it.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223369","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223369","title":"SRG-APP-000488","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223369","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000488","rule_id_src":"SV-223369r961779_rule","rule_id":"SV-223369","rule_version":"O365-OU-000024","rule_title":"When an untrusted program attempts to gain access to a recipient field, such as the, To: field, using the Outlook object model, Outlook must automatically deny it.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Security Form Settings >> Programmatic Security >> Configure Outlook object model prompt when reading address information to \"Enabled (Automatically Deny)\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Security Form Settings >> Programmatic Security >> Configure Outlook object model prompt when reading address information is set to \"Enabled (Automatically Deny)\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\outlook\\security\n\nIf the value for promptoomaddressinformationaccess is set to REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls what happens when an untrusted program attempts to gain access to a recipient field, such as the ''To:'' field, using the Outlook object model.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can choose from four different options when an untrusted program attempts to access a recipient field using the Outlook object model:\n- Prompt user. The user will be prompted to approve every access attempt.\n- Automatically approve. Outlook will automatically grant programmatic access requests from any program. This option can create a significant vulnerability, and is not recommended.\n- Automatically deny. Outlook will automatically deny programmatic access requests from any program.\n- Prompt user based on computer security. Outlook will only prompt users when antivirus software is out of date or not running. This is the default configuration.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, when an untrusted application attempts to access recipient fields, Outlook relies on the setting configured in the ''Programmatic Access'' section of the Trust Center.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108917","V-99813","CCI-002460"],"reference_identifier":"1620","uuid":"6cf29dd3-bb9c-429e-9216-96429a8aa058","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 36FC99E06070A746F5756B55B171120F68745B9E\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'When an untrusted program attempts to gain access to a recipient field, such as the, To: field, using the Outlook object model, Outlook must automatically deny it.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223370","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223370","title":"SRG-APP-000488","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223370","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000488","rule_id_src":"SV-223370r961779_rule","rule_id":"SV-223370","rule_version":"O365-OU-000025","rule_title":"When an untrusted program attempts to programmatically send e-mail in Outlook using the Response method of a task or meeting request, Outlook must automatically deny it.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Security Form Settings >> Programmatic Security >> Configure Outlook object model prompt when responding to meeting and task requests to \"Enabled (Automatically Deny)\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Security Form Settings >> Programmatic Security >> Configure Outlook object model prompt when responding to meeting and task requests is set to \"Enabled (Automatically Deny)\"\n\nUse the Windows Registry to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\outlook\\security\n\nIf the value for promptoommeetingtaskrequestresponse is set to REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls what happens when an untrusted program attempts to programmatically send e-mail in Outlook using the Response method of a task or meeting request. \n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can choose from four different options when an untrusted program attempts to programmatically send e-mail using the Response method of a task or meeting request:\n- Prompt user. The user will be prompted to approve every access attempt.\n- Automatically approve. Outlook will automatically grant programmatic access requests from any program. This option can create a significant vulnerability, and is not recommended.\n- Automatically deny. Outlook will automatically deny programmatic access requests from any program. \n- Prompt user based on computer security. Outlook only prompts users when antivirus software is out of date or not running. This is the default configuration. \n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, when an untrusted application attempts to respond to tasks or meeting requests programmatically, Outlook relies on the setting configured in the ''Programmatic Access'' section of the Trust Center.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108919","V-99815","CCI-002460"],"reference_identifier":"8735","uuid":"903353df-2522-4a60-9f93-b3e2ffe7bfec","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 22C24BACE05F869C5EA78AFE36B072256E60E269\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'When an untrusted program attempts to programmatically send e-mail in Outlook using the Response method of a task or meeting request, Outlook must automatically deny it.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223371","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223371","title":"SRG-APP-000488","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223371","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000488","rule_id_src":"SV-223371r961779_rule","rule_id":"SV-223371","rule_version":"O365-OU-000026","rule_title":"When an untrusted program attempts to send e-mail programmatically using the Outlook object model, Outlook must automatically deny it.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Security Form Settings >> Programmatic Security >> Configure Outlook object model prompt when sending mail to \"Enabled (Automatically Deny)\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Security Form Settings >> Programmatic Security >> Configure Outlook object model prompt when sending mail is set to \"Enabled (Automatically Deny)\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\outlook\\security\n\nIf the value for promptoomsend is set to REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls what happens when an untrusted program attempts to send e-mail programmatically using the Outlook object model. \n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can choose from four different options when an untrusted program attempts to send e-mail programmatically using the Outlook object model: \n- Prompt user - The user will be prompted to approve every access attempt.\n- Automatically approve - Outlook will automatically grant programmatic access requests from any program. This option can create a significant vulnerability, and is not recommended. \n- Automatically deny - Outlook will automatically deny programmatic access requests from any program. \n- Prompt user based on computer security. Outlook will only prompt users when antivirus software is out of date or not running. \n\nImportant: This policy setting only applies if the \"Outlook Security Mode\" policy setting under \"Microsoft Outlook 2016\\Security\\Security Form Settings\" is configured to \"Use Outlook Security Group Policy\".\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, when an untrusted application attempts to send mail programmatically, Outlook relies on the setting configured in the ''Programmatic Access'' section of the Trust Center.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108921","V-99817","CCI-002460"],"reference_identifier":"9562","uuid":"96720091-645a-4631-a741-6aa29a6ca907","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 41E859A4DD236DF70B69464DDC0B95BBF7BDFCA2\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'When an untrusted program attempts to send e-mail programmatically using the Outlook object model, Outlook must automatically deny it.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223372","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223372","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223372","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","rule_id_src":"SV-223372r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223372","rule_version":"O365-OU-000027","rule_title":"Outlook must be configured to not allow hyperlinks in suspected phishing messages.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Trust Center \"Allow hyperlinks in suspected phishing e-mail messages\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Trust Center \"Allow hyperlinks in suspected phishing e-mail messages\" is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\outlook\\options\\mail\n\nIf the value JunkMailEnableLinks is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether hyperlinks in suspected phishing e-mail messages in Outlook are allowed. If you enable this policy setting, Outlook will allow hyperlinks in suspected phishing messages that are not also classified as junk e-mail. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Outlook will not allow hyperlinks in suspected phishing messages, even if they are not classified as junk e-mail.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108923","V-99819","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6996","uuid":"2da96145-8586-4127-ad5c-00cf701c53bc","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2011BFE529E797628B7EA0F62B3769E4741DF4B3\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Outlook must be configured to not allow hyperlinks in suspected phishing messages.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223373","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223373","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223373","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223373r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223373","rule_version":"O365-OU-000028","rule_title":"The Security Level for macros in Outlook must be configured to Warn for signed and disable unsigned.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Trust Center >> Security setting for macros must to \"Enabled: Warn for signed, disable unsigned\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Outlook 2016 >> Security >> Trust Center >> Security setting for macros must be set to \"Enabled: Warn for signed, disable unsigned\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\outlook\\security\n\nIf the value for level is set to REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls the security level for macros in Outlook. \n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can choose from four options for handling macros in Outlook: \n- Always warn. This option corresponds to the \"Warnings for all macros\" option in the \"Macro Security\" section of the Outlook Trust Center. Outlook disables all macros that are not opened from a trusted location, even if the macros are signed by a trusted publisher. For each disabled macro, Outlook displays a security alert dialog box with information about the macro and its digital signature (if present), and allows users to enable the macro or leave it disabled. \n- Never warn, disable all. This option corresponds to the \"No warnings and disable all macros\" option in the Trust Center. Outlook disables all macros that are not opened from trusted locations, and does not notify users. \n- Warning for signed, disable unsigned. This option corresponds to the \"Warnings for signed macros; all unsigned macros are disabled\" option in the Trust Center. Outlook handles macros as follows: \n--If a macro is digitally signed by a trusted publisher, the macro can run if the user has already trusted the publisher. \n--If a macro has a valid signature from a publisher that the user has not trusted, the security alert dialog box for the macro lets the user choose whether to enable the macro for the current session, disable the macro for the current session, or to add the publisher to the Trusted Publishers list so that it will run without prompting the user in the future. \n--If a macro does not have a valid signature, Outlook disables it without prompting the user, unless it is opened from a trusted location. \nThis option is the default configuration in Outlook. \n- No security check. This option corresponds to the \"No security check for macros (Not recommended)\" option in the Trust Center. Outlook runs all macros without prompting users. This configuration makes users' computers vulnerable to potentially malicious code and is not recommended. \n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the behavior is the equivalent of Enabled -- Warning for signed, disable unsigned.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108925","V-99821","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"5214","uuid":"fa7d6548-8e13-415c-b610-d2b6843bb912","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 84A5B21712B403336A2C9227EC29B1DDD52A9434\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Security Level for macros in Outlook must be configured to Warn for signed and disable unsigned.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223374","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223374","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223374","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223374r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223374","rule_version":"O365-PR-000001","rule_title":"Trusted Locations on the network must be disabled in Project.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Project 2016 >> Project Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Allow Trusted Locations on the network to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Project 2016 >> Project Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Allow Trusted Locations on the network is set to \"Disabled\".\n \nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\ms project\\security\\trusted locations\n\nIf the value allownetworklocations is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether trusted locations on the network can be used.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, users can specify trusted locations on network shares or in other remote locations that are not under their direct control by clicking the \"Add new location\" button in the Trusted Locations section of the Trust Center. Content, code, and add-ins are allowed to load from trusted locations with minimal security and without prompting the user for permission.\n\nIf you disable this policy setting, the selected application ignores any network locations listed in the Trusted Locations section of the Trust Center. \n\nIf you also deploy Trusted Locations via Group Policy, you should verify whether any of them are remote locations. If any of them are remote locations and you do not allow remote locations via this policy setting, those policy keys that point to remote locations will be ignored on client computers.\n\nDisabling this policy setting does not delete any network locations from the Trusted Locations list, but causes disruption for users who add network locations to the Trusted Locations list. Users are also prevented from adding new network locations to the Trusted Locations list in the Trust Center. We recommended that you do not enable this policy setting as the \"Allow Trusted Locations on my network (not recommended)\" check box also states. Therefore, in practice, it should be possible to disable this policy setting in most situations without causing significant usability issues for most users.\n\nIf you do not enable this policy setting, users can select the \"Allow Trusted Locations on my network (not recommended)\" check box if desired and then specify trusted locations by clicking the \"Add new location\" button.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108955","V-99851","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"1138","uuid":"a9a56067-cb40-4617-a4be-577a2b8d4342","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2177DA603286E4FA8FF42F0F508C974E5BE544D1\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Trusted Locations on the network must be disabled in Project.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223375","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223375","title":"SRG-APP-000131","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223375","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000131","rule_id_src":"SV-223375r1016169_rule","rule_id":"SV-223375","rule_version":"O365-PR-000002","rule_title":"Project must automatically disable unsigned add-ins without informing users.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Project 2016 >> Project Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> \"Disable Trust Bar Notification for unsigned application add-ins and block them\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Project 2016 >> Project Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> \"Disable Trust Bar Notification for unsigned application add-ins and block them\" is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\Microsoft\\office\\16.0\\ms project\\security\n\nIf the value notbpromptunsignedaddin is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether the specified Office application notifies users when unsigned application add-ins are loaded or silently disable such add-ins without notification. This policy setting only applies if the \"Require that application add-ins are signed by Trusted Publisher\" policy setting is enabled, which prevents users from changing this policy setting. \n\nIf this policy setting is enabled, applications automatically disable unsigned add-ins without informing users. \n\nIf this policy setting is disabled, if this application is configured to require that all add-ins be signed by a trusted publisher, any unsigned add-ins the application loads will be disabled and the application will display the Trust Bar at the top of the active window. The Trust Bar contains a message that informs users about the unsigned add-in. \n\nIf this policy setting is not configured, the disable behavior applies, and in addition, users can configure this requirement themselves in the \"Add-ins\" category of the Trust Center for the application.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108957","V-99853","CCI-003992","CCI-001749"],"reference_identifier":"4943","uuid":"ad82c12e-762d-4baa-bd73-31cbf6076e90","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-223376","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223376","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223376","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223376r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223376","rule_version":"O365-PR-000003","rule_title":"VBA Macros not digitally signed must be blocked in Project.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Project 2016 >> Project Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> VBA Macro Notification Settings to \"Enabled\" \"Disable all except digitally signed macros\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Project 2016 >> Project Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> VBA Macro Notification Settings is set to \"Enabled\" \"Disable all except digitally signed macros\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\ms project\\security\n\nIf the value for vbawarnings is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding. A value of REG_DWORD =  4 is also acceptable. If the registry key does not exist or is not configured properly, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls how the specified applications warn users when Visual Basic for Applications (VBA) macros are present.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can choose from four options for determining how the specified applications will warn the user about macros:\n\n- Disable all with notification: The application displays the Trust Bar for all macros, whether signed or unsigned. This option enforces the default configuration in Office. This option also allows users to potentially enable unsigned/untrusted macros.  If a site requires the use of macros, they must be signed /approved and added to appropriate locations listed in the Trust Center Settings. \n- Disable all except digitally signed macros: The application displays the Trust Bar for digitally signed macros, allowing users to enable them or leave them disabled. Any unsigned macros are disabled, and users are not notified.\n- Disable all without notification: The application disables all macros, whether signed or unsigned, and does not notify users.\n- Enable all macros (not recommended): All macros are enabled, whether signed or unsigned. This option can significantly reduce security by allowing dangerous code to run undetected.\n\nIf you disable this policy setting, \"Disable all with notification\" will be the default setting.\n\nIf you do not configure this policy setting, when users open files in the specified applications that contain VBA macros, the applications open the files with the macros disabled and display the Trust Bar with a warning that macros are present and have been disabled. Users can inspect and edit the files if appropriate, but cannot use any disabled functionality until they enable it by clicking \"Enable Content\" on the Trust Bar. If the user clicks \"Enable Content\", then the document is added as a trusted document.\n\nImportant: If \"Disable all except digitally signed macros\" is selected, users will not be able to open unsigned Access databases.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108959","V-99855","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"6725","uuid":"a75d7b70-2a66-492e-a6e6-ec7ff0c49ca7","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C5335DAA691768BC99B4F4115FCE0FF8DD45B13E\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'VBA Macros not digitally signed must be blocked in Project.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223377","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223377","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223377","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223377r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223377","rule_version":"O365-PT-000001","rule_title":"VBA Macros not digitally signed must be blocked in PowerPoint.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft PowerPoint 2016 >> PowerPoint Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> VBA Macro Notification Settings to \"Enabled\" \"Disable all except digitally signed macros\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft PowerPoint 2016 >> PowerPoint Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> VBA Macro Notification Settings is set to \"Enabled\" \"Disable all except digitally signed macros\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\powerpoint\\security\n\nIf the value for vbawarnings is REG_DWORD = 3 this is not a finding. A value of REG_DWORD =  4 is also acceptable. If the registry key does not exist or is not configured properly, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls how the specified applications warn users when Visual Basic for Applications (VBA) macros are present.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can choose from four options for determining how the specified applications will warn the user about macros:\n\n- Disable all with notification: The application displays the Trust Bar for all macros, whether signed or unsigned. This option enforces the default configuration in Office. This option also allows users to potentially enable unsigned/untrusted macros.  If a site requires the use of macros, they must be signed /approved and added to appropriate locations listed in the Trust Center Settings. \n- Disable all except digitally signed macros: The application displays the Trust Bar for digitally signed macros, allowing users to enable them or leave them disabled. Any unsigned macros are disabled, and users are not notified.\n- Disable all without notification: The application disables all macros, whether signed or unsigned, and does not notify users.\n- Enable all macros (not recommended): All macros are enabled, whether signed or unsigned. This option can significantly reduce security by allowing dangerous code to run undetected.\n\nIf you disable this policy setting, \"Disable all with notification\" will be the default setting.\n\nIf you do not configure this policy setting, when users open files in the specified applications that contain VBA macros, the applications open the files with the macros disabled and display the Trust Bar with a warning that macros are present and have been disabled. Users can inspect and edit the files if appropriate, but cannot use any disabled functionality until they enable it by clicking \"Enable Content\" on the Trust Bar. If the user clicks \"Enable Content\", then the document is added as a trusted document.\n\nImportant: If \"Disable all except digitally signed macros\" is selected, users will not be able to open unsigned Access databases.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108929","V-99825","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3494","uuid":"4f88070f-08a5-4ab1-8e15-116995a38d7d","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 074B9C65CE9A72B8F261BB88101554E86B70D736\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'VBA Macros not digitally signed must be blocked in PowerPoint.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223378","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223378","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223378","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223378r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223378","rule_version":"O365-PT-000002","rule_title":"The ability to run programs from PowerPoint must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft PowerPoint 2016 >> PowerPoint Options >> Security >> Run Programs to \"Enabled\" \"Disable (do not run any programs)\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft PowerPoint 2016 >> PowerPoint Options >> Security >> Run Programs is set to \"Enabled\" \"Disable (do not run any programs)\".\n \nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\powerpoint\\security\n\nIf the value runprograms does not exist, this is not a finding. If the value is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls the prompting and activation behavior for the \"Run Programs\" option for action buttons in PowerPoint.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can choose from three options to control how the \"Run Programs\" option functions:\n- Disable (do not run any programs). If users click an action button with the \"Run Programs\" action assigned to it, nothing will happen. This option enforces the default configuration in PowerPoint.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108931","V-99827","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"5392","uuid":"1adaa8f7-c4c6-4f13-a4fe-43b3f5c5f479","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BA30491F6F73E2C0110E397483AFD713F9986EF2\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The ability to run programs from PowerPoint must be disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223379","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223379","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223379","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223379r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223379","rule_version":"O365-PT-000003","rule_title":"Open/Save of PowerPoint 97-2003 presentations, shows, templates, and add-in files must be blocked.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft PowerPoint 2016 >> PowerPoint Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings >> PowerPoint 97-2003 presentations, shows, templates and add-in files to \"Enabled\" \"Open/Save blocked, use open policy\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft PowerPoint 2016 >> PowerPoint Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings >> PowerPoint 97-2003 presentations, shows, templates and add-in files is set to \"Enabled\" \"Open/Save blocked, use open policy\".\n \nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\powerpoint\\security\\fileblock\n\nIf the value for binaryfiles is set to REG_DWORD = 2, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to determine whether users can open, view, edit, or save PowerPoint files with the format specified by the title of this policy setting.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can specify whether users can open, view, edit, or save files.\n\nThe options that can be selected are below. Note: Not all options may be available for this policy setting.\n- Do not block: The file type will not be blocked.\n- Save blocked: Saving of the file type will be blocked.\n- Open/Save blocked, use open policy: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked. The file will open based on the policy setting configured in the \"default file block behavior\" key.\n- Block: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the file will not open.\n- Open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit the file type will not be enabled.\n- Allow editing and open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit will be enabled.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the file type will not be blocked.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108933","V-99829","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"5388","uuid":"b6d188d9-40cf-44c5-9a17-d17a17b12d96","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-223380","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223380","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223380","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223380r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223380","rule_version":"O365-PT-000004","rule_title":"The default file block behavior must be set to not open blocked files in PowerPoint.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft PowerPoint 2016 >> PowerPoint Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings \"Set default file block behavior\" to \"Enabled: Blocked files are not opened\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft PowerPoint 2016 >> PowerPoint Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings \"Set default file block behavior\" is set to \"Enabled: Blocked files are not opened\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\PowerPoint\\security\\fileblock\n\nIf the value OpenInProtectedView is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to determine if users can open, view, or edit Word files. If you enable this policy setting, you can set one of these options:\n- Blocked files are not opened.\n- Blocked files open in Protected View and cannot be edited.\n- Blocked files open in Protected View and can be edited. \n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the behavior is the same as the \"Blocked files are not opened\" setting. Users will not be able to open blocked files.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108935","V-99831","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"2168","uuid":"b1a301ec-9039-49fa-be6d-2b1c0e1bc8d2","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: AAF5A67BF2A5BD9A35E36E1B41E5F2CEF86E9AA4\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The default file block behavior must be set to not open blocked files in PowerPoint.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223381","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223381","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223381","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223381r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223381","rule_version":"O365-PT-000005","rule_title":"Encrypted macros in PowerPoint Open XML presentations must be scanned.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft PowerPoint 2016 >> PowerPoint Options >> Security \"Scan encrypted macros in PowerPoint Open XML presentations\" to \"Enabled\" and \"Scan encrypted macros\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft PowerPoint 2016 >> PowerPoint Options >> Security \"Scan encrypted macros in PowerPoint Open XML presentations\" is set to \"Enabled\" and \"Scan encrypted macros\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\PowerPoint\\security\n\nIf the value PowerPointBypassEncryptedMacroScan does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether encrypted macros in Open XML presentations are required to be scanned with anti-virus software before being opened. If you enable this policy setting, you may choose one of these options:\n\n- Scan encrypted macros: Encrypted macros are disabled unless anti-virus software is installed. Encrypted macros are scanned by your anti-virus software when you attempt to open an encrypted presentation that contains macros.\n- Scan if anti-virus software available: If anti-virus software is installed, scan the encrypted macros first before allowing them to load. If anti-virus software is not available, allow encrypted macros to load.\n- Load macros without scanning: Do not check for anti-virus software and allow macros to be loaded in an encrypted file. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the behavior will be similar to the \"Scan encrypted macros\" option.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108937","V-99833","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"9265","uuid":"668e775e-7998-4514-a6f9-d4c606ab21fd","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9B6324C1AF3A7EF0A31E6CE1B37CB255F7D3FD94\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Encrypted macros in PowerPoint Open XML presentations must be scanned.' is not present or not in use on this Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223382","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223382","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223382","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223382r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223382","rule_version":"O365-PT-000006","rule_title":"File validation in PowerPoint must be enabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft PowerPoint 2016 >> PowerPoint Options >> Security \"Turn off file validation\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft PowerPoint 2016 >> PowerPoint Options >> Security \"Turn off file validation\" is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\PowerPoint\\security\\filevalidation\n\nIf the value EnableOnLoad is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to turn off the file validation feature. If you enable this policy setting, file validation will be turned off. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, file validation will be turned on. Office Binary Documents (97-2003) are checked to see if they conform against the file format schema before they are opened.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108939","V-99835","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"9948","uuid":"4f24858a-70d1-4eed-9ce8-79a208adb304","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-223383","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223383","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223383","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223383r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223383","rule_version":"O365-PT-000007","rule_title":"Macros from the Internet must be blocked from running in PowerPoint.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft PowerPoint 2016 >> PowerPoint Options >> Security >> Trust Center \"Block macros from running in Office files from the Internet\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft PowerPoint 2016 >> PowerPoint Options >> Security >> Trust Center \"Block macros from running in Office files from the Internet\" is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\powerpoint\\security\n\nIf the value blockcontentexecutionfrominternet is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to block macros from running in Office files that come from the Internet. If you enable this policy setting, macros are blocked from running, even if \"Enable all macros\" is selected in the Macro Settings section of the Trust Center. Also, instead of having the choice to \"Enable Content\", users will receive a notification that macros are blocked from running. \n\nIf the Office file is saved to a trusted location or was previously trusted by the user, macros will be allowed to run. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the settings configured in the Macro Settings section of the Trust Center determine whether macros run in Office files that come from the Internet.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108941","V-99837","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"5151","uuid":"81939d37-11f8-4c82-84a7-2533c0a5114f","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0CF46249ADEAFE07C9437D49B27B5D53467976D8\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Macros from the Internet must be blocked from running in PowerPoint.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223384","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223384","title":"SRG-APP-000131","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223384","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000131","rule_id_src":"SV-223384r1016170_rule","rule_id":"SV-223384","rule_version":"O365-PT-000008","rule_title":"Unsigned add-ins in PowerPoint must be blocked with no Trust Bar Notification to the user.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft PowerPoint 2016 >> PowerPoint Options >> Security >> Trust Center \"Disable Trust Bar Notification for unsigned application add-ins and block them\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft PowerPoint 2016 >> PowerPoint Options >> Security >> Trust Center \"Disable Trust Bar Notification for unsigned application add-ins and block them\" is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\Microsoft\\office\\16.0\\powerpoint\\security\n\nIf the value notbpromptunsignedaddin is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether the specified Office application notifies users when unsigned application add-ins are loaded or silently disable such add-ins without notification. This policy setting only applies if the \"Require that application add-ins are signed by Trusted Publisher\" policy setting is enabled, which prevents users from changing this policy setting. \n\nIf this policy setting is enabled, applications automatically disable unsigned add-ins without informing users. \n\nIf this policy setting is disabled, if this application is configured to require that all add-ins be signed by a trusted publisher, any unsigned add-ins the application loads will be disabled and the application will display the Trust Bar at the top of the active window. The Trust Bar contains a message that informs users about the unsigned add-in. \n\nIf this policy setting is not configured, the disable behavior applies, and in addition, users can configure this requirement themselves in the \"Add-ins\" category of the Trust Center for the application.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108943","V-99839","CCI-003992","CCI-001749"],"reference_identifier":"6926","uuid":"37dc6a35-09ff-43ca-9afc-28d3ed272365","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B55B983D2A9AA0B997ABACCA6BDADB54046DBA29\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Unsigned add-ins in PowerPoint must be blocked with no Trust Bar Notification to the user.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223385","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223385","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223385","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223385r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223385","rule_version":"O365-PT-000009","rule_title":"Files downloaded from the Internet must be opened in Protected view in PowerPoint.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft PowerPoint 2016 >> PowerPoint Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Protected View \"Do not open files from the Internet zone in Protected View\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft PowerPoint 2016 >> PowerPoint Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Protected View \"Do not open files from the Internet zone in Protected View\" is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\PowerPoint\\security\\protectedview\n\nIf the value DisableInternetFilesInPV is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to determine if files downloaded from the Internet zone open in Protected View. If you enable this policy setting, files downloaded from the Internet zone do not open in Protected View. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, files downloaded from the Internet zone open in Protected View.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108945","V-99841","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"5333","uuid":"cbd108d8-6f0e-4501-8178-442a099a6173","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FC7779F7A3CE2949C63A3BA31CD8F4816F2A959D\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Files downloaded from the Internet must be opened in Protected view in PowerPoint.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223386","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223386","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223386","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223386r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223386","rule_version":"O365-PT-000010","rule_title":"PowerPoint attachments opened from Outlook must be in Protected View.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft PowerPoint 2016 >> PowerPoint Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Protected View \"Turn off Protected View for attachments opened from Outlook\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft PowerPoint 2016 >> PowerPoint Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Protected View \"Turn off Protected View for attachments opened from Outlook\" is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\PowerPoint\\security\\protectedview\n\nIf the value DisableAttachmentsInPV is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows for determining whether PowerPoint files in Outlook attachments open in Protected View. If enabling this policy setting, Outlook attachments do not open in Protected View. If disabling or not configuring this policy setting, Outlook attachments open in Protected View.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108947","V-99843","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"9805","uuid":"21190e7b-06a1-4811-b405-d1c9b4c3b6f7","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 895DA6B41968C6997BB569571DF5F7CF8BC49408\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'PowerPoint attachments opened from Outlook must be in Protected View.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223387","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223387","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223387","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223387r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223387","rule_version":"O365-PT-000011","rule_title":"Files in unsafe locations must be opened in Protected view in PowerPoint.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft PowerPoint 2016 >> PowerPoint Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Protected View \"Do not open files in unsafe locations in Protected View\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft PowerPoint 2016 >> PowerPoint Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Protected View \"Do not open files in unsafe locations in Protected View\" is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\PowerPoint\\security\\protectedview\n\nIf the value DisableUnsafeLocationsInPV is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether files located in unsafe locations will open in Protected View. If unsafe locations have not been specified, only the \"Downloaded Program Files\" and \"Temporary Internet Files\" folders are considered unsafe locations. If enabling this policy setting, files located in unsafe locations do not open in Protected View. If disabling or not configuring this policy setting, files located in unsafe locations open in Protected View.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108949","V-99845","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"2880","uuid":"18e924fc-7bba-4c74-9812-f3cf3ebc72c1","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B053119309CE0ABCFBB8C29E5E9AAB1BEEE71B45\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Files in unsafe locations must be opened in Protected view in PowerPoint.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223388","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223388","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223388","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223388r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223388","rule_version":"O365-PT-000012","rule_title":"If file validation fails, files must be opened in Protected view in PowerPoint with ability to edit disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft PowerPoint 2016 >> PowerPoint Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Protected View >> Set document behavior if file validation fails to \"Enabled: Open in Protected View\". \n\nUncheck the \"Allow edit\" check box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft PowerPoint 2016 >> PowerPoint Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Protected View >> Set document behavior if file validation fails is set to \"Enabled: Open in Protected View\". Verify the check box for \"Allow edit\" is not selected.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\PowerPoint\\security\\filevalidation\n\nIf the value openinprotectedview does not exist, this is not a finding. \n\nIf both the value for openinprotectedview is REG_DWORD = 1 and the value for DisableEditFromPV is set to REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls how Office handles documents when they fail file validation. If you enable this policy setting, you can configure the following options for files that fail file validation:\n\n- Block files completely. Users cannot open the files.\n- Open files in Protected View and disallow edit. Users cannot edit the files. This is also how Office handles the files if you disable this policy setting.\n- Open files in Protected View and allow edit. Users can edit the files. This is also how Office handles the files if you do not configure this policy setting.\n\nIf you disable this policy setting, Office follows the \"Open files in Protected View and disallow edit\" behavior. If you do not configure this policy setting, Office follows the \"Open files in Protected View and allow edit\" behavior.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108951","V-99847","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"4775","uuid":"80646f49-4616-4495-9e60-d1e3ef66d1ed","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5E077D287E29B341DC711AFD6F6E292240D26E95\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'If file validation fails, files must be opened in Protected view in PowerPoint with ability to edit disabled.' is not present or not in use on this Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223389","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223389","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223389","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223389r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223389","rule_version":"O365-PT-000013","rule_title":"The use of network locations must be ignored in PowerPoint.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft PowerPoint 2016 >> PowerPoint Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Trusted Locations \"Allow Trusted Locations on the network\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft PowerPoint 2016 >> PowerPoint Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Trusted Locations \"Allow Trusted Locations on the network\" is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\PowerPoint\\security\\trusted locations\n\nIf the value AllowNetworkLocations is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether trusted locations on the network can be used. If you enable this policy setting, users can specify trusted locations on network shares or in other remote locations that are not under their direct control by clicking the \"Add new location\" button in the Trusted Locations section of the Trust Center. Content, code, and add-ins are allowed to load from trusted locations with minimal security and without prompting the user for permission. \n\nIf you disable this policy setting, the selected application ignores any network locations listed in the Trusted Locations section of the Trust Center. If you also deploy Trusted Locations via Group Policy, you should verify whether any of them are remote locations. If any of them are remote locations and you do not allow remote locations via this policy setting, those policy keys that point to remote locations will be ignored on client computers. \n\nDisabling this policy setting does not delete any network locations from the Trusted Locations list, but causes disruption for users who add network locations to the Trusted Locations list. Users are also prevented from adding new network locations to the Trusted Locations list in the Trust Center. It is recommended that you do not enable this policy setting, as the \"Allow Trusted Locations on my network (not recommended) check box also states. Therefore, in practice, it should be possible to disable this policy setting in most situations without causing significant usability issues for most users. If you do not enable this policy setting, users can select the \"Allow Trusted Locations on my network (not recommended)\" check box if desired and then specify trusted locations by clicking the \"Add new location\" button.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108953","V-99849","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"1612","uuid":"c0c22d2c-0402-4fd8-977b-c3e9050902df","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F1B897F67FB6DC0034881103744C8A91313FE759\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The use of network locations must be ignored in PowerPoint.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223390","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223390","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223390","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223390r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223390","rule_version":"O365-PU-000001","rule_title":"Publisher must be configured to prompt the user when another application programmatically opens a macro.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Publisher 2016 >> Security >> Publisher Automation Security Level to \"Enabled\" \"By UI (prompted)\"","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Publisher 2016 >> Security >> Publisher Automation Security Level is set to \"Enabled\" \"By UI (prompted)\".\n \nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\common\\security\n\nIf the value automationsecuritypublisher is REG_DWORD = 2, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether the specified Office application notifies users when unsigned application add-ins are loaded or silently disable such add-ins without notification. This policy setting only applies if you enable the \"Require that application add-ins are signed by Trusted Publisher\" policy setting, which prevents users from changing this policy setting.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, applications automatically disable unsigned add-ins without informing users.\n \nIf you disable this policy setting, if this application is configured to require that all add-ins be signed by a trusted publisher, any unsigned add-ins the application loads will be disabled and the application will display the Trust Bar at the top of the active window. The Trust Bar contains a message that informs users about the unsigned add-in.\n\nIf you do not configure this policy setting, the disable behavior applies, and in addition, users can configure this requirement themselves in the \"Add-ins\" category of the Trust Center for the application.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108961","V-99857","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"3890","uuid":"eabc3463-5328-4ac2-9a0a-7a0c15411540","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DD2F499CC66A62D9AE8220E2B6F0CAFC7AC28CCE\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Publisher must be configured to prompt the user when another application programmatically opens a macro.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223391","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223391","title":"SRG-APP-000131","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223391","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000131","rule_id_src":"SV-223391r1016171_rule","rule_id":"SV-223391","rule_version":"O365-PU-000002","rule_title":"Publisher must automatically disable unsigned add-ins without informing users.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Publisher 2016 >> Security >> Trust Center >> Disable Trust Bar Notification for unsigned application add-ins to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Publisher 2016 >> Security >> Trust Center >> Disable Trust Bar Notification for unsigned application add-ins is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\publisher\\security\n\nIf the value notbpromptunsignedaddin is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether the specified Office application notifies users when unsigned application add-ins are loaded or silently disable such add-ins without notification. This policy setting only applies if the \"Require that application add-ins are signed by Trusted Publisher\" policy setting is enabled, which prevents users from changing this policy setting.\n\nIf this policy setting is enabled, applications automatically disable unsigned add-ins without informing users.\n \nIf this policy setting is disabled, if this application is configured to require that all add-ins be signed by a trusted publisher, any unsigned add-ins the application loads will be disabled and the application will display the Trust Bar at the top of the active window. The Trust Bar contains a message that informs users about the unsigned add-in.\n\nIf this policy setting is not configured, the disable behavior applies, and in addition, users can configure this requirement themselves in the \"Add-ins\" category of the Trust Center for the application.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108963","V-99859","CCI-003992","CCI-001749"],"reference_identifier":"7656","uuid":"9ded982a-30cc-4e9a-8aff-742d65685e89","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1963B16FEEE0957E73FE074DE136A8A284D92943\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Publisher must automatically disable unsigned add-ins without informing users.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223392","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223392","title":"SRG-APP-000131","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223392","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000131","rule_id_src":"SV-223392r1016172_rule","rule_id":"SV-223392","rule_version":"O365-PU-000003","rule_title":"Publisher must disable all unsigned VBA macros.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Publisher 2016 >> Security >> Trust Center >> VBA Macro Notification Settings >> VBA Macro Notification Settings must be set to \"Enabled\" and \"Disable all except digitally signed macros\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Set policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Publisher 2016 >> Security >> Trust Center >> VBA Macro Notification Settings >> VBA Macro Notification Settings to \"Enabled\" \"Disable all except digitally signed macros\".\n \nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\publisher\\security\n\nIf the value vbawarnings is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding. A value of REG_DWORD = 4 is also acceptable. If the registry key does not exist or is not configured properly, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls how the specified applications warn users when Visual Basic for Applications (VBA) macros are present.\n\nIf this policy setting is enabled, users can choose from four options for determining how the specified applications will warn the user about macros:\n \n- Disable all with notification: The application displays the Trust Bar for all macros, whether signed or unsigned. This option enforces the default configuration in Office. This option also allows users to potentially enable unsigned/untrusted macros. If a site requires the use of macros, they must be signed/approved and added to appropriate locations listed in the Trust Center Settings. \n- Disable all except digitally signed macros: The application displays the Trust Bar for digitally signed macros, allowing users to enable them or leave them disabled. Any unsigned macros are disabled, and users are not notified.\n- Disable all without notification: The application disables all macros, whether signed or unsigned, and does not notify users.\n- Enable all macros (not recommended): All macros are enabled, whether signed or unsigned. This option can significantly reduce security by allowing dangerous code to run undetected.\n \nIf this policy setting is disabled, \"Disable all with notification\" will be the default setting.\n \nIf this policy setting is not configured, when users open files in the specified applications that contain VBA macros, the applications open the files with the macros disabled and display the Trust Bar with a warning that macros are present and have been disabled. Users can inspect and edit the files if appropriate, but cannot use any disabled functionality until they enable it by clicking \"Enable Content\" on the Trust Bar. If the user clicks \"Enable Content\", then the document is added as a trusted document.\n \nImportant: If \"Disable all except digitally signed macros\" is selected, users will not be able to open unsigned Access databases.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108965","V-99861","CCI-003992","CCI-001749"],"reference_identifier":"9954","uuid":"4e10189a-1fa9-435b-b18b-3cf0e7d06cd6","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1C1DA3258AD63D70220375532CE8C39338D32941\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Publisher must disable all unsigned VBA macros.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223393","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223393","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223393","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-223393r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223393","rule_version":"O365-VI-000001","rule_title":"VBA Macros not digitally signed must be blocked in Visio.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates/Microsoft Visio 2016 >> Visio Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> VBA Macro Notification Settings to \"Enabled\" and select \"Disable all except digitally signed macros\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates/Microsoft Visio 2016 >> Visio Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> VBA Macro Notification Settings is set to \"Enabled\" and \"Disable all except digitally signed macros\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\visio\\security\n\nIf the value for vbawarnings is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding. A value of REG_DWORD =  4 is also acceptable. If the registry key does not exist or is not configured properly, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls how the specified applications warn users when Visual Basic for Applications (VBA) macros are present.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can choose from four options for determining how the specified applications will warn the user about macros:\n\n- Disable all with notification: The application displays the Trust Bar for all macros, whether signed or unsigned. This option enforces the default configuration in Office. This option also allows users to potentially enable unsigned/untrusted macros.  If a site requires the use of macros, they must be signed /approved and added to appropriate locations listed in the Trust Center Settings. \n- Disable all except digitally signed macros: The application displays the Trust Bar for digitally signed macros, allowing users to enable them or leave them disabled. Any unsigned macros are disabled, and users are not notified.\n- Disable all without notification: The application disables all macros, whether signed or unsigned, and does not notify users.\n- Enable all macros (not recommended): All macros are enabled, whether signed or unsigned. This option can significantly reduce security by allowing dangerous code to run undetected.\n\nIf you disable this policy setting, \"Disable all with notification\" will be the default setting.\n\nIf you do not configure this policy setting, when users open files in the specified applications that contain VBA macros, the applications open the files with the macros disabled and display the Trust Bar with a warning that macros are present and have been disabled. Users can inspect and edit the files if appropriate, but cannot use any disabled functionality until they enable it by clicking \"Enable Content\" on the Trust Bar. If the user clicks \"Enable Content\", then the document is added as a trusted document.\n\nImportant: If \"Disable all except digitally signed macros\" is selected, users will not be able to open unsigned Access databases.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108967","V-99863","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"8104","uuid":"dbb083e8-184b-4e58-bb29-d823785386d5","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A9351AAFADFCF32AD8182ACB685F2CB9F67C6AF6\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'VBA Macros not digitally signed must be blocked in Visio.' is not present or not in use on this Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223394","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223394","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223394","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223394r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223394","rule_version":"O365-VI-000002","rule_title":"Trusted Locations on the network must be disabled in Visio.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Visio 2016 >> Visio Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Allow Trusted Locations on the network to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Visio 2016 >> Visio Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Allow Trusted Locations on the network is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\visio\\security\\trusted locations\n\nIf the value for allownetworklocations is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether trusted locations on the network can be used.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, users can specify trusted locations on network shares or in other remote locations that are not under their direct control by clicking the \"Add new location\" button in the Trusted Locations section of the Trust Center. Content, code, and add-ins are allowed to load from trusted locations with minimal security and without prompting the user for permission.\n\nIf you disable this policy setting, the selected application ignores any network locations listed in the Trusted Locations section of the Trust Center. \n\nIf you also deploy Trusted Locations via Group Policy, you should verify whether any of them are remote locations. If any of them are remote locations and you do not allow remote locations via this policy setting, those policy keys that point to remote locations will be ignored on client computers.\n\nDisabling this policy setting does not delete any network locations from the Trusted Locations list, but causes disruption for users who add network locations to the Trusted Locations list. Users are also prevented from adding new network locations to the Trusted Locations list in the Trust Center. We recommended that you do not enable this policy setting as the \"Allow Trusted Locations on my network (not recommended)\" check box also states. Therefore, in practice, it should be possible to disable this policy setting in most situations without causing significant usability issues for most users.\n\nIf you do not enable this policy setting, users can select the \"Allow Trusted Locations on my network (not recommended)\" check box if desired and then specify trusted locations by clicking the \"Add new location\" button.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108969","V-99865","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"8692","uuid":"81d67408-9468-476e-b2f0-274e093b2f60","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0C4D4FC87A1F043F2EEDD64FCA6375D9EB073E3B\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Trusted Locations on the network must be disabled in Visio.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223395","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223395","title":"SRG-APP-000131","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223395","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000131","rule_id_src":"SV-223395r1016173_rule","rule_id":"SV-223395","rule_version":"O365-VI-000003","rule_title":"Visio must automatically disable unsigned add-ins without informing users.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Visio 2016 >> Visio Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Disable Trust Bar Notification for unsigned application add-ins and block them to Enabled.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Visio 2016 >> Visio Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Disable Trust Bar Notification for unsigned application add-ins and block them is set to Enabled.\n \nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\visio\\security\n\nIf the value notbpromptunsignedaddin is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether the specified Office application notifies users when unsigned application add-ins are loaded or silently disable such add-ins without notification. This policy setting only applies if the \"Require that application add-ins are signed by Trusted Publisher\" policy setting is enabled, which prevents users from changing this policy setting.\n\nIf this policy setting is enabled, applications automatically disable unsigned add-ins without informing users.\n \nIf this policy setting is disabled, if this application is configured to require that all add-ins be signed by a trusted publisher, any unsigned add-ins the application loads will be disabled and the application will display the Trust Bar at the top of the active window. The Trust Bar contains a message that informs users about the unsigned add-in.\n\nIf this policy setting is not configured, the disable behavior applies, and in addition, users can configure this requirement themselves in the \"Add-ins\" category of the Trust Center for the application.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108971","V-99867","CCI-003992","CCI-001749"],"reference_identifier":"2121","uuid":"968b9cb2-fa07-49e2-9bfc-3013502c418a","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BE5A5E16658D9B5B53608058F8810A4E225B289A\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Visio must automatically disable unsigned add-ins without informing users.' is not present or not in use on this Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223396","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223396","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223396","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223396r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223396","rule_version":"O365-VI-000004","rule_title":"Visio 2000-2002 Binary Drawings, Templates and Stencils must be blocked.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Visio 2016 >> Visio Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings \"Visio 2000-2002 Binary Drawings, Templates and Stencils\" to \"Enabled\" and \"Open/Save blocked\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Visio 2016 >> Visio Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings \"Visio 2000-2002 Binary Drawings, Templates and Stencils\" is set to \"Enabled\" and \"Open/Save blocked\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\visio\\security\\fileblock\n\nIf the value \"visio2000files\" is REG_DWORD = 2, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to determine whether users can open or save Visio files with the format specified by the title of this policy setting.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can specify whether users can open or save files.\n\nThe options that can be selected are below. Note: Not all options may be available for this policy setting.\n\n-Do not block: The file type will not be blocked.\n-Save blocked: Saving of the filet type will be blocked.\n-Open/Save blocked: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the file type will be blocked.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108973","V-99869","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"3919","uuid":"32a0b861-ecc8-474a-b2c3-757d04f4c828","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E5E8C84B08FD1249FC57C8491371A8CED96BE448\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Visio 2000-2002 Binary Drawings, Templates and Stencils must be blocked.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223397","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223397","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223397","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223397r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223397","rule_version":"O365-VI-000005","rule_title":"Visio 2003-2010 Binary Drawings, Templates and Stencils must be blocked.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Visio 2016 >> Visio Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings \"Visio 2003-2010 Binary Drawings, Templates and Stencils\" to \"Enabled\" and \"Open/Save blocked\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Visio 2016 >> Visio Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings \"Visio 2003-2010 Binary Drawings, Templates and Stencils\" is set to \"Enabled\" and \"Open/Save blocked\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\visio\\security\\fileblock\n\nIf the value \"visio2003files\" is REG_DWORD = 2, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to determine whether users can open or save Visio files with the format specified by the title of this policy setting.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can specify whether users can open or save files.\n\nThe options that can be selected are below. Note: Not all options may be available for this policy setting.\n\n-Do not block: The file type will not be blocked.\n-Save blocked: Saving of the filet type will be blocked.\n-Open/Save blocked: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the file type will be blocked.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108975","V-99871","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"5619","uuid":"c7f83522-2233-491c-9c4d-6311d3d35dfc","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1033423BF0673CED2ED137755BEE90EA39CDA980\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Visio 2003-2010 Binary Drawings, Templates and Stencils must be blocked.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223398","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223398","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223398","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223398r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223398","rule_version":"O365-VI-000006","rule_title":"Visio 5.0 or earlier Binary Drawings, Templates and Stencils must be blocked.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Visio 2016 >> Visio Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings \"Visio 5.0 or earlier Binary Drawings, Templates and Stencils\" to \"Enabled\" and \"Open/Save blocked\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Visio 2016 >> Visio Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings \"Visio 5.0 or earlier Binary Drawings, Templates and Stencils\" is set to \"Enabled\" and \"Open/Save blocked\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\visio\\security\\fileblock\n\nIf the value \"visio50andearlierfiles\" is REG_DWORD = 2, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to determine whether users can open or save Visio files with the format specified by the title of this policy setting.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can specify whether users can open or save files.\n\nThe options that can be selected are below. Note: Not all options may be available for this policy setting.\n\n-Do not block: The file type will not be blocked.\n-Save blocked: Saving of the filet type will be blocked.\n-Open/Save blocked: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the file type will be blocked.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108977","V-99873","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"6598","uuid":"7e38cd1b-5e00-4b71-be2e-cc755c6b7856","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A22E90BE7B973D66FB1E6269E5B928D0C80F9F7E\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Visio 5.0 or earlier Binary Drawings, Templates and Stencils must be blocked.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223399","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223399","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223399","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223399r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223399","rule_version":"O365-VI-000007","rule_title":"Macros must be blocked from running in Visio files from the Internet.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Visio 2016 >>  Visio Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Block macros from running in Office files from the Internet  to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Visio 2016 >>  Visio Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Block macros from running in Office files from the Internet is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\visio\\security\n\nIf the value blockcontentexecutionfrominternet is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to block macros from running in Office files that come from the Internet.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, macros are blocked from running, even if \u201cEnable all macros\u201d is selected in the Macro Settings section of the Trust Center. Also, instead of having the choice to \u201cEnable Content\u201d, users will receive a notification that macros are blocked from running. If the Office file is saved to a trusted location or was previously trusted by the user, macros will be allowed to run.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the settings configured in the Macro Settings section of the Trust Center determine whether macros run in Office files that come from the Internet.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108979","V-99875","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3623","uuid":"351d4584-e7ee-4137-9d04-c261cae17414","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 293DF5DED96A7B4193B1E62AFE5B5558C5DEDBB7\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Macros must be blocked from running in Visio files from the Internet.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223400","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223400","title":"SRG-APP-000131","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223400","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000131","rule_id_src":"SV-223400r1016174_rule","rule_id":"SV-223400","rule_version":"O365-WD-000001","rule_title":"Word must automatically disable unsigned add-ins without informing users.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Word 2016 >> Word Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Disable Trust Bar Notification for unsigned application add-ins and block them to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Word 2016 >> Word Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Disable Trust Bar Notification for unsigned application add-ins and block them is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\word\\security\n\nIf the value for notbpromptunsignedaddin is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether the specified Office application notifies users when unsigned application add-ins are loaded or silently disable such add-ins without notification. This policy setting only applies if the \"Require that application add-ins are signed by Trusted Publisher\" policy setting is enabled, which prevents users from changing this policy setting.\n\nIf this policy setting is enabled, applications automatically disable unsigned add-ins without informing users.\n \nIf this policy setting is disabled, if this application is configured to require that all add-ins be signed by a trusted publisher, any unsigned add-ins the application loads will be disabled and the application will display the Trust Bar at the top of the active window. The Trust Bar contains a message that informs users about the unsigned add-in.\n\nIf this policy setting is not configured, the disable behavior applies, and in addition, users can configure this requirement themselves in the \"Add-ins\" category of the Trust Center for the application.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108981","V-99877","CCI-003992","CCI-001749"],"reference_identifier":"1082","uuid":"9b9eb0f6-c00c-4654-b45a-3746258dec91","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2D05E395CCD000F5E08642E10D785B8AA58D067C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Word must automatically disable unsigned add-ins without informing users.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223401","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223401","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223401","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id_src":"SV-223401r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223401","rule_version":"O365-WD-000002","rule_title":"In Word, encrypted macros must be scanned.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Word 2016 >> Word Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Scan encrypted macros in Word Open XML documents to \"Enabled\" \"Scan encrypted macros (default)\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Word 2016 >> Word Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Scan encrypted macros in Word Open XML documents is set to \"Enabled\" \"Scan encrypted macros (default)\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\word\\security\n\nIf the value WordBypassEncryptedMacroScan does not exist, this is not a finding. If the value is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether encrypted macros in Open XML documents be are required to be scanned with anti-virus software before being opened.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you may choose one of these options:\n- Scan encrypted macros: encrypted macros are disabled unless anti-virus software is installed. Encrypted macros are scanned by your anti-virus software when you attempt to open an encrypted workbook that contains macros.\n- Scan if anti-virus software available: if anti-virus software is installed, scan the encrypted macros first before allowing them to load. If anti-virus software is not available, allow encrypted macros to load.\n- Load macros without scanning: do not check for anti-virus software and allow macros to be loaded in an encrypted file.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the behavior will be similar to the \"Scan encrypted macros\" option.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108983","V-99879","CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"6884","uuid":"a854e5ea-be94-4abe-95d2-294d5aec5b2b","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B582A6B1511B5D52EDA9FF56B6B36814BF351F46\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'In Word, encrypted macros must be scanned.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223402","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223402","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223402","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223402r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223402","rule_version":"O365-WD-000003","rule_title":"Files downloaded from the Internet must be opened in Protected view in Word.","fix_text":"Set the policy setting, User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Word 2016 >> Word Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Protected View >> Do not open files from the Internet zone in Protected View to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy setting, User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Word 2016 >> Word Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Protected View >> Do not open files from the Internet zone in Protected View is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\word\\security\\protectedview\n\nIf the value for disableinternetfilesinpv is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding. If the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is REG_DWORD = 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to determine if files downloaded from the Internet zone open in Protected View.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, files downloaded from the Internet zone do not open in Protected View.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, files downloaded from the Internet zone open in Protected View.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108985","V-99881","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"9415","uuid":"d52ae4a0-d926-4a5f-b199-494b87ab402d","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2F0F1254372D97ACD01CAFF1640DE6CD8D8F3148\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Files downloaded from the Internet must be opened in Protected view in Word.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223403","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223403","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223403","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223403r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223403","rule_version":"O365-WD-000004","rule_title":"Files located in unsafe locations must be opened in Protected view in Word.","fix_text":"Set the policy setting, User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Word 2016 >> Word Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Protected View >> Do not open files in unsafe locations in Protected View to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Word 2016 >> Word Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Protected View >> Do not open files in unsafe locations in Protected View is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\word\\security\\protectedview.\n\nIf the value for disableunsafelocationsinpv is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding. If the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is REG_DWORD = 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting lets you determine if files located in unsafe locations will open in Protected View. If you have not specified unsafe locations, only the \"Downloaded Program Files\" and \"Temporary Internet Files\" folders are considered unsafe locations.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, files located in unsafe locations do not open in Protected View.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, files located in unsafe locations open in Protected View.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108987","V-99883","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"8499","uuid":"2ad75045-00d1-4a6d-85a5-7b6d5e65d8c6","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A0AC53AF2D87C99D37543F0DD3EE2B011C097D83\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Files located in unsafe locations must be opened in Protected view in Word.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223404","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223404","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223404","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223404r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223404","rule_version":"O365-WD-000005","rule_title":"If file validation fails, files must be opened in Protected view in Word with ability to edit disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Word 2016 >> Word Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Protected View >> Set document behavior if file validation fails to \"Enabled: Open in Protected View\". \n\nUncheck the \"Allow edit\" check box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Word 2016 >> Word Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Protected View >> Set document behavior if file validation fails is set to \"Enabled: Open in Protected View\". Verify the check box for \"Allow edit\" is not selected.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\Word\\security\\filevalidation\n\nIf the value openinprotectedview does not exist, this is not a finding. \n\nIf both the value for openinprotectedview is REG_DWORD = 1 and the value for DisableEditFromPV is set to REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls how Office handles documents when they fail file validation. \n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can configure the following options for files that fail file validation:\n- Block files completely. Users cannot open the files.\n- Open files in Protected View and disallow edit. Users cannot edit the files. This is also how Office handles the files if you disable this policy setting.\n- Open files in Protected View and allow edit. Users can edit the files. This is also how Office handles the files if you do not configure this policy setting.\n\nIf you disable this policy setting, Office follows the \"Open files in Protected View and disallow edit\" behavior.\n\nIf you do not configure this policy setting, Office follows the \"Open files in Protected View and allow edit\" behavior.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108989","V-99885","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"8969","uuid":"b8e4bddd-c390-47ef-b740-82e311c537b5","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 85B21BD7F8618D60732D8683563D7C7D220A597B\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'If file validation fails, files must be opened in Protected view in Word with ability to edit disabled.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223405","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223405","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223405","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223405r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223405","rule_version":"O365-WD-000006","rule_title":"Word attachments opened from Outlook must be in Protected View.","fix_text":"Set policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Word 2016 >> Word Options >> Security>> Trust Center>> Protected View >> Turn off Protected View for attachments opened from Outlook to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Word 2016 >> Word Options >> Security>> Trust Center>> Protected View >> Turn off Protected View for attachments opened from Outlook is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\word\\security\\protectedview\n\nIf the value for disableattachmentsinpv is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to determine if Word files in Outlook attachments open in Protected View.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, Outlook attachments do not open in Protected View.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Outlook attachments open in Protected View.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108991","V-99887","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"1907","uuid":"57465ba6-e988-4f24-8f9f-48faa8dd9907","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E90246E4E374D0B3A90B420A53BF31E4D279796F\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Word attachments opened from Outlook must be in Protected View.' is not present or not in use on this Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223406","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223406","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223406","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223406r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223406","rule_version":"O365-WD-000007","rule_title":"The default file block behavior must be set to not open blocked files in Word.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Word 2016 >> Word Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings \"Set default file block behavior\" to \"Enabled: Blocked files are not opened\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Word 2016 >> Word Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings \"Set default file block behavior\" is set to \"Enabled: Blocked files are not opened\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\word\\security\\fileblock\n\nIf the value OpenInProtectedView is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to determine if users can open, view, or edit Word files.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can set one of these options:\n- Blocked files are not opened.\n- Blocked files open in Protected View and cannot be edited.\n- Blocked files open in Protected View and can be edited.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the behavior is the same as the \"Blocked files are not opened\" setting. Users will not be able to open blocked files.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108993","V-99889","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"8489","uuid":"23960ee7-0b16-48f7-b4a5-ca3120e97c4b","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F7EC76AC79F13335FC5E22ABE943DD28104BE837\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The default file block behavior must be set to not open blocked files in Word.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223407","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223407","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223407","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223407r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223407","rule_version":"O365-WD-000008","rule_title":"Open/Save of Word 2 and earlier binary documents and templates must be blocked.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Word 2016 >> Word Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings \"Word 2 and earlier binary documents and templates\" to \"Enabled: Open/Save blocked, use open policy\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Word 2016 >> Word Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings \"Word 2 and earlier binary documents and templates\" is set to \"Enabled: Open/Save blocked, use open policy\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\word\\security\\fileblock\n\nIf the value Word2Files is REG_DWORD = 2, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to determine whether users can open, view, edit, or save Word files with the format specified by the title of this policy setting. If you enable this policy setting, you can specify whether users can open, view, edit, or save files. The options that can be selected are below. Note: Not all options may be available for this policy setting.\n\n- Do not block: The file type will not be blocked.\n- Save blocked: Saving of the file type will be blocked.\n- Open/Save blocked, use open policy: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked. The file will open based on the policy setting configured in the \"default file block behavior\" key.\n- Block: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the file will not open.\n- Open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit the file type will not be enabled.\n- Allow editing and open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit will be enabled. \n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the file type will be blocked.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108995","V-99891","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"4810","uuid":"5c3deeda-8588-4ea3-ab89-4cb53ed382b0","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 44D8920D659A60B992C4F234BDB5C3F8B0C0DC87\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Open/Save of Word 2 and earlier binary documents and templates must be blocked.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223408","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223408","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223408","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223408r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223408","rule_version":"O365-WD-000009","rule_title":"Open/Save of Word 2000 binary documents and templates must be blocked.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Word 2016 >> Word Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings \"Word 2000 binary documents and templates\" to \"Enabled: Open/Save blocked, use open policy\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Word 2016 >> Word Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings \"Word 2000 binary documents and templates\" is set to \"Enabled: Open/Save blocked, use open policy\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\word\\security\\fileblock\n\nIf the value Word2000Files is REG_DWORD = 2, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to determine whether users can open, view, edit, or save Word files with the format specified by the title of this policy setting. If you enable this policy setting, you can specify whether users can open, view, edit, or save files. The options that can be selected are below. Note: Not all options may be available for this policy setting.\n\n- Do not block: The file type will not be blocked.\n- Save blocked: Saving of the file type will be blocked.\n- Open/Save blocked, use open policy: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked. The file will open based on the policy setting configured in the \"default file block behavior\" key.\n- Block: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the file will not open.\n- Open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit the file type will not be enabled.\n- Allow editing and open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit will be enabled. \n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the file type will not be blocked.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108997","V-99893","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"3425","uuid":"7f959336-5b86-472c-9cc5-f09033cfb459","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 326FE55A081B6AC869B42B9B0558EDF671B113B2\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Open/Save of Word 2000 binary documents and templates must be blocked.' matches the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223409","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223409","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223409","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223409r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223409","rule_version":"O365-WD-000010","rule_title":"Open/Save of Word 2003 binary documents and templates must be blocked.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Word 2016 >> Word Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings \"Word 2003 binary documents and templates\" to \"Enabled: Open/Save blocked, use open policy\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Word 2016 >> Word Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings \"Word 2003 binary documents and templates\" is set to \"Enabled: Open/Save blocked, use open policy\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\word\\security\\fileblock\n\nIf the value word2003files is REG_DWORD = 2, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to determine whether users can open, view, edit, or save Word files with the format specified by the title of this policy setting. If you enable this policy setting, you can specify whether users can open, view, edit, or save files. The options that can be selected are below. Note: Not all options may be available for this policy setting.\n\n- Do not block: The file type will not be blocked.\n- Save blocked: Saving of the file type will be blocked.\n- Open/Save blocked, use open policy: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked. The file will open based on the policy setting configured in the \"default file block behavior\" key.\n- Block: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the file will not open.\n- Open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit the file type will not be enabled.\n- Allow editing and open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit will be enabled. \n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the file type will not be blocked.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-108999","V-99895","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"6489","uuid":"6921e98e-24f3-4c24-a33f-2546c9aae94a","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-baa2c2a025f8","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365ProPlus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6F1B1C17E27CDD9ED13842E9750B31FE27515527\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Open/Save of Word 2003 binary documents and templates must be blocked.' was not present or did not match the expected value on Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus."},{"group_id_src":"V-223410","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223410","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223410","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","rule_id_src":"SV-223410r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223410","rule_version":"O365-WD-000011","rule_title":"Open/Save of Word 2007 and later binary documents and templates must be blocked.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Word 2016 >> Word Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings \"Word 2007 and later binary documents and templates\" to \"Enabled: Open/Save blocked, use open policy\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Word 2016 >> Word Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings \"Word 2007 and later binary documents and templates\" is set to \"Enabled: Open/Save blocked, use open policy\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\word\\security\\fileblock\n\nIf the value word2007files is REG_DWORD = 2, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to determine whether users can open, view, edit, or save Word files with the format specified by the title of this policy setting. If you enable this policy setting, you can specify whether users can open, view, edit, or save files. The options that can be selected are below. Note: Not all options may be available for this policy setting.\n\n- Do not block: The file type will not be blocked.\n- Save blocked: Saving of the file type will be blocked.\n- Open/Save blocked, use open policy: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked. The file will open based on the policy setting configured in the \"default file block behavior\" key.\n- Block: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the file will not open.\n- Open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit the file type will not be enabled.\n- Allow editing and open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit will be enabled. \n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the file type will not be blocked.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-109001","V-99897","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"1472","uuid":"bd85c8aa-dc4d-493f-a20f-290765e91a69","stig_uuid":"1a7c5017-94bc-46a6-b24b-ba